Pset_ActionRequest.name: Pset_ActionRequest
Pset_ActionRequest.definition: An action request is a request for an action to fulfill a need.  HISTORY: IFC4: Removed RequestSourceType, RequestDescription, Status

properties.name: RequestSourceLabel
properties.definition: A specific name or label that further qualifies the identity of a request source. In the event of an email, this may be the email address.

properties.name: RequestSourceName
properties.definition: The person making the request, where known.

properties.name: RequestComments
properties.definition: Comments that may be made on the request.

Pset_ActorCommon.name: Pset_ActorCommon
Pset_ActorCommon.definition: A property set that enables further classification of actors, including the ability to give a number of actors to be designated as a population, the number being specified as a property to be dealt with as a single value rather than having to aggregate a number of instances of IfcActor.

properties.name: NumberOfActors
properties.definition: The number of actors that are to be dealt with together in the population.

properties.name: ActorCategory
properties.definition: Designation of the category into which the actors in the population belong.

properties.name: SkillLevel
properties.definition: Skill level exhibited by the actor and which indicates an extent of their capability to perform actions on the artefacts upon which they can act.

Pset_ActuatorPHistory.name: Pset_ActuatorPHistory
Pset_ActuatorPHistory.definition: Properties for history of actuators.HISTORY Added in IFC4.

properties.name: PositionHistory
properties.definition: Indicates position of the actuator over time where 0.0 is fully closed and 1.0 is fully open.

properties.name: QualityHistory
properties.definition: Indicates the quality of measurement or failure condition, which may be further qualified by the Status.  True: measured values are considered reliable; False: measured values are considered not reliable (i.e. a fault has been detected); Unknown: reliability of values is uncertain.

properties.name: StatusHistory
properties.definition: Indicates an error code or identifier, whose meaning is specific to the particular automation system.  Example values include: 'ConfigurationError', 'NotConnected', 'DeviceFailure', 'SensorFailure', 'LastKnown, 'CommunicationsFailure', 'OutOfService'.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: ActuatorStatus
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: FailPosition
properties.definition: Specifies the required fail-safe position of the actuator.

properties.name: ManualOverride
properties.definition: Identifies whether hand-operated operation is provided as an override (= TRUE) or not (= FALSE). Note that this value should be set to FALSE by default in the case of a Hand Operated Actuator.

properties.name: ActuatorApplication
properties.definition: Indicates application of actuator.

Pset_ActuatorTypeElectricActuator.name: Pset_ActuatorTypeElectricActuator
Pset_ActuatorTypeElectricActuator.definition: A device that electrically actuates a control element.

properties.name: ActuatorInputPower
properties.definition: Maximum input power requirement.

properties.name: ElectricActuatorType
properties.definition: Enumeration that identifies electric actuator as defined by its operational principle.

properties.name: ControlPulseCurrent
properties.definition: The current of the electric actuator control pulse.

Pset_ActuatorTypeHydraulicActuator.name: Pset_ActuatorTypeHydraulicActuator
Pset_ActuatorTypeHydraulicActuator.definition: A device that hydraulically actuates a control element.

properties.name: InputPressure
properties.definition:
Maximum input or design pressure for the object.

Maximum design pressure for the actuator.

properties.name: InputFlowrate
properties.definition:
Maximum input flowrate requirement.

Hydraulic flowrate.

Pset_ActuatorTypeLinearActuation.name: Pset_ActuatorTypeLinearActuation
Pset_ActuatorTypeLinearActuation.definition:
Characteristics of linear actuation of an actuator
History: Replaces Pset_LinearActuator

properties.name: Force
properties.definition: Indicates the maximum close-off force for the actuator.

properties.name: Stroke
properties.definition: Indicates the maximum distance the actuator must traverse.

Pset_ActuatorTypePneumaticActuator.name: Pset_ActuatorTypePneumaticActuator
Pset_ActuatorTypePneumaticActuator.definition: A device that pneumatically actuates a control element

properties.name: InputPressure
properties.definition:
Maximum input or design pressure for the object.

Control air pressure.

properties.name: InputFlowrate
properties.definition:
Maximum input flowrate requirement.

Control air flowrate.

Pset_ActuatorTypeRotationalActuation.name: Pset_ActuatorTypeRotationalActuation
Pset_ActuatorTypeRotationalActuation.definition:
Characteristics of rotational actuation of an actuator
History: Replaces Pset_RotationalActuator

properties.name: Torque
properties.definition: Indicates the maximum close-off torque for the actuator.

properties.name: RangeAngle
properties.definition: Indicates the maximum rotation the actuator must traverse.

Pset_Address.name: Pset_Address
Pset_Address.definition: This Property Set represents an address for delivery of paper based mail and other postal deliveries.

properties.name: Purpose
properties.definition: Indication of the purpose of this object

properties.name: Description
properties.definition: The Description of the object.

properties.name: UserDefinedPurpose
properties.definition: Allows for specification of user specific purpose of the address beyond the enumeration values provided by Purpose attribute of type IfcAddressTypeEnum. When a value is provided for attribute UserDefinedPurpose, in parallel the attribute Purpose shall have enumeration value USERDEFINED.

properties.name: InternalLocation
properties.definition: An organization defined address for internal mail delivery.

properties.name: AddressLines
properties.definition: The postal address.NOTE  A postal address may occupy several lines (or elements) when recorded. It is expected that normal usage will incorporate relevant elements of the following address concepts: A location within a building (e.g. 3rd Floor) Building name (e.g. Interoperability House) Street number (e.g. 6400) Street name (e.g. Alliance Boulevard). Typical content of address lines may vary in different countries.

properties.name: PostalBox
properties.definition: An address that is implied by an identifiable mail drop.

properties.name: Town
properties.definition: The name of a town.

properties.name: Region
properties.definition: The name of a region.EXAMPLE  The counties of the United Kingdom and the states of North America are examples of regions.

properties.name: PostalCode
properties.definition: The code that is used by the country's postal service.

properties.name: Country
properties.definition: The two letter country code (from ISO 3166).

properties.name: TelephoneNumbers
properties.definition: The list of telephone numbers at which telephone messages may be received.

properties.name: FacsimileNumbers
properties.definition: The list of fax numbers at which fax messages may be received.

properties.name: PagerNumber
properties.definition: The pager number at which paging messages may be received.

properties.name: ElectronicMailAddresses
properties.definition: The list of Email addresses at which Email messages may be received.

properties.name: WWWHomePageURL
properties.definition: The world wide web address at which the preliminary page of information for the person or organization can be located.NOTE  Information on the world wide web for a person or organization may be separated into a number of pages and across a number of host sites, all of which may be linked together. It is assumed that all such information may be referenced from a single page that is termed the home page for that person or organization.

properties.name: MessagingIDs
properties.definition: IDs or addresses for any other means of telecommunication, for example instant messaging, voice-over-IP, or file transfer protocols. The communication protocol is indicated by the URI value with scheme designations such as irc:, sip:, or ftp:.

Pset_AirSideSystemInformation.name: Pset_AirSideSystemInformation
Pset_AirSideSystemInformation.definition: Attributes that apply to an air side HVAC system.HISTORY New property set in IFC Release 1.0.

properties.name: Description
properties.definition: The Description of the object.

properties.name: AirSideSystemType
properties.definition: This enumeration specifies the basic types of possible air side systems (e.g., Constant Volume, Variable Volume, etc.).

properties.name: AirSideSystemDistributionType
properties.definition: This enumeration defines the basic types of air side systems (e.g., SingleDuct, DualDuct, Multizone, etc.).

properties.name: EnergyGainTotal
properties.definition: The total amount of energy gains for the spaces served by the system during the peak cooling conditions, plus any system-level total energy gains.

properties.name: EnergyGainSensible
properties.definition: The sum of total energy gains for the spaces served by the system during the peak cooling conditions, plus any system-level sensible energy gains.

properties.name: EnergyLoss
properties.definition: The sum of energy losses for the spaces served by the system during the peak heating conditions.

properties.name: InfiltrationDiversitySummer
properties.definition: Diversity factor for Summer infiltration.

properties.name: InfiltrationDiversityWinter
properties.definition: Diversity factor for Winter infiltration.

properties.name: ApplianceDiversity
properties.definition: Diversity of appliance load.

properties.name: HeatingTemperatureDelta
properties.definition: Heating temperature difference for calculating space air flow rates.

properties.name: CoolingTemperatureDelta
properties.definition: Cooling temperature difference for calculating space air flow rates.

properties.name: Ventilation
properties.definition: Required outside air ventilation.

properties.name: FanPower
properties.definition: Fan motor loads contributing to the cooling load.

Pset_AirTerminalBoxPHistory.name: Pset_AirTerminalBoxPHistory
Pset_AirTerminalBoxPHistory.definition: Air terminal box performance history attributes.

properties.name: DamperPosition
properties.definition: Control damper position, ranging from 0 to 1; damper position (0=closed=90deg position angle, 1=open=0deg position angle).

properties.name: AtmosphericPressure
properties.definition: Ambient atmospheric pressure.

properties.name: Sound
properties.definition: Sound performance.

Pset_AirTerminalBoxTypeCommon.name: Pset_AirTerminalBoxTypeCommon
Pset_AirTerminalBoxTypeCommon.definition: Air terminal box type common attributes.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: AirFlowRateRange
properties.definition: Possible range of airflow that can be delivered.

properties.name: AirPressureRange
properties.definition: Allowable air static pressure range at the entrance of the air terminal box.

properties.name: NominalAirFlowRate
properties.definition: Nominal air flow rate.

properties.name: ArrangementType
properties.definition:
Terminal box arrangement.
SingleDuct: Terminal box receives warm or cold air from a single air supply duct.
DualDuct: Terminal box receives warm and cold air from separate air supply ducts.

properties.name: ReheatType
properties.definition: Terminal box reheat type.

properties.name: HasSoundAttenuator
properties.definition: If TRUE, the object has sound attenuation.

properties.name: HasReturnAir
properties.definition: Terminal box has return air mixed with supply air from duct work.

properties.name: HasFan
properties.definition: Terminal box has a fan inside (fan powered box).

properties.name: NominalInletAirPressure
properties.definition: Nominal airflow inlet static pressure.

properties.name: NominalDamperDiameter
properties.definition: Nominal damper diameter.

properties.name: HousingThickness
properties.definition: Air terminal box housing material thickness.

properties.name: OperationTemperatureRange
properties.definition:
Allowable operation ambient air temperature range.

Allowable operational range of the ambient air temperature.

properties.name: ReturnAirFractionRange
properties.definition: Allowable return air fraction range as a fraction of discharge airflow.

Pset_AirTerminalOccurrence.name: Pset_AirTerminalOccurrence
Pset_AirTerminalOccurrence.definition: Air terminal occurrence attributes attached to an instance of IfcAirTerminal.

properties.name: AirFlowRate
properties.definition:
Air flow rate.

The actual airflow rate as designed.

properties.name: AirTerminalLocation
properties.definition: Location  (a single type of diffuser can be used for multiple locations); high means close to ceiling.

Pset_AirTerminalPHistory.name: Pset_AirTerminalPHistory
Pset_AirTerminalPHistory.definition: Air terminal performance history common attributes.

properties.name: AirFlowRateHistory
properties.definition: Volumetric flow rate.

properties.name: NeckAirVelocity
properties.definition: Air velocity at the neck.

properties.name: SupplyAirTemperatureHeating
properties.definition: Supply air temperature in heating mode.

properties.name: SupplyAirTemperatureCooling
properties.definition: Supply air temperature in cooling mode.

properties.name: PressureDrop
properties.definition:
Pressure drop.

Drop in total pressure between inlet and outlet at nominal air-flow rate.

properties.name: InductionRatio
properties.definition: Induction ratio versus distance from the diffuser and its discharge direction; induction ratio (or entrainment ratio) is the ratio of the volumetric flow rate in the jet to the volumetric flow rate at the air terminal.

properties.name: CenterlineAirVelocity
properties.definition: Centerline air velocity versus distance from the diffuser and temperature differential; a function of distance from diffuser and temperature difference between supply air and room air.

Pset_AirTerminalTypeCommon.name: Pset_AirTerminalTypeCommon
Pset_AirTerminalTypeCommon.definition:
Air terminal type common attributes.
SoundLevel attribute deleted in IFC2x2 Pset Addendum: Use IfcSoundProperties instead.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: AirTerminalShape
properties.definition: Shape of the air terminal. Slot is typically a long narrow supply device with an aspect ratio generally greater than 10 to 1.

properties.name: FaceType
properties.definition: Identifies how the terminal face of an AirTerminal is constructed.

properties.name: SlotWidth
properties.definition: Slot width.

properties.name: SlotLength
properties.definition: Slot length.

properties.name: NumberOfSlots
properties.definition: Indicates the number of  slots.

properties.name: FlowPattern
properties.definition: Flow pattern.

properties.name: AirFlowRateRange
properties.definition:
Possible range of airflow that can be delivered.

Air flowrate range within which the air terminal is designed to operate.

properties.name: TemperatureRange
properties.definition:
Allowable maximum and minimum temperature.

Temperature range within which the air terminal is designed to operate.

properties.name: DischargeDirection
properties.definition:
Discharge direction of the air terminal.Parallel: discharges parallel to mounting surface designed so that flow attaches to the surface.
Perpendicular:  discharges away from mounting surface.
Adjustable: both parallel and perpendicular discharge.

properties.name: ThrowLength
properties.definition: The horizontal or vertical axial distance an airstream travels after leaving an AirTerminal before the maximum stream velocity is reduced to a specified terminal velocity under isothermal conditions at the upper value of the AirFlowrateRange.

properties.name: AirDiffusionPerformanceIndex
properties.definition: The Air Diffusion Performance Index (ADPI) is used for cooling mode conditions. If several measurements of air velocity and air temperature are made throughout the occupied zone of a space, the ADPI is the percentage of locations where measurements were taken that meet the specifications for effective draft temperature and air velocity.

properties.name: FinishType
properties.definition: The type of finish for the air terminal.

properties.name: FinishColour
properties.definition: The finish colour of the object.

properties.name: AirTerminalMountingType
properties.definition:
The way the air terminal is mounted to the ceiling, wall, etc.Surface: mounted to the surface of something (e.g., wall, duct, etc.).
Flat flush: mounted flat and flush with a surface.
Lay-in: mounted in a lay-in type ceiling (e.g., a dropped ceiling grid).

properties.name: CoreType
properties.definition: Identifies the way the core of the AirTerminal is constructed.

properties.name: CoreSetHorizontal
properties.definition: Degree of horizontal (in the X-axis of the LocalPlacement) blade set from the centerline.

properties.name: CoreSetVertical
properties.definition: Degree of vertical (in the Y-axis of the LocalPlacement) blade set from the centerline.

properties.name: HasIntegralControl
properties.definition: If TRUE, a self powered temperature control is included in the AirTerminal.

properties.name: FlowControlType
properties.definition: Type of flow control element that may be included as a part of the construction of the air terminal.

properties.name: HasSoundAttenuator
properties.definition: If TRUE, the object has sound attenuation.

properties.name: HasThermalInsulation
properties.definition: If TRUE, the air terminal has thermal insulation.

properties.name: NeckArea
properties.definition: Neck area of the air terminal.

properties.name: EffectiveArea
properties.definition: Effective discharge area of the air terminal.

properties.name: AirFlowrateVersusFlowControlElement
properties.definition: Air flowrate versus flow control element position at nominal pressure drop.

Pset_AirToAirHeatRecoveryPHistory.name: Pset_AirToAirHeatRecoveryPHistory
Pset_AirToAirHeatRecoveryPHistory.definition: Air to Air Heat Recovery performance history common attributes.

properties.name: SensibleEffectiveness
properties.definition: Sensible heat transfer effectiveness, where effectiveness is defined as the ratio of heat transfer to maximum possible heat transfer.

properties.name: TotalEffectiveness
properties.definition: Total heat transfer effectiveness: The ratio of heat transfer to the maximum possible heat transfer.

properties.name: TemperatureEffectiveness
properties.definition: Temperature heat transfer effectiveness: The ratio of primary airflow temperature changes to maximum possible temperature changes.

properties.name: DefrostTemperatureEffectiveness
properties.definition: Temperature heat transfer effectiveness when defrosting is active.

properties.name: HumidityEffectiveness
properties.definition: Humidity heat transfer effectiveness: The ratio of primary airflow absolute humidity changes to maximum possible absolute humidity changes.

properties.name: SensibleHeatTransferRate
properties.definition: Sensible heat transfer rate.

properties.name: LatentHeatTransferRate
properties.definition: Latent heat transfer rate.

properties.name: TotalHeatTransferRate
properties.definition: Total heat transfer rate.

properties.name: SensibleEffectivenessTable
properties.definition: Sensible heat transfer effectiveness curve as a function of the primary and secondary air flow rate.

properties.name: TotalEffectivenessTable
properties.definition: Total heat transfer effectiveness curve as a function of the primary and secondary air flow rate.

properties.name: AirPressureDropCurves
properties.definition: Air pressure drop as function of air flow rate.

Pset_AirToAirHeatRecoveryTypeCommon.name: Pset_AirToAirHeatRecoveryTypeCommon
Pset_AirToAirHeatRecoveryTypeCommon.definition: Air to Air Heat Recovery type common attributes.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: HeatTransferTypeEnum
properties.definition: Type of heat transfer between the two air streams.

properties.name: HasDefrost
properties.definition: has the heat exchanger has defrost function or not.

properties.name: OperationalTemperatureRange
properties.definition:
The temperature range in which the device operates normally.

Allowable operation ambient air temperature range.

Pset_AlarmPHistory.name: Pset_AlarmPHistory
Pset_AlarmPHistory.definition: Properties for history of alarm values.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: Enabled
properties.definition: Indicates whether alarm is enabled or disabled over time.

properties.name: ConditionHistory
properties.definition: Indicates alarm condition over time.  The range of possible values and their meanings is defined by Pset_AlarmTypeCommon.Condition.  An empty value indicates no present alarm condition.

properties.name: Severity
properties.definition: Indicates alarm severity over time, where the scale of values is determined by the control system configuration.  A zero value indicates no present alarm.

properties.name: Acknowledge
properties.definition: Indicates acknowledgement status where False indicates acknowlegement is required and outstanding, True indicates condition has been acknowedged, and Unknown indicates no acknowledgement is required.  Upon resetting the condition, then acknowledgement reverts to Unknown.

properties.name: UserHistory
properties.definition: Indicates acknowledging user over time by identification corresponding to IfcPerson.Identification on an IfcActor.

Pset_AlarmTypeCommon.name: Pset_AlarmTypeCommon
Pset_AlarmTypeCommon.definition: Alarm type common attributes.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: AlarmCondition
properties.definition: Table mapping alarm condition identifiers to descriptive labels, which may be used for interpreting Pset_AlarmPHistory.Condition.

Pset_AlignmentCantSegmentCommon.name: Pset_AlignmentCantSegmentCommon
Pset_AlignmentCantSegmentCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all instances of alignment segment that have designParameters for cant.

properties.name: CantDeficiency
properties.definition: Difference between applied cant and a higher equilibrium cant.

properties.name: CantEquilibrium
properties.definition: Cant at a particular speed at which the vehicle will have a resultant force perpendicular to the running plane.

properties.name: StartSmoothingLength
properties.definition: Length for the circular transition change of curvature at the start of the cant segment, measured from the start of the cant segment to the end of the circular transition change of curvature.

properties.name: EndSmoothingLength
properties.definition: Length for the circular transition change of curvature at the end of the cant segment, measured from the start of the circular transition change of curvature to the end of the cant segment.

Pset_AlignmentVerticalSegmentCommon.name: Pset_AlignmentVerticalSegmentCommon
Pset_AlignmentVerticalSegmentCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all instances of alignment vertical segment.

properties.name: StartElevation
properties.definition: Elevation of the start point relative to the mean sea level.

properties.name: EndElevation
properties.definition: Elevation of the end point relative to the mean sea level.

Pset_AnnotationContourLine.name: Pset_AnnotationContourLine
Pset_AnnotationContourLine.definition: Specifies properties of a standard curve that has a single, consistent measure value.

properties.name: ContourValue
properties.definition: Value of the elevation of the contour above or below a reference plane.

Pset_AnnotationLineOfSight.name: Pset_AnnotationLineOfSight
Pset_AnnotationLineOfSight.definition: Specifies the properties of the line of sight. For example, it can be used to define the line of sight visibility at the junction between two roads (particularly between an access road and a public road); or in the design of a stadium or theatre.

properties.name: SetbackDistance
properties.definition: Setback distance from the point of connection on the major element along the axis of the minor element (e.g. distance from a public road at which the line of sigfht is measured.

properties.name: VisibleAngleLeft
properties.definition: Angle of visibility to the left of the access.

properties.name: VisibleAngleRight
properties.definition: Angle of visibility to the right of the access.

properties.name: RoadVisibleDistanceLeft
properties.definition: Distance visible to the left of the access.

properties.name: RoadVisibleDistanceRight
properties.definition: Distance visible to the right of the access.

Pset_AnnotationSurveyArea.name: Pset_AnnotationSurveyArea
Pset_AnnotationSurveyArea.definition: Specifies particular properties of survey methods to be assigned to survey point set or resulting surface patches

properties.name: AcquisitionMethod
properties.definition: The means by which survey data was acquired.

properties.name: AccuracyQualityObtained
properties.definition: A measure of the accuracy quality of survey points as obtained expressed in percentage terms.

properties.name: AccuracyQualityExpected
properties.definition: A measure of the accuracy quality of survey points as expected expressed in percentage terms.

Pset_Asset.name: Pset_Asset
Pset_Asset.definition: An asset is a uniquely identifiable element which has a financial value and against which maintenance actions are recorded.

properties.name: AssetAccountingType
properties.definition: Identifies the predefined types of risk from which the type required may be set.

properties.name: AssetTaxType
properties.definition: Identifies the predefined types of taxation group from which the type required may be set.

properties.name: AssetInsuranceType
properties.definition: Identifies the predefined types of insurance rating from which the type required may be set.

properties.name: AssetStatus
properties.definition: Current status or stage in life cycle.

properties.name: AssetUse
properties.definition: General use category of the asset

Pset_AudioVisualAppliancePHistory.name: Pset_AudioVisualAppliancePHistory
Pset_AudioVisualAppliancePHistory.definition: Captures realtime information for audio-video devices, such as for security camera footage and retail information displays.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: PowerState
properties.definition: Indicates the power state of the device where True is on and False is off.

properties.name: MediaSourceHistory
properties.definition: Indicates the media source where the identifier corresponds to an entry within the table of available media sources on Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeCommon.MediaSource.

properties.name: MediaContent
properties.definition: Indicates the media content storage location, such as URLs to camera footage within particular time periods.

properties.name: AudioVolumeHistory
properties.definition: Indicates the audio volume level where the integer level corresponds to an entry or interpolation within Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeCommon.AudioVolume.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeAmplifier.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeAmplifier
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeAmplifier.definition: An audio-visual amplifier is a device that renders audio from a single external source connected from a port.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: AmplifierType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of amplifier.

properties.name: AudioAmplification
properties.definition: Indicates audio amplification frequency ranges.

properties.name: AudioMode
properties.definition: Indicates audio sound modes and corresponding labels, if applicable.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeCamera.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeCamera
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeCamera.definition: An audio-visual camera is a device that captures video, such as for security.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: CameraType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of camera.

properties.name: IsOutdoors
properties.definition: Indicates if camera is designed to be used outdoors.

properties.name: VideoResolutionWidth
properties.definition: Indicates the number of horizontal pixels (the largest native video resolution width).

properties.name: VideoResolutionHeight
properties.definition: Indicates the number of vertical pixels (the largest native video resolution height).

properties.name: VideoResolutionMode
properties.definition: Indicates video resolution modes.

properties.name: VideoCaptureInterval
properties.definition: Indicates video frame capture time intervals.

properties.name: PanTiltZoomPreset
properties.definition: Indicates pan/tilt/zoom position presets.

properties.name: PanHorizontal
properties.definition: Indicates horizontal range for panning.

properties.name: PanVertical
properties.definition: Indicates vertical range for panning.

properties.name: TiltHorizontal
properties.definition: Indicates horizontal range for pivoting, where positive values indicate the camera rotating clockwise,

properties.name: TiltVertical
properties.definition: Indicates vertical range for pivoting, where 0.0 is level, +90 degrees is looking up, -90 degrees is looking down.

properties.name: Zoom
properties.definition: Indicates the zoom range.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeCommon.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeCommon
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeCommon.definition: An audio-visual appliance is a device that renders or captures audio and/or video.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: MediaSource
properties.definition: Indicates media sources and corresponding names of ports (IfcDistributionPort with FlowDirection=SINK and PredefinedType=AUDIOVISUAL) or aggregated audio/video components (IfcAudioVisualAppliance).

properties.name: AudioVolume
properties.definition: Indicates discrete audio volume levels and corresponding sound power offsets, if applicable.  Missing values may be interpolated.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeDisplay.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeDisplay
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeDisplay.definition: An audio-visual display is a device that renders video from a screen.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: DisplayType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of display.

properties.name: NominalSize
properties.definition: Indicates the diagonal screen size.

properties.name: DisplayWidth
properties.definition: Indicates the physical width of the screen (only the display surface).

properties.name: DisplayHeight
properties.definition: Indicates the physical height of the screen (only the display surface).

properties.name: Brightness
properties.definition: Indicates the display brightness.

properties.name: ContrastRatio
properties.definition: Indicates the display contrast ratio.

properties.name: RefreshRate
properties.definition: Indicates the display refresh frequency.

properties.name: TouchScreen
properties.definition: Indicates touchscreen support.

properties.name: VideoResolutionWidth
properties.definition: Indicates the number of horizontal pixels (the largest native video resolution width).

properties.name: VideoResolutionHeight
properties.definition: Indicates the number of vertical pixels (the largest native video resolution height).

properties.name: VideoResolutionMode
properties.definition: Indicates video resolution modes.

properties.name: VideoScaleMode
properties.definition: Indicates video scaling modes.

properties.name: VideoCaptionMode
properties.definition: Indicates video closed captioning modes.

properties.name: AudioMode
properties.definition: Indicates audio sound modes and corresponding labels, if applicable.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypePlayer.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypePlayer
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypePlayer.definition: An audio-visual player is a device that plays stored media into a stream of audio and/or video, such as camera footage in security systems, background audio in retail areas, or media presentations in conference rooms or theatres.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: PlayerType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of player.

properties.name: PlayerMediaEject
properties.definition: Indicates whether the media can be ejected from the player (if physical media).

properties.name: PlayerMediaFormat
properties.definition: Indicates supported media formats.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeProjector.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeProjector
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeProjector.definition: An audio-visual projector is a device that projects video to a surface.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: ProjectorType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of projector.

properties.name: VideoResolutionWidth
properties.definition: Indicates the number of horizontal pixels (the largest native video resolution width).

properties.name: VideoResolutionHeight
properties.definition: Indicates the number of vertical pixels (the largest native video resolution height).

properties.name: VideoResolutionMode
properties.definition: Indicates video resolution modes.

properties.name: VideoScaleMode
properties.definition: Indicates video scaling modes.

properties.name: VideoCaptionMode
properties.definition: Indicates video closed captioning modes.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeRailwayComm.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeRailwayCommunicationTerminal
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeRailwayComm.definition: Properties used for railway communication terminals.

properties.name: RailwayCommunicationTerminalType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of railway communication terminal.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeReceiver.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeReceiver
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeReceiver.definition: An audio-visual receiver is a device that switches audio and/or video from multiple sources, including external sources connected from ports and internal aggregated sources.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: ReceiverType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of receiver.

properties.name: AudioAmplification
properties.definition: Indicates audio amplification frequency ranges.

properties.name: AudioMode
properties.definition: Indicates audio sound modes and corresponding labels, if applicable.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeRecordingEq.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeRecordingEquipment
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeRecordingEq.definition: Properties common to IfcAudioVisualAppliance with predefined type set to RECORDINGEQUIPMENT.

properties.name: NumberOfInterfaces
properties.definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

properties.name: StorageCapacity
properties.definition: Indicates the total data storage capacity of the device. It is defined by bytes.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeSpeaker.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeSpeaker
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeSpeaker.definition: An audio-visual speaker is a device that converts amplified audio signals into sound waves.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: SpeakerType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of speaker.

properties.name: SpeakerMounting
properties.definition: Indicates how the speaker is designed to be mounted.

properties.name: SpeakerDriverSize
properties.definition: Indicates the number of drivers and their sizes.

properties.name: FrequencyResponse
properties.definition: Indicates the output over a specified range of frequencies.

properties.name: Impedence
properties.definition: Indicates the speaker impedence.

Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeTuner.name: Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeTuner
Pset_AudioVisualApplianceTypeTuner.definition: An audio-visual tuner is a device that demodulates a signal into a stream of audio and/or video.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: TunerType
properties.definition: Indicates the tuner type.

properties.name: TunerMode
properties.definition: Indicates the tuner modes (or bands).  For example, 'AnalogCable', 'DigitalAir', 'AM', 'FM'.

properties.name: TunerChannel
properties.definition: Indicates the tuner channels, if applicable.

properties.name: TunerFrequency
properties.definition: Indicates the tuner frequencies, if applicable.

Pset_AxleCountingEquipment.name: Pset_AxleCountingEquipment
Pset_AxleCountingEquipment.definition: Properties that are applicable for IfcSensor with predefined type WHEELSENSOR, indicated that the wheel sensor is a axle counting equipment.

properties.name: FailureInformation
properties.definition: The information for failure description.

properties.name: DetectionRange
properties.definition: The detection range of the equipment.

properties.name: OperationalTemperatureRange
properties.definition: The temperature range in which the device operates normally.

properties.name: NominalWeight
properties.definition: Nominal weight of the object.

properties.name: AxleCountingEquipmentType
properties.definition: The type of axle counting equipment.

properties.name: ImpactParameter
properties.definition: Impact parameter of the equipment.

properties.name: RatedVoltage
properties.definition: The range of allowed voltage that a device is certified to handle. The upper bound of this value is the maximum.

properties.name: InsulationResistance
properties.definition: Minimum resistance between one terminal or several terminals connected together and the case or enclosure of a component at specified voltage.

properties.name: AxleCounterResponseTime
properties.definition: The time that axle counter can detect the axles of locomotive and vehicle.

properties.name: MaximumVibration
properties.definition: Maximum tolerable vibration level of the device.

Pset_BalanceWeightTensionerDesignCriteri.name: Pset_BalanceWeightTensionerDesignCriteria
Pset_BalanceWeightTensionerDesignCriteri.definition: Properties of a weight tensioner. The property set can be used by the predefined type TENSIONINGEQUIPMENT of IfcDiscreteAccessory.

properties.name: ReferenceDistanceRopeToPulley
properties.definition: The reference design criteria for distance from the end of the rope to the fixed pulley.It defines the nominal distance in relation to temperature.

properties.name: ReferenceDistanceTensionerToGround
properties.definition: The reference design criteria distance from the last tensioner to the ground or the base surface (B value). It defines the nominal distance in relation to temperature.

Pset_BeamCommon.name: Pset_BeamCommon
Pset_BeamCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrence and type objects of beam.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: Span
properties.definition: Clear span for this object.The shape information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the shape properties, provided in the attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence. For geometry editing applications, like CAD: this value should be write-only.

properties.name: Slope
properties.definition: Slope angle - relative to horizontal (0.0 degrees).The shape information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the shape properties, provided in the attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence.  For geometry editing applications, like CAD: this value should be write-only.

properties.name: Roll
properties.definition:
Rotation against the longitudinal axis.

Relative to the global Z direction for all beams that are non-vertical in regard to the global coordinate system (Profile direction equals global Z is Roll = 0.)The shape information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the shape properties, provided in the attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence.  For geometry editing applications, like CAD: this value should be write-only.Note: new property in IFC4

properties.name: IsExternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

properties.name: ThermalTransmittance
properties.definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of an element, within the direction of the thermal flow (including all materials).

properties.name: LoadBearing
properties.definition: Indicates whether the object is intended to carry loads (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: FireRating
properties.definition: Fire rating for this object. It is given according to the national fire safety classification.

properties.name: DisplacementAccommodated
properties.definition: A list of exactly three boolean values representing an accommodated displacement (value TRUE or 1) or no displacement (value FALSE or 0) on the corresponding axis where the first value represents axis X, second value axis Y and third value axis Z.

properties.name: RotationAccommodated
properties.definition: A list of exactly three boolean values representing an accommodated rotation (value TRUE or 1) or no rotation (value FALSE or 0) about the corresponding axis where the first value represents axis X, second value axis Y and third value axis Z.

Pset_BerthCommon.name: Pset_BerthCommon
Pset_BerthCommon.definition: properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcSpace and types of IfcSpaceType with the predefined type set to BERTH

properties.name: BerthApproach
properties.definition: How the vessel approaches the berth

properties.name: BerthMode
properties.definition: Orientation of vessel as it approaches berth

properties.name: BerthingAngle
properties.definition: Angle of approach for the vessel to the berth

properties.name: BerthingVelocity
properties.definition: Velocity of the vessel as it berths

properties.name: AbnormalBerthingFactor
properties.definition: Risk assessed safety factor

Pset_BoilerPHistory.name: Pset_BoilerPHistory
Pset_BoilerPHistory.definition:
Boiler performance history common attributes.
WaterQuality attribute deleted in IFC2x2 Pset Addendum: Use IfcMaterialProperties instead. CombustionProductsMaximulLoad and CombustionProductsPartialLoad attributes deleted in IFC2x2 Pset Addendum: Use IfcMaterialProperties instead.

properties.name: EnergySourceConsumption
properties.definition: Energy consumption.

properties.name: OperationalEfficiency
properties.definition: Operational efficiency: boiler output divided by total energy input (electrical and fuel).

properties.name: CombustionEfficiency
properties.definition: Combustion efficiency under nominal condition.

properties.name: WorkingPressureHistory
properties.definition: Boiler working pressure.

properties.name: CombustionChamberTemperature
properties.definition: Average combustion chamber temperature.

properties.name: PartLoadRatio
properties.definition: Ratio of the real to the nominal capacity.

properties.name: Load
properties.definition: Boiler real load.

properties.name: PrimaryEnergyConsumption
properties.definition: Boiler primary energy source consumption (i.e., the fuel consumed for changing the thermodynamic state of the fluid).

properties.name: AuxiliaryEnergyConsumption
properties.definition: Boiler secondary energy source consumption (i.e., the electricity consumed by electrical devices such as fans and pumps).

Pset_BoilerTypeCommon.name: Pset_BoilerTypeCommon
Pset_BoilerTypeCommon.definition:
Boiler type common attributes.
SoundLevel attribute deleted in IFC2x2 Pset Addendum: Use IfcSoundProperties instead. PrimaryEnergySource and AuxiliaryEnergySource attributes deleted in IFC2x2 Pset Addendum: Use IfcMaterialProperties instead.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: PressureRating
properties.definition:
Pressure rating of the object.

Nominal pressure rating of the boiler as rated by the agency having jurisdiction.

properties.name: OperatingMode
properties.definition: Identifies the operating mode of the boiler.

properties.name: HeatTransferSurfaceArea
properties.definition: Total heat transfer area of the vessel.

properties.name: NominalPartLoadRatio
properties.definition: Allowable part load ratio range.

properties.name: WaterInletTemperatureRange
properties.definition: Allowable water inlet temperature range.

properties.name: WaterStorageCapacity
properties.definition: Water storage capacity.

properties.name: IsWaterStorageHeater
properties.definition: This is used to identify if the boiler has storage capacity (TRUE). If FALSE, then there is no storage capacity built into the boiler, such as an instantaneous hot water heater.

properties.name: PartialLoadEfficiencyCurves
properties.definition: Boiler efficiency as a function of the partial load factor; E = f (partialLaodfactor).

properties.name: OutletTemperatureRange
properties.definition: Allowable outlet temperature of either the water or the steam.

properties.name: NominalEnergyConsumption
properties.definition: Nominal fuel consumption rate required to produce the total boiler heat output.

properties.name: EnergySource
properties.definition: Enumeration defining the energy source or fuel cumbusted.

properties.name: MaximumOutletPressure
properties.definition: Maximum steam outlet pressure.

properties.name: NominalEfficiencyTable
properties.definition: The nominal efficiency of the boiler as defined by the manufacturer. For steam boilers, a function of inlet temperature versus steam pressure.  Note: as two variables are used, DefiningValues and DefinedValues are null, and values are stored in IfcTable in the following order: InletTemperature(IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure) and OutletTemperature(IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure) in DefiningValues, and NominalEfficiency(IfcNormalisedRatioMeasure) in DefinedValues. For example, DefininfValues(InletTemp, OutletTemp), DefinedValues(null, NominalEfficiency).  The IfcTable is related to IfcPropertyTableValue using IfcMetric and IfcResourceConstraintRelationship.

properties.name: HeatOutput
properties.definition:
Total nominal heat output as listed by the Boiler manufacturer.

For steam boilers, it is a function of inlet temperature versus steam pressure.  Note: as two variables are used, DefiningValues and DefinedValues are null, and values are stored in IfcTable in the following order: InletTemperature(IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure) and OutletTemperature(IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure) in DefiningValues, and HeatOutput(IfcEnergyMeasure) in DefinedValues. For example, DefiningValues(InletTemp, OutletTemp), DefinedValues(null, HeatOutput). The IfcTable is related to IfcPropertyTableValue using IfcMetric and IfcResourceConstraintRelationship.

properties.name: NominalEfficiency
properties.definition:
Nominal object efficiency under nominal conditions.

The nominal efficiency of the boiler as defined by the manufacturer. For water boilers, a function of inlet versus outlet temperature. Note: as two variables are used, DefiningValues and DefinedValues are null, and values are stored in IfcTable in the following order: InletTemperature(IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure), OutletTemperature(IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure), NominalEfficiency(IfcNormalisedRatioMeasure).  The IfcTable is related to IfcPropertyTableValue using IfcMetric and IfcResourceConstraintRelationship.

properties.name: HeatOutput
properties.definition:
Total nominal heat output as listed by the Boiler manufacturer.

For water boilers, it is a function of inlet versus outlet temperature. For steam boilers, it is a function of inlet temperature versus steam pressure.  Note: as two variables are used, DefiningValues and DefinedValues are null, and values are stored in IfcTable in the following order: InletTemperature(IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure), OutletTemperature(IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure), HeatOutput(IfcEnergyMeasure).  The IfcTable is related to IfcPropertyTableValue using IfcMetric and IfcResourceConstraintRelationship.

Pset_BoreholeCommon.name: Pset_BoreholeCommon
Pset_BoreholeCommon.definition: Properties describing the features of a borehole (if not modelled separately).

properties.name: BoreholeState
properties.definition: The state the borehole or trial pit has been left in. (boreholeML).

properties.name: CapDepth
properties.definition: Depth of cap (boreholeML).

properties.name: CapMaterial
properties.definition: Cap material or 'NOT CAPPED' or 'UNKNOWN' (boreholeML).

properties.name: FillingDepth
properties.definition: Depth of filling (boreholeML).

properties.name: FillingMaterial
properties.definition: Filling material or 'NOT FILLED' or 'UNKNOWN' (boreholeML).

properties.name: GroundwaterDepth
properties.definition: Depth groundwater encountered (boreholeML).

properties.name: LiningMaterial
properties.definition: Lining material or 'NOT LINED' or 'UNKNOWN' (boreholeML).

properties.name: LiningThickness
properties.definition: Thickness of the lining.

properties.name: SpreadingRate
properties.definition: The nominal overall mass of material per area covered by the course.

Pset_BreakwaterCommon.name: Pset_BreakwaterCommon
Pset_BreakwaterCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcMarineFacility with the predefined type set to BREAKWATER.

properties.name: StructuralStyle
properties.definition: Structural style of the element

properties.name: Elevation
properties.definition: Elevation of the entity

properties.name: StructureIndicator
properties.definition: The type of bridge structure (composite, coated, homogeneous or other)

Pset_BuildingCommon.name: Pset_BuildingCommon
Pset_BuildingCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all instances of IfcBuilding. Please note that several building attributes are handled directly at the IfcBuilding instance, the building number (or short name) by IfcBuilding.Name, the building name (or long name) by IfcBuilding.LongName, and the description (or comments) by IfcBuilding.Description. Actual building quantities, like building perimeter, building area and building volume are provided by IfcElementQuantity, and the building classification according to national building code by IfcClassificationReference.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: BuildingID
properties.definition: A unique identifier assigned to a building. A temporary identifier is initially assigned at the time of making a planning application. This temporary identifier is changed to a permanent identifier when the building is registered into a statutory buildings and properties database.

properties.name: IsPermanentID
properties.definition: Indicates whether the identity assigned to the object is permanent (= TRUE) or temporary (=FALSE).

properties.name: ConstructionMethod
properties.definition: The type of construction action to the object, e.g. new construction, renovation, refurbishment, etc.

properties.name: FireProtectionClass
properties.definition: Main fire protection class for the building which is assigned from the fire protection classification table as given by the relevant national building code.

properties.name: SprinklerProtection
properties.definition: Indication whether this object is sprinkler protected (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: SprinklerProtectionAutomatic
properties.definition:
Indication whether this object has an automatic sprinkler protection (TRUE) or not (FALSE).
It should only be given, if the property "SprinklerProtection" is set to TRUE.

properties.name: OccupancyType
properties.definition:
Occupancy type for this object.
It is defined according to the presiding national building code.

properties.name: GrossPlannedArea
properties.definition: Total planned gross area of the spatial structure element. Used for programming the spatial structure element.

properties.name: NetPlannedArea
properties.definition: Total planned net area of the object. Used for programming the object.

properties.name: NumberOfStoreys
properties.definition:
The number of storeys within a building.
Captured for those cases where the IfcBuildingStorey entity is not used. Note that if IfcBuildingStorey is asserted and the number of storeys in a building can be determined from it, then this approach should be used in preference to setting a property for the number of storeys.

properties.name: YearOfConstruction
properties.definition: Year of construction of this building, including expected year of completion.

properties.name: YearOfLastRefurbishment
properties.definition: Year of last major refurbishment, or reconstruction, of the building (applies to reconstruction works).

properties.name: IsLandmarked
properties.definition: This builing is listed as a historic building (TRUE), or not (FALSE), or unknown.

properties.name: ElevationOfRefHeight
properties.definition: Elevation above sea level of the reference height used for all storey elevation measures, equals to height 0.0. It is usually the ground floor level.

properties.name: ElevationOfTerrain
properties.definition: Elevation above the minimal terrain level around the foot print of the building, given in elevation above sea level.

Pset_BuildingElementProxyCommon.name: Pset_BuildingElementProxyCommon
Pset_BuildingElementProxyCommon.definition: Common properties for built elements that don't have a specific entity name.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: IsExternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

properties.name: ThermalTransmittance
properties.definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of an element, within the direction of the thermal flow (including all materials).

properties.name: LoadBearing
properties.definition: Indicates whether the object is intended to carry loads (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: FireRating
properties.definition: Fire rating for this object. It is given according to the national fire safety classification.

Pset_BuildingStoreyCommon.name: Pset_BuildingStoreyCommon
Pset_BuildingStoreyCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all instances of IfcBuildingStorey. Please note that several building attributes are handled directly at the IfcBuildingStorey instance, the building storey number (or short name) by IfcBuildingStorey.Name, the building storey name (or long name) by IfcBuildingStorey.LongName, and the description (or comments) by IfcBuildingStorey.Description. Actual building storey quantities, like building storey perimeter, building storey area and building storey volume are provided by IfcElementQuantity, and the building storey classification according to national building code by IfcClassificationReference.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: EntranceLevel
properties.definition: Indication whether this building storey is an entrance level to the building (TRUE), or (FALSE) if otherwise.

properties.name: AboveGround
properties.definition: Indication whether this building storey is fully above ground (TRUE), or below ground (FALSE), or partially above and below ground (UNKNOWN) - as in sloped terrain.

properties.name: SprinklerProtection
properties.definition: Indication whether this object is sprinkler protected (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: SprinklerProtectionAutomatic
properties.definition:
Indication whether this object has an automatic sprinkler protection (TRUE) or not (FALSE).
It should only be given, if the property "SprinklerProtection" is set to TRUE.

properties.name: LoadBearingCapacity
properties.definition: Maximum load bearing capacity of the floor structure throughtout the storey as designed.

properties.name: GrossPlannedArea
properties.definition: Total planned gross area of the spatial structure element. Used for programming the spatial structure element.

properties.name: NetPlannedArea
properties.definition: Total planned net area of the object. Used for programming the object.

properties.name: ElevationOfSSLRelative
properties.definition: Elevation of the top surface of the structural slab level given in elevation above the local zero height. If the level varies and there is no significantly more prominent elevation, then this property may be omitted. In case of any inconsistency with the geometric positioning of the top surface, the geometric representation takes precedence.

properties.name: ElevationOfFFLRelative
properties.definition: Elevation of the top surface of the finished floor level given in elevation above the local zero height. If the level varies and there is no significantly more prominent elevation, then this property may be omitted. In case of any inconsistency with the geometric positioning of the top surface, the geometric representation takes precedence.

Pset_BuildingSystemCommon.name: Pset_BuildingSystemCommon
Pset_BuildingSystemCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of building systems.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

Pset_BuildingUse.name: Pset_BuildingUse
Pset_BuildingUse.definition: Provides information on on the real estate context of the building of interest both current and anticipated.

properties.name: MarketCategory
properties.definition: Category of use e.g. residential, commercial, recreation etc.

properties.name: MarketSubCategory
properties.definition: Subset of category of use e.g. multi-family, 2 bedroom, low rise.

properties.name: PlanningControlStatus
properties.definition: Label of zoning category or class, or planning control category for the site or facility.

properties.name: NarrativeText
properties.definition: Added information relating to the adjacent building use that is not appropriate to the general descriptive text associated with an entity through the inherited IfcRoot.Description.

properties.name: VacancyRateInCategoryNow
properties.definition: Percentage of vacancy found in the particular category currently.

properties.name: TenureModesAvailableNow
properties.definition: A list of the tenure modes that are currently available expressed in terms of IfcLabel.

properties.name: MarketSubCategoriesAvailableNow
properties.definition: A list of the sub categories of property that are currently available expressed in terms of IfcLabel.

properties.name: RentalRatesInCategoryNow
properties.definition: Range of the cost rates for property currently available in the required category.

properties.name: VacancyRateInCategoryFuture
properties.definition: Percentage of vacancy found in the particular category expected in the future.

properties.name: TenureModesAvailableFuture
properties.definition: A list of the tenure modes that are expected to be available in the future expressed in terms of IfcLabel.

properties.name: MarketSubCategoriesAvailableFuture
properties.definition: A list of the sub categories of property that are expected to be available in the future expressed in terms of IfcLabel.

properties.name: RentalRatesInCategoryFuture
properties.definition: Range of the cost rates for property expected to be available in the future in the required category.

Pset_BuildingUseAdjacent.name: Pset_BuildingUseAdjacent
Pset_BuildingUseAdjacent.definition: Provides information on adjacent buildings and their uses to enable their impact on the building of interest to be determined. Note that for each instance of the property set used, where there is an existence of risk, there will be an instance of the property set Pset_Risk (q.v).

properties.name: MarketCategory
properties.definition: Category of use e.g. residential, commercial, recreation etc.

properties.name: MarketSubCategory
properties.definition: Subset of category of use e.g. multi-family, 2 bedroom, low rise.

properties.name: PlanningControlStatus

Pset_CableSegmentTypeCableSegment.name: Pset_CableSegmentTypeCableSegment
Pset_CableSegmentTypeCableSegment.definition: Electrical cable with a specific purpose to lead electric current within a circuit or any other electric construction. Includes all types of electric cables, mainly several electrical segments wrapped together, e.g. cable, tube, busbar. Note that the number of conductors within a cable is determined by an aggregation mechanism that aggregates the conductors within the cable. A single-core cable is defined in IEV 461-06-02 as being 'a cable having only one core'; a multiconductor cable is defined in IEV 461-06-03 as b eing 'a cable having more than one conductor, some of which may be uninsulated'; a mulicore cable is defined in IEV 461-06-04 as being 'a cable having more than one core'.

Pset_CableSegmentTypeFiberTubeSegment.name: Pset_CableSegmentTypeFiberTubeSegment

properties.name: FiberTubeColour

properties.name: NumberOfFibers

Pset_CableSegmentTypeOpticalCableSegment.definition: Properties of optical cables segments. This property set is applicable to a type or occurrence of IfcCableSegment with predefined type OPTICALCABLESEGMENT.

properties.name: NumberOfFibers

properties.name: NumberOfSingleModeFibers
properties.definition: Total number of single-mode fibers in the optical fiber cable.

properties.name: NumberOfTubes

properties.name: FiberMode

Pset_CableSegmentTypeStitchWire.name: Pset_CableSegmentTypeStitchWire
Pset_CableSegmentTypeStitchWire.definition: Properties of stitch wires. This property set is applicable to a type or occurrence of IfcCableSegment with predefined type STICHWIRE.

properties.name: AssemblyInstruction

properties.name: NominalLength
properties.definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: MechanicalTension
properties.definition: Nominal value of mechanical force applied to a flow segment.

properties.name: UltimateTensileStrength
properties.definition: Indicates the maximum stress that a material or element can withstand before breaking while being stretched or pulled.

properties.name: TensileStrength
properties.definition: Indicates the ability to withstand breakage apart under applied force.

Pset_CableSegmentTypeWirePairSegment.name: Pset_CableSegmentTypeWirePairSegment
Pset_CableSegmentTypeWirePairSegment.definition: Properties of wire pair segments. This property set is applicable to a type or occurrence of IfcCableSegment with predefined type WIREPAIRSEGMENT.

properties.name: CharacteristicImpedance
properties.definition:
A quantity defined for a mode of propagation at a given frequency in a specific uniform transmission line or uniform waveguide by one of the three following relations:
Z1 = S/ |I|2
Z2 = |U|2 / S
Z3 = U / I
where Z is the complex characteristic impedance, S the complex power and U and I are the values, usually complex, respectively of a voltage and a current conventionally defined for each type of mode by analogy with transmission line equations.

properties.name: ConductorDiameter
properties.definition: Indicates the conductor diameter. It is only used for twisted and untwisted wire pair.

properties.name: CoreConductorDiameter
properties.definition: Indicates the core conductor diameter. It is only used for coaxial wire pair.

properties.name: JacketColour
properties.definition: Indicates the colour of the cable or fitting jacket.

properties.name: ShieldConductorDiameter
properties.definition: Indicates the shielded conductor diameter. It is only used for coaxial wire pair.

properties.name: WirePairType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of wire pair, i.e., twisted, untwisted or coaxial pair.

Pset_CargoCommon.name: Pset_CargoCommon
Pset_CargoCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcTransportElement and types of IfcTransportElementType with the predefined type set to CARGO.

properties.name: ProcessItem
properties.definition: The type of item (and its measurement method) being modelled within a process. This can be cargo, passengers or vehicles that pass through the system.

properties.name: AdditionalProcessing
properties.definition: Any additional or special processing requirements on the associated cargo.

properties.name: ProcessDirection
properties.definition: The direction of flow of the cargo within the process.

Pset_CessBetweenRails.name: Pset_CessBetweenRails
Pset_CessBetweenRails.definition: Properties in this property set are applicable for IfcSlab with PredefinedType TRACKSLAB, indicated that the slab is a cess or covering between rails.

properties.name: JointRelativePosition
properties.definition: Indicates the relative position of the joint, which lies in the left or right rail or in the middle, or in combination. The left rail is to the left as facing in the direction of increasing stationing values, and the right rail is to the right.

properties.name: CheckRailType
properties.definition: Type of the check rail. Check rail types enumerated in this property are defined based on EN 13674.

properties.name: LoadCapacity
properties.definition: Indicates the highest permissible load capacity.

properties.name: UsagePurpose
properties.definition: The purpose of usage of the cess between rails, e.g. maintenance, rescue services.

properties.name: Capacity
properties.definition:
The capacity of the element.

The product of the ideal capacity and the overall volumetric efficiency of the compressor.

properties.name: EnergyEfficiencyRatio
properties.definition:
Energy efficiency ratio (EER).

Ratio of net cooling capacity to the total input rate of electric power applied.  By definition, the units are BTU/hour per Watt.
The input electric power may be obtained from Pset_DistributionPortPHistoryElectrical.RealPower on the 'Power' port of the IfcChiller.

properties.name: CoefficientOfPerformance
properties.definition:
The Coefficient of performance (COP) is the ratio of heat removed to energy input.
The energy input may be obtained by multiplying
Pset_DistributionPortPHistoryGas.FlowRate on the 'Fuel' port of the IfcChiller by Pset_MaterialFuel.LowerHeatingValue.
The IfcDistributionPort for fuel has an associated IfcMaterial with fuel properties and is assigned to an IfcPerformanceHistory object nested within this IfcPerformanceHistory object.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: ChillerCapacity
properties.definition: Nominal cooling capacity of chiller at standardized conditions as defined by the agency having jurisdiction.

properties.name: NominalEfficiency
properties.definition: Nominal object efficiency under nominal conditions.

properties.name: NominalCondensingTemperature
properties.definition: Chiller condensing temperature.

properties.name: NominalEvaporatingTemperature
properties.definition: Chiller evaporating temperature.

properties.name: NominalHeatRejectionRate
properties.definition: Sum of the refrigeration effect and the heat equivalent of the power input to the compressor.

properties.name: NominalPowerConsumption
properties.definition: Nominal total power consumption.

properties.name: CapacityCurve
properties.definition:
Chiller cooling capacity is a function of condensing temperature and evaporating temperature, data is in table form, Capacity = f (TempCon, TempEvp), capacity = a1+b1*Tei+c1*Tei\^2+d1*Tci+e1*Tci\^2+f1*Tei*Tci.
This table uses multiple input variables; to represent, both DefiningValues and DefinedValues lists are null and IfcTable is attached using IfcResourceConstraintRelationship and IfcMetric.  Columns are specified in the following order:
1.IfcPowerMeasure:Capacity
2.IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure:CondensingTemperature
3.IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure:EvaporatingTemperature

properties.name: CoefficientOfPerformanceCurve
properties.definition:
Chiller coefficient of performance (COP) is function of condensing temperature and evaporating temperature, data is in table form, COP= f (TempCon, TempEvp), COP = a2+b2*Tei+c2*Tei\^2+d2*Tci+e2*Tci\^2+f2*Tei*Tci.
This table uses multiple input variables; to represent, both DefiningValues and DefinedValues lists are null and IfcTable is attached using IfcResourceConstraintRelationship and IfcMetric.  Columns are specified in the following order:
1.IfcPositiveRatioMeasure:CoefficientOfPerformance
2.IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure:CondensingTemperature
3.IfcThermodynamicTemperatureMeasure:EvaporatingTemperature

properties.name: FullLoadRatioCurve
properties.definition: Ratio of actual power to full load power as a quadratic function of part load, at certain condensing and evaporating temperature, FracFullLoadPower = f ( PartLoadRatio).

properties.name: MaximumTransmissionAttenuation

The temperature range in which the device operates normally.

Allowable operational air temperature range.

properties.name: AirFlowRateRange
properties.definition:
Possible range of airflow that can be delivered.

For cases where there is no airflow across the coil (e.g. electric coil in a floor slab), then the value is zero.

properties.name: NominalSensibleCapacity
properties.definition: Nominal sensible capacity.

properties.name: NominalLatentCapacity
properties.definition: Nominal latent capacity.

properties.name: NominalUA
properties.definition: Nominal UA value.

properties.name: CoilPlacement
FluidPressureRange
properties.definition: Allowable water working pressure range inside the tube.

properties.name: CoilCoolant
properties.definition: The fluid used for heating or cooling used by the hydronic coil.

properties.name: CoilConnectionDirection
properties.definition: Coil connection direction (facing into the air stream).
