CrossFlow: Air and water flow are perpendicular.

properties.name: SecondarySurfaceArea

properties.name: TotalUACurves
properties.definition: Total UA curves, UA - air and water velocities, UA = [(C1 * AirFlowRate\^0.8)\^-1 + (C2 * WaterFlowRate\^0.8)\^-1]\^-1.  Note: as two variables are used, DefiningValues and DefinedValues are null, and values are stored in IfcTable in the following order: AirFlowRate,WaterFlowRate,UA.  The IfcTable is related to IfcPropertyTableValue using IfcMetric and IfcResourceConstraintRelationship.

properties.name: BypassFactor

properties.name: SensibleHeatRatio

properties.name: WetCoilFraction

Pset_ControllerTypeFloating.name: Pset_ControllerTypeFloating
Pset_ControllerTypeFloating.definition: Properties for signal handling for an analog controller taking disparate valued multiple inputs and creating a single valued output.  HISTORY: IFC4 adapted from Pset_ControllerTypeCommon and applicable predefined type made specific to FLOATING; ACCUMULATOR and PULSECONVERTER types added; additional properties added to replace Pset_AnalogInput and Pset_AnalogOutput.

properties.name: ControlType
properties.definition:
The type controller, signal modification effected and applicable ports

CONSTANT: No inputs; SignalOffset is written to the output value.
MODIFIER: Single analog input is read, added to SignalOffset, multiplied by SignalFactor, and written to the output value.
ABSOLUTE: Single analog input is read and absolute value is written to the output value.
INVERSE: Single analog input is read, 1.0 is divided by the input value and written to the output value.
HYSTERISIS: Single analog input is read, delayed according to SignalTime, and written to the output value.
RUNNINGAVERAGE: Single analog input is read, averaged over SignalTime, and written to the output value.
DERIVATIVE: Single analog input is read and the rate of change during the SignalTime is written to the output value.
INTEGRAL: Single analog input is read and the average value during the SignalTime is written to the output value.
BINARY: Single binary input is read and SignalOffset is written to the output value if True.
ACCUMULATOR: Single binary input is read, and for each pulse the SignalOffset is added to the accumulator, and while the accumulator is greater than the SignalFactor, the accumulator is decremented by SignalFactor and the integer result is incremented by one.
PULSECONVERTER: Single integer input is read, and for each increment the SignalMultiplier is added and written to the output value.
SUM: Two analog inputs are read, added, and written to the output value.
SUBTRACT: Two analog inputs are read, subtracted, and written to the output value.
PRODUCT: Two analog inputs are read, multiplied, and written to the output value.
DIVIDE: Two analog inputs are read, divided, and written to the output value.
AVERAGE: Two analog inputs are read and the average is written to the output value.
MAXIMUM: Two analog inputs are read and the maximum is written to the output value.
MINIMUM: Two analog inputs are read and the minimum is written to the output value..
INPUT: Controller element is a dedicated input.
OUTPUT: Controller element is a dedicated output.
VARIABLE: Controller element is an in-memory variable.

properties.name: Labels
properties.definition:
Table mapping values to labels

Labels indicate transition points such as 'Hi', 'Lo', 'HiHi', or 'LoLo'.

properties.name: Range
properties.definition: The physical range of values supported by the device.

properties.name: Value
properties.definition:
The expected range and default value.

The expected range and default value.  While the property data type is IfcReal (to support all cases including when the units are unknown), a unit may optionally be provided to indicate the measure and unit.  The LowerLimitValue and UpperLimitValue must fall within the physical Range and may be used to determine extents when charting Pset_ControllerPHistory.Value.

properties.name: SignalOffset
properties.definition: Offset constant added to modified signal.

properties.name: SignalFactor
properties.definition: Factor multiplied onto offset signal.

properties.name: SignalTime
properties.definition: Time factor used for integral and running average controllers.

properties.name: ControlType

The type controller, signal modification effected and applicable ports

INPUT: Controller element is a dedicated input.
OUTPUT: Controller element is a dedicated output.
VARIABLE: Controller element is an in-memory variable.

properties.name: Labels

properties.name: IntegerRange

properties.name: Value

The expected range and default value.  The LowerLimitValue and UpperLimitValue must fall within the physical Range.

Pset_ControllerTypeProgrammable.definition: Properties for Discrete Digital Control (DDC) or programmable logic controllers.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

SECONDARY: Controller communicates with primary controller and its own managed devices.

properties.name: FirmwareVersion
properties.definition: Indicates version of device firmware according to device manufacturer.

properties.name: Application
properties.definition: Indicates application of controller.

Pset_ControllerTypeProportional.name: Pset_ControllerTypeProportional
Pset_ControllerTypeProportional.definition: Properties for signal handling for an proportional controller taking setpoint and feedback inputs and creating a single valued output. HISTORY: In IFC4, SignalFactor1, SignalFactor2 and SignalFactor3 changed to ProportionalConstant, IntegralConstant and DerivativeConstant.  SignalTime1 and SignalTime2 changed to SignalTimeIncrease and SignalTimeDecrease.

properties.name: ControlType
properties.definition:
The type controller, signal modification effected and applicable ports

PROPORTIONAL: Output is proportional to the control error. The gain of a proportional control (Kp) will have the effect of reducing the rise time and reducing , but never eliminating, the steady-state error of the variable controlled.
PROPORTIONALINTEGRAL: Part of the output is proportional to the control error and part is proportional to the time integral of the control error. Adding the gain of an integral control (Ki) will have the effect of eliminating the steady-state error of the variable controlled, but it may make the transient response worse.
PROPORTIONALINTEGRALDERIVATIVE: Part of the output is proportional to the control error, part is proportional to the time integral of the control error and part is proportional to the time derivative of the control error. Adding the gain of a derivative control (Kd) will have the effect of increasing the stability of the system, reducing the overshoot, and improving the transient response of the variable controlled.

properties.name: Labels
properties.definition:
Table mapping values to labels

Labels indicate transition points such as 'Hi', 'Lo', 'HiHi', or 'LoLo'.

properties.name: Range
properties.definition: The physical range of values supported by the device.

properties.name: Value
properties.definition:
The expected range and default value.

The expected range and default value.  While the property data type is IfcReal (to support all cases including when the units are unknown), a unit may optionally be provided to indicate the measure and unit.

properties.name: ProportionalConstant
properties.definition: The proportional gain factor of the controller (usually referred to as Kp).

properties.name: IntegralConstant
properties.definition: The integral gain factor of the controller (usually referred to as Ki).  Asserted where ControlType is PROPORTIONALINTEGRAL or PROPORTIONALINTEGRALDERIVATIVE.

properties.name: DerivativeConstant
properties.definition: The derivative gain factor of the controller (usually referred to as Kd).  Asserted where ControlType is PROPORTIONALINTEGRALDERIVATIVE.

properties.name: SignalTimeIncrease
properties.definition: Time factor used for exponential increase.

properties.name: SignalTimeDecrease
properties.definition: Time factor used for exponential decrease.

Pset_ControllerTypeTwoPosition.name: Pset_ControllerTypeTwoPosition
Pset_ControllerTypeTwoPosition.definition: Properties for signal handling for an analog controller taking disparate valued multiple inputs and creating a single valued binary output. HISTORY: In IFC4, extended properties to replace Pset_BinaryInput and Pset_BinaryOutput.

properties.name: ControlType
properties.definition:
The type controller, signal modification effected and applicable ports

LOWERLIMITSWITCH: Single analog input is read and if less than Value.LowerBound then True is written to the output value.
UPPERLIMITSWITCH: Single analog input is read and if more than Value.UpperBound then True is written to the output value.
LOWERBANDSWITCH: Single analog input is read and if less than Value.LowerBound+BandWidth then True is written to the output value.
UPPERBANDSWITCH: Single analog input is read and if more than Value.UpperBound-BandWidth then True is written to the output value.
NOT: Single binary input is read and the opposite value is written to the output value.
AND: Two binary inputs are read and if both are True then True is written to the output value.
OR: Two binary inputs are read and if either is True then True is written to the output value.
XOR: Two binary inputs are read and if one is true then True is written to the output value.
CALENDAR: No inputs; the current time is compared with an IfcWorkCalendar to which the IfcController is assigned and True is written if active.
INPUT: Controller element is a dedicated input.
OUTPUT: Controller element is a dedicated output.
VARIABLE: Controller element is an in-memory variable.

properties.name: Labels
properties.definition:

Labels indicate the meanings of True and False, such as 'Open' and 'Closed'

properties.name: Polarity
properties.definition: True indicates normal polarity; False indicates reverse polarity.

properties.name: Value
properties.definition:
The expected range and default value.

The default value such as normally-closed or normally-open.

BypassValveControl: Bypass valve modulates the water flow to control duty.

VariableSpeedPump: vary pump speed to control duty.

Pset_DistributionSystemCommon.name: Pset_DistributionSystemCommon
Pset_DistributionSystemCommon.definition: Distribution system occurrence attributes attached to an instance of IfcDistributionSystem.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition:
Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

E.g. 'WWS/VS1', which indicates the system to be WWS, subsystems VSI/400.

properties.name: ElectricalSystemType
properties.definition:
For certain purposes of electrical regulations, IEC 60364 defines types of system using type identifiers. Assignment of identifiers depends upon the relationship of the source, and of exposed conductive parts of the installation, to Ground (Earth).   Identifiers that may be assigned through IEC 60364 are:TN type system, a system having one or more points of the source of energy directly earthed, the exposed conductive parts of the installation being connected to that point by protective conductors,
TN C type system, a TN type system in which neutral and protective functions are combined in a single conductor throughout the system,
TN S type system, a TN type system having separate neutral and protective conductors throughout the system,
TN C S type system, a TN type system in which neutral and protective functions are combined in a single conductor in part of the system,
TT type system, a system having one point of the source of energy directly earthed, the exposed conductive parts of the installation being connected to earth electrodes electrically independent of the earth electrodes of the source,
IT type system, a system having no direct connection between live parts and Earth, the exposed conductive parts of the electrical installation being earthed.

properties.name: ElectricalSystemCategory
properties.definition: Designates the voltage range of the circuit, according to IEC.  HIGHVOLTAGE indicates >1000V AC or >1500V DV; LOWVOLTAGE indicates 50-1000V AC or 120-1500V DC; EXTRALOWVOLTAGE indicates <50V AC or <120V DC.

properties.name: Diversity
properties.definition:
The ratio, expressed as a numerical
value or as a percentage, of the
simultaneous maximum demand of
a group of electrical appliances or
consumers within a specified period,
to the sum of their individual maximum
demands within the same
period. The group of electrical appliances is in this case connected to this circuit. Definition from IEC 60050, IEV 691-10-04
NOTE1: It is often not desirable to size each conductor in a distribution system to support the total connected load at that point in the network. Diversity is applied on the basis of the anticipated loadings that are likely to result from all loads not being connected at the same time.
NOTE2: Diversity is applied to final circuits only, not to sub-main circuits supplying other DBs.

properties.name: NumberOfLiveConductors
properties.definition: Number of live conductors within this circuit. Either this property or the ConductorFunction property (if only one) may be asserted.

properties.name: MaximumAllowedVoltageDrop
properties.definition:
The maximum voltage drop across the circuit that must not be exceeded.
There are two  voltage drop limit settings that may be applied; one for sub-main circuits, and one in each Distribution Board or Consumer Unit for final circuits connected to that board. The settings should limit the overall voltage drop to the required level. Default settings of 1.5% for sub-main circuits and 2.5% for final circuits, giving an overall limit of 4% may be applied.
NOTE: This value may also be specified as a constraint within an IFC model if required but is included within the property set at this stage pending implementation of the required capabilities within software applications.

properties.name: NetImpedance
properties.definition: The maximum earth loop impedance upstream of a circuit (typically stated as the variable Zs). This value is for 55o C (130oF) Celsius usage.

properties.name: RatedVoltageRange
properties.definition: Voltage range as declared by the manufacturer expressed by its lower and upper rated voltages [Source : IEC 62368-1:2010, 3.3.10.5].

properties.name: ContactWireNominalDrop

properties.name: PressureRange

properties.name: ContactWireNominalHeight

properties.name: ContactWireUplift

properties.name: ElectricalClearance

properties.name: NumberOfOverlappingSpans

properties.name: PantographType

properties.name: TensionLength

properties.definition:
Acoustic rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code. It indicates the sound transmission resistance of this object by an index ratio (instead of providing full sound absorption values).

properties.name: SecurityRating
properties.definition:
Index based rating system indicating security level.
It is giving according to the national building code.

properties.name: DurabilityRating
properties.definition: Durability against mechanical stress. It is given according to the national code or regulation.

properties.name: HygrothermalRating
properties.definition: Resistance against hygrothermal impact from different temperatures and humidities inside and outside. It is given according to the national code or regulation.

properties.name: WaterTightnessRating
properties.definition:
Water tightness rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code.

properties.name: MechanicalLoadRating
properties.definition:
Mechanical load rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code.

properties.name: WindLoadRating
properties.definition:
Wind load resistance rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code.

properties.name: Infiltration
properties.definition: Infiltration flowrate of outside air for the filler object based on the area of the filler object at a pressure level of 50 Pascals. It shall be used, if the length of all joints is unknown.

properties.name: IsExternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

properties.name: ThermalTransmittance
properties.definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of an element, within the direction of the thermal flow (including all materials).

properties.name: GlazingAreaFraction
properties.definition:
Fraction of the glazing area relative to the total area of the filling element.
It shall be used, if the glazing area is not given separately for all panels within the filling element.

properties.name: HandicapAccessible
properties.definition: Indication that this object is designed to be accessible by the handicapped. Set to (TRUE) if this object is rated as handicap accessible according to the local building codes, otherwise (FALSE). It is giving according to the requirements of the national building code.

properties.name: FireExit
properties.definition:
Indication whether this object is designed to serve as an exit in the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Here it defines an exit door in accordance to the national building code.

properties.name: HasDrive
properties.definition: Indication whether this object has an automatic drive to operate it (TRUE) or no drive (FALSE)

properties.name: SelfClosing
properties.definition: Indication whether this object is designed to close automatically after use (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: SmokeStop
properties.definition: Indication whether the object is designed to provide a smoke stop (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Pset_DoorLiningProperties.name: Pset_DoorLiningProperties
Pset_DoorLiningProperties.definition: Properties of the door lining.HISTORY New property set in IFC4.3.2.0 to replace the entity IfcDoorLiningProperties

properties.name: LiningDepth
properties.definition:
The depth of the lining.

For a door, it is the depth of the door lining, measured perpendicular to the plane of the door lining. If omitted (and with a given value to lining thickness) it indicates an adjustable depth (i.e. a depth that adjusts to the thickness of the wall into which the occurrence of this door style is inserted).

properties.name: LiningThickness
properties.definition:
Thickness of the lining.

For a door, it is the thickness of the door lining as explained in the figure above. If LiningThickness value is 0. (zero) it denotes a door without a lining (all other lining parameters shall be set to NIL in this case). If the LiningThickness is NIL it denotes that the value is not available.

properties.name: ThresholdDepth
properties.definition: Depth (dimension in plane perpendicular to door leaf) of the door threshold. Only given if the door lining includes a threshold. If omitted (and with a given value to threshold thickness) it indicates an adjustable depth (i.e. a depth that adjusts to the thickness of the wall into which the occurrence of this door style is inserted).

properties.name: ThresholdThickness
properties.definition: Thickness of the door threshold as explained in the figure above. If ThresholdThickness value is 0. (zero) it denotes a door without a threshold (ThresholdDepth shall be set to NIL in this case). If the ThresholdThickness is NIL it denotes that the information about a threshold is not available.

properties.name: TransomThickness
properties.definition:
Thickness of the transom.

For a door, it is the thickness (width in plane parallel to door leaf) of the transom (if provided - that is, if the TransomOffset attribute is set), which divides the door leaf from a glazing (or window) above. If the TransomThickness is set to zero (and the TransomOffset set to a positive length), then the door is divided vertically into a leaf and transom window area without a physical frame.

properties.name: TransomOffset
properties.definition: Offset of the transom (if given) which divides the door leaf from a glazing (or window) above. The offset is given from the bottom of the door opening.

properties.name: LiningOffset
properties.definition:
Offset of the lining.

For a door, it is the offset (dimension in plane perpendicular to door leaf) of the door lining. The offset is given as distance to the x axis of the local placement.

properties.name: ThresholdOffset
properties.definition: Offset (dimension in plane perpendicular to door leaf) of the door threshold. The offset is given as distance to the x axis of the local placement. Only given if the door lining includes a threshold and the parameter is known.

properties.name: CasingThickness
properties.definition:
Thickness of the casing.

For a door, it is the dimension in plane of the door leaf. If given it is applied equally to all four sides of the adjacent wall.

properties.name: CasingDepth
properties.definition:
Depth of the casing.

For a door, it is the dimension in the plane perpendicular to door leaf. If given it is applied equally to all four sides of the adjacent wall.

properties.name: LiningToPanelOffsetX
properties.definition:
Offset between the lining and the panel, measured along the x-axis of the local placement.

For a door, it is the offset between the lining and the window panel.

properties.name: LiningToPanelOffsetY
properties.definition:
Offset between the lining and the panel, measured along the y-axis of the local placement.

For a door, it is the offset between the lining and the door panel.

Pset_DoorPanelProperties.name: Pset_DoorPanelProperties
Pset_DoorPanelProperties.definition: Properties of the door panel.HISTORY New property set in IFC4.3.2.0 to replace the entity IfcDoorPanelProperties

properties.name: PanelDepth
properties.definition:
Depth of the panel.

For a door, it is the depth of the door panel, measured perpendicular to the plane of the door leaf.

properties.name: PanelOperation
properties.definition:
The way of operation of a panel.

For a door, it is the way of operation of the panel. The PanelOperation of the door panel shall correspond to the OperationType of the IfcDoorType by which it is referenced.

properties.name: PanelWidth
properties.definition:
Width of the panel.

For a door, it is the width of the panel, given as ratio relative to the total clear opening width of the door. If omitted, it defaults to 1. A value shall be provided for all doors with OperationType's at IfcDoorType defining a door with more then one panel.

properties.name: PanelPosition
properties.definition:
Position of the panel.

For a door, it is the position of the panel within the door. The PanelPosition of the door panel shall correspond to the OperationType of the IfcDoorType by which it is referenced.

Pset_DoorTypeTurnstile.name: Pset_DoorTypeTurnstile
Pset_DoorTypeTurnstile.definition: Properties common to turnstiles or automatic gates used to control the flow of people or vehicles. This property set is applied to IfcDoor instances of predefined type TURNSTILE.

properties.name: IsBidirectional
properties.definition: Indicates whether the turnstile is bidirectional.

properties.name: TurnstileType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of turnstile gate.

properties.name: NarrowChannelWidth
properties.definition: Indicates the width of the narrow channel.

properties.name: WideChannelWidth
properties.definition: Indicates the width of the wide channel.

Pset_DoorWindowGlazingType.name: Pset_DoorWindowGlazingType
Pset_DoorWindowGlazingType.definition: Properties common to the definition of the glazing component of occurrences of IfcDoor and IfcWindow, used for thermal and lighting calculations.

properties.name: GlassLayers
properties.definition: Number of glass layers within the frame. E.g. "2" for double glazing.

properties.name: GlassThickness1
properties.definition: Thickness of the first (inner) glass layer.

properties.name: GlassThickness2
properties.definition: Thickness of the second (intermediate or outer) glass layer.

properties.name: GlassThickness3
properties.definition: Thickness of the third (outer) glass layer.

properties.name: FillGas
properties.definition: Name of the gas by which the gap between two glass layers is filled. It is given for information purposes only.

properties.name: GlassColour
properties.definition: Colour (tint) selection for this glazing. It is given for information purposes only.

properties.name: IsTempered
properties.definition: Indication whether the glass is tempered (TRUE) or not (FALSE) .

properties.name: IsLaminated
properties.definition: Indication whether the glass is layered with other materials (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: IsCoated
properties.definition: Indication whether the glass is coated with a material (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: IsWired
properties.definition: Indication whether the glass includes a contained wire mesh to prevent break-in (TRUE) or not (FALSE)

properties.name: VisibleLightReflectance
properties.definition: Fraction of the visible light that is reflected by the glazing at normal incidence. It is a value without unit.

properties.name: VisibleLightTransmittance
properties.definition: Fraction of the visible light that passes the object at normal incidence. It is a value without unit.

properties.name: SolarAbsorption
properties.definition: (Asol) The ratio of incident solar radiation that is absorbed by a glazing system. It is the sum of the absorption distributed to the exterior (a) and to the interior (qi). Note the following equation Asol + Rsol + Tsol = 1

properties.name: SolarReflectance
properties.definition: (Rsol): The ratio of incident solar radiation that is reflected by a glazing system (also named e). Note the following equation Asol + Rsol + Tsol = 1

properties.name: SolarTransmittance
properties.definition: The ratio of incident solar radiation that directly passes through a system (also named e). Note the following equation Asol + Rsol + Tsol = 1

properties.name: SolarHeatGainTransmittance
properties.definition: (SHGC): The ratio of incident solar radiation that contributes to the heat gain of the interior, it is the solar radiation that directly passes (Tsol or e) plus the part of the absorbed radiation that is distributed to the interior (qi). The SHGC is referred to also as g-value (g = e + qi).

properties.name: ShadingCoefficient
properties.definition: (SC): The measure of the ability of a glazing to transmit solar heat, relative to that ability for 3 mm (1/8-inch) clear, double-strength, single glass. Shading coefficient is being phased out in favor of the solar heat gain coefficient (SHGC), and is approximately equal to the SHGC multiplied by 1.15. The shading coefficient is expressed as a number without units between 0 and 1.

properties.name: ThermalTransmittanceSummer
properties.definition:
Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of a material.
Summer thermal transmittance coefficient of the glazing only, often referred to as (U-value).

properties.name: ThermalTransmittanceWinter
properties.definition:
Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of a material.
Winter thermal transmittance coefficient of the glazing only, often referred to as (U-value).

properties.name: InteriorRoughnessCoefficient
properties.definition: The interior roughness of the material of the object.

properties.name: HasLiner
properties.definition: TRUE if the fitting has interior duct insulating lining, FALSE if it does not.

properties.name: Colour
properties.definition: Colour of this object.

Pset_DuctFittingPHistory.name: Pset_DuctFittingPHistory
Pset_DuctFittingPHistory.definition: Duct fitting performance history common attributes.

properties.name: LossCoefficient
properties.definition: Dimensionless loss coefficient used for calculating fluid resistance representing the ratio of total pressure loss to velocity pressure at a referenced cross-section.

properties.name: AtmosphericPressure
properties.definition: Ambient atmospheric pressure.

properties.name: AirFlowLeakage
properties.definition: Volumetric leakage flow rate.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: PressureClass
properties.definition:
Nominal pressure rating of the object.

Pressure classification as defined by the authority having jurisdiction (e.g., SMACNA, etc.).

properties.name: PressureRange
properties.definition: Allowable maximum and minimum working pressure (relative to ambient pressure).

properties.name: TemperatureRange
properties.definition: Allowable maximum and minimum temperature.

Pset_DuctSegmentOccurrence.name: Pset_DuctSegmentOccurrence
Pset_DuctSegmentOccurrence.definition: Duct segment occurrence attributes attached to an instance of IfcDuctSegment.

properties.name: InteriorRoughnessCoefficient
properties.definition: The interior roughness of the material of the object.

properties.name: HasLiner
properties.definition: TRUE if the fitting has interior duct insulating lining, FALSE if it does not.

properties.name: Colour
properties.definition: Colour of this object.

Pset_DuctSegmentPHistory.name: Pset_DuctSegmentPHistory
Pset_DuctSegmentPHistory.definition: Duct segment performance history common attributes.

properties.name: LossCoefficient
properties.definition: Dimensionless loss coefficient used for calculating fluid resistance representing the ratio of total pressure loss to velocity pressure at a referenced cross-section.

properties.name: AtmosphericPressure
properties.definition: Ambient atmospheric pressure.

properties.name: LeakageCurveHistory
properties.definition: Leakage per unit length curve versus working pressure. If a scalar is expressed then it represents LeakageClass which is flowrate per unit area at a specified pressure rating (e.g., ASHRAE Fundamentals 2001 34.16.).

properties.name: FluidFlowLeakage
properties.definition: Volumetric leakage flow rate.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: CrossSectionShape
properties.definition: Cross sectional shape. Note that this shape is uniform throughout the length of the segment. For nonuniform shapes, a transition fitting should be used instead.

properties.name: WorkingPressure
properties.definition:
Working pressure.

Pressure classification as defined by the authority having jurisdiction (e.g., SMACNA, etc.).

properties.name: PressureRange
properties.definition: Allowable maximum and minimum working pressure (relative to ambient pressure).

properties.name: TemperatureRange
properties.definition: Allowable maximum and minimum temperature.

properties.name: LongitudinalSeam
properties.definition: The type of seam to be used along the longitudinal axis of the duct segment.

properties.name: NominalDiameterOrWidth
properties.definition: The nominal diameter or width of the duct segment.

properties.name: NominalHeight
properties.definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: Reinforcement
properties.definition: The type of reinforcement, if any, used for the duct segment.

properties.name: ReinforcementSpacing
properties.definition: The spacing between reinforcing elements.

Pset_DuctSilencerPHistory.name: Pset_DuctSilencerPHistory
Pset_DuctSilencerPHistory.definition: Duct silencer performance history common attributes.

properties.name: AirFlowRate
properties.definition:
Air flow rate.

Volumetric air flow rate.

properties.name: AirPressureDropCurve
properties.definition: Air pressure drop as a function of air flow rate.

Pset_DuctSilencerTypeCommon.name: Pset_DuctSilencerTypeCommon
Pset_DuctSilencerTypeCommon.definition:
Duct silencer type common attributes.
InsertionLoss and RegeneratedSound attributes deleted in IFC2x2 Pset Addendum: Use IfcSoundProperties instead.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: HydraulicDiameter
properties.definition: Hydraulic diameter.

properties.name: Length
properties.definition: The length of the object.

properties.name: Weight
properties.definition: Total weight of object

properties.name: AirFlowRateRange
properties.definition: Possible range of airflow that can be delivered.

properties.name: WorkingPressureRange
properties.definition: Allowable minimum and maximum  working pressure (relative to ambient pressure).

properties.name: TemperatureRange
properties.definition: Allowable maximum and minimum temperature.

properties.name: HasExteriorInsulation
properties.definition: TRUE if the silencer has exterior insulation. FALSE if it does not.

Pset_ElectricalDeviceCommon.name: Pset_ElectricalDeviceCommon
Pset_ElectricalDeviceCommon.definition: A collection of properties that are commonly used by electrical device types.

properties.name: RatedCurrent
properties.definition: The current that a device is designed to handle.

properties.name: RatedVoltage
properties.definition: The range of allowed voltage that a device is certified to handle. The upper bound of this value is the maximum.

properties.name: NominalFrequencyRange
properties.definition: The upper and lower limits of frequency for which the operation of the device is certified.

properties.name: PowerFactor
properties.definition:
Power factor; usually as ratio.

The ratio between the rated electrical power and the product of the rated current and rated voltage

properties.name: ConductorFunction
properties.definition: Indicates function of the conductors to which the load is connected. Where L1, L2 and L3 represent the phase lines according to IEC 60446 notation (sometimes phase lines may be referenced by color [Red, Blue, Yellow] or by number [1, 2, 3] etc). Protective Earth is sometimes also known as CPC or common protective conductor. Note that for an electrical device, a set of line conductor functions may be applied.

properties.name: NumberOfPoles
properties.definition:
Number of poles that the object would affect.

The number of live lines that is intended to be handled by the device.

properties.name: HasProtectiveEarth
properties.definition: Indicates whether the object has a protective earth connection (=TRUE) or not (= FALSE).

properties.name: InsulationStandardClass
properties.definition: Insulation standard classes provides basic protection information against electric shock. Defines levels of insulation required in terms of constructional requirements (creepage and clearance distances) and electrical requirements (compliance with electric strength tests). Basic insulation is considered to be shorted under single fault conditions. The actual values required depend on the working voltage to which the insulation is subjected, as well as other factors. Also indicates whether the electrical device has a protective earth connection.

properties.name: IP_Code
properties.definition: IP Code, the International Protection Marking, IEC 60529), classifies and rates the degree of protection provided against intrusion.

properties.name: IK_Code
properties.definition: IK Code according to IEC 62262 (2002) is a numeric classification for the degree of protection provided by enclosures for electrical equipment against external mechanical impacts.NOTE  In earlier labeling, the third numeral (1..) had been occasionally added to the closely related IP Code on ingress protection, to indicate the level of impact protection.

properties.name: EarthingStyle
properties.definition: Indicates the earthing style of the electric device.

properties.name: HeatDissipation
properties.definition: Indicates the heat dissipation of the electric device measured in power.

properties.name: Power
properties.definition: The actual power and operable range.

properties.name: NominalPowerConsumption
properties.definition: Nominal total power consumption.

properties.name: NumberOfPowerSupplyPorts
properties.definition: Indicates the number of power supply ports of the electric device.

Pset_ElectricalDeviceCompliance.name: Pset_ElectricalDeviceCompliance
Pset_ElectricalDeviceCompliance.definition: Properties related to information about compliance to standards or regulations of electric devices.

properties.name: ElectroMagneticStandardsCompliance
properties.definition: Information about compliance with regard to electro magnetic related standards.

properties.name: ExplosiveAtmosphereStandardsCompliance
properties.definition: Information about compliance with regard to explosive atmosphere related standards.

properties.name: FireProofingStandardsCompliance
properties.definition: Information about compliance with regard to fire proofing related standards.

properties.name: LightningProtectionStandardsCompliance
properties.definition: Information about compliance with regard to lightning protection related standards.

Pset_ElectricalFeederLine.name: Pset_ElectricalFeederLine
Pset_ElectricalFeederLine.definition: Properties of conductors used as feeder line. This property set is applicable to a type or occurrence of IfcCableSegment with predefined type CONDUCTORSEGMENT.

properties.name: CurrentCarryingCapacity
properties.definition: Maximum value of electric current which can be carried continuously by a conductor, a device or an apparatus, under specified conditions without its steady-state temperature exceeding a  specified value. Based on IEC60826-11-13. NOTE: The temperature specified value is maximum Design Ambient Temperature.

properties.name: DesignAmbientTemperature
properties.definition: The highest and lowest local ambient temperature likely to be encountered.

properties.name: ElectricalClearanceDistance
properties.definition: The distance between two conductive parts along a string stretched the shortest way between these conductive parts. (IEV ref 441-17-31)

properties.name: ElectricalFeederType
properties.definition: Type of electrical feeder.

Pset_ElectricAppliancePHistory.name: Pset_ElectricAppliancePHistory
Pset_ElectricAppliancePHistory.definition: Captures realtime information for electric appliances, such as for energy usage.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: PowerState
properties.definition: Indicates the power state of the device where True is on and False is off.

Pset_ElectricApplianceTypeCommon.name: Pset_ElectricApplianceTypeCommon
Pset_ElectricApplianceTypeCommon.definition: Common properties for electric appliances.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

Pset_ElectricApplianceTypeDishwasher.name: Pset_ElectricApplianceTypeDishwasher
Pset_ElectricApplianceTypeDishwasher.definition: Common properties for dishwasher appliances.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: DishwasherType
properties.definition: Type of dishwasher.

Pset_ElectricApplianceTypeElectricCooker.name: Pset_ElectricApplianceTypeElectricCooker
Pset_ElectricApplianceTypeElectricCooker.definition: Common properties for electric cooker appliances.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: ElectricCookerType
properties.definition: Type of electric cooker.

Pset_ElectricFlowStorageDeviceTypeBatter.name: Pset_ElectricFlowStorageDeviceTypeBattery
Pset_ElectricFlowStorageDeviceTypeBatter.definition: Properties of batteries. The property set can be used by the predefined type BATTERY of IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.

properties.name: CurrentRegulationRate
properties.definition: It shows the ability of DC regulated power supply to suppress the fluctuation of output voltage caused by the change of load current (output current) when the input voltage is constant.

properties.name: NominalSupplyCurrent
properties.definition: The nominal current of the supply.

properties.name: VoltageRegulationRate
properties.definition: When the input side voltage changes from the lowest allowable input value to the specified maximum value, the relative change value of the output voltage is the percentage of the rated output voltage.

properties.name: AssemblyInstruction
properties.definition: Instructions to describe how the system / equipment / facility is assembled.

properties.name: BatteryChargingType
properties.definition: Identifies the predefined types of battery charging.

properties.name: EncapsulationTechnologyCode
properties.definition: Code indicating the encapsulation technology which has been applied in an electric, electronic or electromechanical component.

properties.name: OpenCircuitVoltage
properties.definition: Voltage of a cell or battery when the discharge current is zero  [Source IEC 482-03-32]

Pset_ElectricFlowStorageDeviceTypeCapaci.name: Pset_ElectricFlowStorageDeviceTypeCapacitor
Pset_ElectricFlowStorageDeviceTypeCapaci.definition: Properties of capacitors. The property set can be used by the predefined type CAPACITOR of IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.

properties.name: NumberOfPhases
properties.definition: Number of phases that the equipment operates on.

Pset_ElectricFlowStorageDeviceTypeCommon.name: Pset_ElectricFlowStorageDeviceTypeCommon
Pset_ElectricFlowStorageDeviceTypeCommon.definition: The characteristics of the supply associated with an electrical device occurrence acting as a source of supply to an electrical distribution system NOTE: Properties within this property set should ONLY be used in circumstances when an electrical supply is applied. The property set, the properties contained and their values are not applicable to a circumstance where the sypply  is not being applied to the eletrical system or is temporarily disconnected. All properties within this property set are considered to represent a steady state situation.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: NominalSupplyVoltage
properties.definition: The nominal voltage of the supply.

properties.name: NominalSupplyVoltageOffset
properties.definition: The maximum and minimum allowed voltage of the supply e.g. boundaries of 380V/440V may be applied for a nominal voltage of 400V.

properties.name: NominalFrequency
properties.definition: The nominal frequency of the supply.

properties.name: ConnectedConductorFunction
properties.definition: Function of the conductors to which the load is connected.

properties.name: ShortCircuit3PoleMaximumState
properties.definition: Maximum 3 pole short circuit current provided at the point of supply.

properties.name: ShortCircuit3PolePowerFactorMaximumState
properties.definition: Power factor of the maximum 3 pole short circuit current provided at the point of supply.

properties.name: ShortCircuit2PoleMinimumState
properties.definition: Minimum 2 pole short circuit current provided at the point of supply.

properties.name: ShortCircuit2PolePowerFactorMinimumState
properties.definition: Power factor of the minimum 2 pole short circuit current provided at the point of supply.

properties.name: ShortCircuit1PoleMaximumState
properties.definition: Maximum 1 pole short circuit current provided at the point of supply i.e. the fault between 1 phase and N.

properties.name: ShortCircuit1PolePowerFactorMaximumState
properties.definition: Power factor of the maximum 1 pole short circuit current provided at the point of supply i.e. the fault between 1 phase and N.

properties.name: ShortCircuit1PoleMinimumState
properties.definition: Minimum 1 pole short circuit current provided at the point of supply i.e. the fault between 1 phase and N.

properties.name: ShortCircuit1PolePowerFactorMinimumState
properties.definition: Power factor of the minimum 1 pole short circuit current provided at the point of supply i.e. the fault between 1 phase and N.

properties.name: EarthFault1PoleMaximumState
properties.definition: Maximum 1 pole earth fault current provided at the point of supply i.e. the fault between 1 phase and PE/PEN.

properties.name: EarthFault1PolePowerFactorMaximumState
properties.definition: Power factor of the maximum 1 pole earth fault  current provided at the point of supply i.e. the fault between 1 phase and PE/PEN.

properties.name: EarthFault1PoleMinimumState
properties.definition: Minimum 1 pole earth fault current provided at the point of supply i.e. the fault between 1 phase and PE/PEN.

properties.name: EarthFault1PolePowerFactorMinimumState
properties.definition: Power factor of the minimum 1 pole earth fault current provided at the point of supply i.e. the fault between 1 phase and PE/PEN.

properties.name: MaximumInsulatedVoltage

properties.name: RatedCapacitance

Pset_EnvironmentalImpactIndicators.name: Pset_EnvironmentalImpactIndicators
Pset_EnvironmentalImpactIndicators.definition:
Environmental impact indicators are related to a given functional unit (ISO 14040 concept). An example of functional unit is a "Double glazing window with PVC frame" and the unit to consider is "one square meter of opening elements filled by this product.
Indicators values are valid for the whole life cycle or only a specific phase (see LifeCyclePhase property). Values of all the indicators are expressed per year according to the expected service life. The first five properties capture the characteristics of the functional unit. The following properties are related to environmental indicators.
There is a consensus agreement international for the five one. Last ones are not yet fully and formally agreed at the international level.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". Pset_FastenerRailWeld.definition: Properties of Welded rail joint used in railway. The property set can be used by the predefined type WELD of IfcFastener.

properties.name: IsLiftingBracket
properties.definition: Indicates whether the connection is done between rail with different height (TRUE) or with same height (FALSE).

properties.name: TemperatureDuringInstallation
properties.definition: Normalised working temperature.

properties.name: JointRelativePosition
properties.definition: Indicates the relative position of the joint, which lies in the left or right rail or in the middle, or in combination. The left rail is to the left as facing in the direction of increasing stationing values, and the right rail is to the right.

properties.name: AssemblyPlace
properties.definition: Enumeration defining where the assembly is intended to take place, either in a factory, other offsite location or on the building site.

properties.name: Type1
properties.definition: Type of weld seam according to ISO 2553.  Note, combined welds are given by two corresponding symbols in the direction of the normal axis of the coordinate system.  For example, an X weld is specified by Type1 = 'V' and Type2 = 'V'.

properties.name: Type2
properties.definition: See Type1.

properties.name: Surface1
properties.definition: Aspect of weld seam surface, i.e. 'plane', 'curved' or 'hollow'.  Combined welds are given by two corresponding symbols analogous to Type1 and Type2.

properties.name: Surface2
properties.definition: See Surface1.

properties.name: Process
properties.definition: Reference number of the welding process according to ISO 4063, an up to three digits long code

properties.name: ProcessName
properties.definition: Name of the welding process.  Alternative to the numeric Process property.

properties.name: NominalThroatThickness
properties.definition: Design value of the height of the largest isosceles triangle that can be inscribed in the section of a fillet weld.REFERENCE Symbol a according to ISO 2553:2019.

properties.name: WeldWidth
properties.definition: Required elongated hole width at the faying surface or seam weld width at the faying surface.REFERENCE Symbol c according to ISO 2553:2019.

properties.name: WeldDiameter
properties.definition: Dimension of the required hole diameter at the faying surface, or required spot weld diameter at the faying surface, or required stud diameter.REFERENCE Symbol d according to ISO 2553:2019.

properties.name: WeldElementSpacing
properties.definition: Spacing between weld elements (centre to centre)REFERENCE Symbol e according to ISO 2553:2019.

properties.name: WeldElementLength
properties.definition: Length of each weld element.REFERENCE Symbol l according to ISO 2553:2019.

properties.name: NumberOfWeldElements
properties.definition: Number of weld elements.REFERENCE Symbol n according to ISO 2553:2019.

properties.name: DeepPenetrationThroatThickness
properties.definition: Nominal throat thickness or effective throat thickness to which a certain amount of fusion penetration is added.REFERENCE Symbol s according to ISO 2553:2019.

properties.name: WeldLegLength
properties.definition: Distance from the actual or projected intersection of the fusion faces and the toe of a fillet weld, measured across the fusion face.REFERENCE Symbol z according to ISO 2553:2019.

properties.name: Intermittent
properties.definition: If fillet weld, intermittent or not

properties.name: Staggered
properties.definition: If intermittent weld, staggered or not

properties.name: AirParticleFilterType
properties.definition:
A panel dry type extended surface filter is a dry-type air filter with random fiber mats or blankets in the forms of pockets, V-shaped or radial pleats, and include the following:CoarseFilter: Filter with a efficiency lower than 30% for atmosphere dust-spot.
CoarseMetalScreen: Filter made of metal screen.
CoarseCellFoams: Filter made of cell foams.
CoarseSpunGlass: Filter made of spun glass.
MediumFilter: Filter with an efficiency between 30-98% for atmosphere dust-spot.
MediumElectretFilter: Filter with fine electret synthetic fibers.
MediumNaturalFiberFilter: Filter with natural fibers.
HEPAFilter: High efficiency particulate air filter.
ULPAFilter: Ultra low penetration air filter.
MembraneFilters: Filter made of membrane for certain pore diameters in flat sheet and pleated form.
A renewable media with a moving curtain viscous filter are random-fiber media coated with viscous substance in roll form or curtain where fresh media is fed across the face of the filter and the dirty media is rewound onto a roll at the bottom or to into a reservoir:
RollForm: Viscous filter used in roll form.
AdhesiveReservoir: Viscous filter used in moving curtain form.
A renewable moving curtain dry media filter is a random-fiber dry media of relatively high porosity used in moving-curtain(roll) filters.
An electrical filter uses electrostatic precipitation to remove and collect particulate contaminants.

properties.name: FrameMaterial
properties.definition: Filter frame material.

properties.name: SeparationType
properties.definition: Air particulate filter media separation type.

properties.name: DustHoldingCapacity
properties.definition: Maximum filter dust holding capacity.

properties.name: FaceSurfaceArea
properties.definition: Face area of filter frame.

properties.name: MediaExtendedArea

properties.name: NominalCountedEfficiency
properties.definition: Nominal filter efficiency based the particle count concentration before and after the filter against particles with a certain size distribution.

properties.name: NominalWeightedEfficiency
properties.definition: Nominal filter efficiency based the particle weight concentration before and after the filter against particles with a certain size distribution.

properties.name: PressureDropCurve
properties.definition: Under certain dust holding weight, DelPressure = f (fluidflowRate)

properties.name: CountedEfficiencyCurve
properties.definition: Counted efficiency curve as a function of dust holding weight, efficiency = f (dust holding weight).

properties.name: WeightedEfficiencyCurve
properties.definition: Weighted efficiency curve as a function of dust holding weight, efficiency = f (dust holding weight).

properties.name: NominalParticleGeometricMeanDiameter
properties.definition: Particle geometric mean diameter associated with nominal efficiency.

properties.name: NominalParticleGeometricStandardDeviation
properties.definition: Particle geometric standard deviation associated with nominal efficiency.

properties.name: CompressedAirFilterType
properties.definition: ACTIVATEDCARBON: absorbs oil vapor and odor; PARTICLE_FILTER: used to absorb solid particles of medium size; COALESCENSE_FILTER: used to absorb fine solid, oil, and water particles, also called micro filter

properties.name: OperationPressureMax
properties.definition: Maximum pressure under normal operating conditions.

properties.name: ParticleAbsorptionCurve
properties.definition: Ratio of particles that are removed by the filter.  Each entry describes the ratio of particles absorbed greater than equal to the specified size and less than the next specified size.  For example,  given for 3 significant particle sizes >= 0,1 micro m, >= 1 micro m, >= 5 micro m
