The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: ContributedLuminousFlux
properties.definition: Luminous flux is a photometric measure of radiant flux, i.e. the volume of light emitted from a light source. Luminous flux is measured either for the interior as a whole or for a part of the interior (partial luminous flux for a solid angle). All other photometric parameters are derivatives of luminous flux. Luminous flux is measured in lumens (lm). The luminous flux is given as a nominal value for each lamp.

properties.name: LightEmitterNominalPower
properties.definition: Light emitter nominal power.

properties.name: LampMaintenanceFactor
properties.definition: Non recoverable losses of luminous flux of a lamp due to lamp depreciation; i.e. the decreasing of light output of a luminaire due to aging and dirt.

properties.name: LampBallastType
properties.definition:
The type of ballast used to stabilise gas discharge by limiting the current during operation and to deliver the necessary striking voltage for starting. Ballasts are needed to operate Discharge Lamps such as Fluorescent, Compact Fluorescent, High-pressure Mercury, Metal Halide and High-pressure Sodium Lamps.
Magnetic ballasts are chokes which limit the current passing through a lamp connected in series on the principle of self-induction. The resultant current and power are decisive for the efficient operation of the lamp. A specially designed ballast is required for every type of lamp to comply with lamp rating in terms of Luminous Flux, Color Appearance and service life. The two types of magnetic ballasts for fluorescent lamps are KVG Conventional   (EC-A series) and VVG Low-loss ballasts (EC-B series). Low-loss ballasts have a higher efficiency, which means reduced ballast losses and a lower thermal load. Electronic ballasts are used to run fluorescent lamps at high frequencies (approx. 35 - 40 kHz).

properties.name: LampCompensationType
properties.definition: Identifies the form of compensation used for power factor correction and radio suppression.

properties.name: ColourAppearance
properties.definition: In both the DIN and CIE standards, artificial light sources are classified in terms of their colour appearance. To the human eye they all appear to be white; the difference can only be detected by direct comparison. Visual performance is not directly affected by differences in colour appearance.

properties.name: Spectrum
properties.definition: The spectrum of radiation describes its composition with regard to wavelength. Light, for example, as the portion of electromagnetic radiation that is visible to the human eye, is radiation with wavelengths in the range of approx. 380 to 780 nm (1 nm = 10 m). The corresponding range of colours varies from violet to indigo, blue, green, yellow, orange, and red. These colours form a continuous spectrum, in which the various spectral sectors merge into each other.

properties.name: ColourTemperature
properties.definition: The colour temperature of any source of radiation is defined as the temperature (in Kelvin) of a black-body or Planckian radiator whose radiation has the same chromaticity as the source of radiation. Often the values are only approximate colour temperatures as the black-body radiator cannot emit radiation of every chromaticity value. The colour temperatures of the commonest artificial light sources range from less than 3000K (warm white) to 4000K (intermediate) and over 5000K (daylight).

properties.name: ColourRenderingIndex
properties.definition: The CRI indicates how well a light source renders eight standard colours compared to perfect reference lamp with the same colour temperature. The CRI scale ranges from 1 to 100, with 100 representing perfect rendering properties.

Pset_LandRegistration.name: Pset_LandRegistration
Pset_LandRegistration.definition: Specifies the identity of land within a statutory registration system.NOTE  The property LandTitleID is to be used in preference to deprecated attribute LandTitleNumber in IfcSite.

properties.name: LandID
properties.definition: Identification number assigned by the statutory registration authority to a land parcel.

properties.name: IsPermanentID
properties.definition: Indicates whether the identity assigned to the object is permanent (= TRUE) or temporary (=FALSE).

properties.name: LandTitleID
properties.definition: Identification number assigned by the statutory registration authority to the title to a land parcel.

Pset_LightFixtureTypeCommon.name: Pset_LightFixtureTypeCommon
Pset_LightFixtureTypeCommon.definition:
Common data for light fixtures.
History: IFC4 - Article number and manufacturer specific information deleted. Use Pset_ManufacturerTypeInformation. ArticleNumber instead.   Load properties moved from Pset_LightFixtureTypeThermal (deleted).

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: NumberOfSources
properties.definition: Number of sources .

properties.name: TotalWattage
properties.definition: Wattage on whole lightfitting device with all sources intact.

properties.name: LightFixtureMountingType
properties.definition: A list of the available types of mounting for light fixtures from which that required may be selected.

properties.name: LightFixturePlacingType
properties.definition: A list of the available types of placing specification for light fixtures from which that required may be selected.

properties.name: MaintenanceFactor
properties.definition: The arithmetical allowance made for depreciation of lamps and reflective equipment from their initial values due to dirt, fumes, or age.

properties.name: MaximumPlenumSensibleLoad
properties.definition: Maximum or Peak sensible thermal load contributed to return air plenum by the light fixture.

properties.name: MaximumSpaceSensibleLoad
properties.definition: Maximum or Peak sensible thermal load contributed to the conditioned space by the light fixture.

properties.name: SensibleLoadToRadiant
properties.definition: Percent of sensible thermal load to radiant heat.

properties.name: SecurityLightingType
properties.definition: The type of security lighting.

properties.name: FixtureHeight
properties.definition: The height of the fixture, such as the text height of an exit sign.

properties.name: SelfTestFunction
properties.definition: The type of self test function.

properties.name: BackupSupplySystem
properties.definition: The type of backup supply system.

properties.name: PictogramEscapeDirection
properties.definition: The direction of escape pictogram.

properties.name: Addressablility
properties.definition: The type of addressability.

Pset_LinearReferencingMethod.name: Pset_LinearReferencingMethod
Pset_LinearReferencingMethod.definition: Describes the manner in which measurements are made along (and optionally offset from) a linear element.NOTE Definition according to ISO 19148:2021

properties.name: LRMName
properties.definition:
Gives the name of this Linear Referencing Method, such as kilometre-point.NOTE Definition according to ISO 19148:2021.
NOTE Names of commonly used Linear Referencing Methods are included in ISO 19148, Annex C, along with recognized name aliases.

properties.name: LRMType
properties.definition:
Gives the type of this Linear Referencing Method.NOTE Definition according to ISO 19148:2021, LRMType.
NOTE Since the definition in ISO 19148:2021, LRMType is stereotyped as a CodeList it is open for user defined extensions. In this Pset this is handled by adding the enumeration constant LRM_USERDEFINED and the additional property UserDefinedLRMType

properties.name: UserDefinedLRMType
properties.definition: Gives the user defined type of this Linear Referencing Method when property LRMType is LRM_USERDEFINED.

properties.name: LRMUnit
properties.definition: Specifies the units of measure used by this Linear Referencing Method for measures along the linear element being measured.NOTE Definition according to ISO 19148:2021.

properties.name: LRMConstraint
properties.definition: Allows for the specification of constraints imposed by this Linear Referencing Method. For example, a Reference Post Linear Referencing Method may specify that referents be of type reference marker.NOTE definition according to ISO 19148:2021

Pset_MaintenanceStrategy.name: Pset_MaintenanceStrategy
Pset_MaintenanceStrategy.definition: Property set for the association of a maintenance strategy to an element, asset of system.

properties.name: AssetCriticality
properties.definition: Rating of the asset's criticality to the operation of the facility

properties.name: AssetFrailty
properties.definition: Rating of the asset's frailty to breakage or deterioration

properties.name: AssetPriority
properties.definition: Combined criticality and frailty rating indicating the operational and maintenance priority of the asset

properties.name: MonitoringType
properties.definition: Monitoring strategy chosen for the asset

properties.name: AccidentResponse
properties.definition: Accident response chosen for the asset

Pset_MaintenanceTriggerCondition.name: Pset_MaintenanceTriggerCondition
Pset_MaintenanceTriggerCondition.definition: Trigger levels for an asset that has an inspection-based maintenance strategy

properties.name: ConditionTargetPerformance
properties.definition: Target condition of the asset

properties.name: ConditionMaintenanceLevel
properties.definition: Condition that will trigger maintenance

properties.name: ConditionReplacementLevel
properties.definition: Condition that will trigger a replacement process

properties.name: ConditionDisposalLevel
properties.definition: Condition that will trigger a disposal process

Pset_MaintenanceTriggerDuration.name: Pset_MaintenanceTriggerDuration
Pset_MaintenanceTriggerDuration.definition: Trigger levels for an asset that has an PPM based maintenance strategy.

properties.name: DurationTargetPerformance
properties.definition: Target time to failure of the asset

properties.name: DurationMaintenanceLevel
properties.definition: Duration interval at which maintenance is performed

properties.name: DurationReplacementLevel
properties.definition: Duration interval at which replacement is performed

properties.name: DurationDisposalLevel
properties.definition: Duration interval at which disposal is performed

Pset_MaintenanceTriggerPerformance.name: Pset_MaintenanceTriggerPerformance
Pset_MaintenanceTriggerPerformance.definition: Properties for performance based maintenance policies

properties.name: TargetPerformance
properties.definition: Target capacity or performance of the asset. Units of the performance value are specified through the propertyValue units attribute.

properties.name: PerformanceMaintenanceLevel
properties.definition: Performance level at which maintenance takes place

properties.name: ReplacementLevel
properties.definition: Performance level at which replacement takes place

properties.name: DisposalLevel
properties.definition: Performance level at which disposal takes place

Pset_ManufacturerOccurrence.name: Pset_ManufacturerOccurrence
Pset_ManufacturerOccurrence.definition:
Defines properties of individual instances of manufactured products that may be given by the manufacturer.
HISTORY: IFC 2x4: AssemblyPlace property added. This property does not need to be asserted if Pset_ManufacturerTypeInformation is allocated to the type and the AssemblyPlace property is asserted there.

properties.name: AcquisitionDate
properties.definition: The date that the manufactured item was purchased.

properties.name: BarCode
properties.definition: The identity of the bar code given to an occurrence of the product.

properties.name: SerialNumber
properties.definition: The manufacturer's serial number assigned to an occurrence of a product.

properties.name: BatchReference
properties.definition: The identity of the batch reference from which an occurrence of a product is taken.

properties.name: AssemblyPlace
properties.definition: Enumeration defining where the assembly is intended to take place, either in a factory, other offsite location or on the building site.

properties.name: ManufacturingDate
properties.definition: Date on which the element was manufactured.

Pset_ManufacturerTypeInformation.name: Pset_ManufacturerTypeInformation
Pset_ManufacturerTypeInformation.definition:
Defines characteristics of types (ranges) of manufactured products that may be given by the manufacturer. Note that the term 'manufactured' may also be used to refer to products that are supplied and identified by the supplier or that are assembled off site by a third party provider.
HISTORY: This property set replaces the entity IfcManufacturerInformation from previous IFC releases. IFC 2x4: AssemblyPlace property added.

properties.name: GlobalTradeItemNumber
properties.definition: The Global Trade Item Number (GTIN) is an identifier for trade items developed by GS1 (www.gs1.org).

properties.name: ArticleNumber
properties.definition: Article number or reference that is be applied to a configured product according to a standard scheme for article number definition as defined by the manufacturer. It is often used as the purchasing number.

properties.name: ModelReference
properties.definition: The model number or designator of the product model (or product line) as assigned by the manufacturer of the manufactured item.

properties.name: ModelLabel
properties.definition: The descriptive model name of the product model (or product line) as assigned by the manufacturer of the manufactured item.

properties.name: Manufacturer
properties.definition: The organization that manufactured and/or assembled the item.

properties.name: ProductionYear
properties.definition: The year of production of the manufactured item.

properties.name: AssemblyPlace
properties.definition: Enumeration defining where the assembly is intended to take place, either in a factory, other offsite location or on the building site.

properties.name: OperationalDocument
properties.definition: Manufacturer's operational document

properties.name: SafetyDocument
properties.definition: Manufacturer's safety document

properties.name: PerformanceCertificate
properties.definition: Manufacturer's performance certificate

Pset_MarineFacilityTransportation.name: Pset_MarineFacilityTransportation
Pset_MarineFacilityTransportation.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcMarineFacility which are catagorised as transportation facilities such as Ports, marinas etc.

properties.name: Berths
properties.definition: Number of standard berths within the facility

properties.name: BerthGrade
properties.definition: Berth grade

properties.name: BerthCargoWeight
properties.definition: Total cargo weight of berths within the facility

Pset_MarinePartChamberCommon.name: Pset_MarinePartChamberCommon
Pset_MarinePartChamberCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcMarinePart with the predefined type set to CHAMBER.

properties.name: EffectiveChamberSize
properties.definition: Volumetric measure defining the effective chamber size for operational and design activities.

properties.name: StructuralType
properties.definition: Structural type of the object

Pset_MarineVehicleCommon.name: Pset_MarineVehicleCommon
Pset_MarineVehicleCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcTransportElement and types of IfcTransportElementType with the predefined type set to VEHICLEMARINE.

properties.name: LengthBetweenPerpendiculars
properties.definition: Length of vessel from rudder shaft to crossing point of the bow and the loaded waterline.

properties.name: VesselDepth
properties.definition: Depth of the vessel from the main deck to the keel.

properties.name: VesselDraft
properties.definition: Depth of vessel from the waterline to the keel (LightShip, Ballasted, Maximum)

properties.name: AboveDeckProjectedWindEnd
properties.definition: End on projected windage area above the main deck

properties.name: AboveDeckProjectedWindSide
properties.definition: Side on projected windage area above the main deck

properties.name: Displacement
properties.definition: Weight of water displaced by the vessel

properties.name: CargoDeadWeight
properties.definition: Weight of (bulk) cargo carried

properties.name: LaneMeters
properties.definition: Length of lanes accommodating vehicles on roll-on, roll-off vessels

Pset_MarineVehicleDesignCriteria.name: Pset_MarineVehicleDesignCriteria
Pset_MarineVehicleDesignCriteria.definition: Properties common to the definition of design criteria of all occurrences of IfcTransportElement and types of IfcTransportElementType with the predefined type set to MARINEVEHICLE

properties.name: AllowableHullPressure
properties.definition: Allowable contact pressure between fender and hull

properties.name: SoftnessCoefficient
properties.definition: Vessel flexibility factor - proportion of impact energy absorbed by the hull.

Pset_MarkerGeneral.name: Pset_MarkerGeneral
Pset_MarkerGeneral.definition: Properties common to a signalling marker made as an assembly of elements. The property set can be used by the predefined type SIGNAL_ASSEMBLY of IfcElementAssembly.

properties.name: ApproachSpeed
properties.definition: The design speed of trains approaching the signal if different from the line speed.

properties.name: MarkerType
properties.definition: The type of marker (sign) e.g. stop signal, restriction signal, track circuit tuning zone sign or others specified in PEnum_MarkerType.

properties.name: NominalHeight
properties.definition:
The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

The nominal height of the furniture of this type. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: Symbol
properties.definition: Content which is shown on the sign, e.g. text, number, arrow or icon. The string can also be a pointer to a symbol catalog.

properties.name: NominalWidth
properties.definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: DashedLine
properties.definition: State if the line is dashed or continuous

properties.name: DashedLinePattern
properties.definition: Indicates the pattern for dashed line types e.g. '3+9'

properties.name: NominalWidth
properties.definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Pset_MaterialCombustion.name: Pset_MaterialCombustion
Pset_MaterialCombustion.definition: A set of extended material properties of products of combustion generated by elements typically used within the context of building services and flow distribution systems.

properties.name: SpecificHeatCapacity
properties.definition:
Defines the specific heat capacity of a material.

Specific heat of the products of combustion: heat energy absorbed per temperature unit.

properties.name: N20Content
properties.definition: Nitrous oxide (N2O) content of the products of combustion. This is measured in weight of N2O per unit weight and is therefore unitless.

properties.name: COContent
properties.definition: Carbon monoxide (CO) content of the products of combustion. This is measured in weight of CO per unit weight and is therefore unitless.

properties.name: CO2Content
properties.definition: Carbon dioxide (CO2) content of the products of combustion. This is measured in weight of CO2 per unit weight and is therefore unitless.

Pset_MaterialCommon.name: Pset_MaterialCommon
Pset_MaterialCommon.definition: A set of general material properties.

properties.name: MolecularWeight
properties.definition: Molecular weight of material (typically gas).

properties.name: Porosity
properties.definition: The void fraction of the total volume occupied by material (Vbr - Vnet)/Vbr.

properties.name: MassDensity
properties.definition: Material mass density.

Pset_MaterialConcrete.name: Pset_MaterialConcrete
Pset_MaterialConcrete.definition: A set of extended mechanical properties related to concrete materials.

properties.name: CompressiveStrength
properties.definition: The compressive strength of the object or material.

properties.name: MaxAggregateSize
properties.definition: The maximum aggregate size of the concrete.

properties.name: AdmixturesDescription
properties.definition: Description of the admixtures added to the concrete mix.

properties.name: Workability
properties.definition: Description of the workability of the fresh concrete defined according to local standards.

properties.name: WaterImpermeability
properties.definition: Description of the water impermeability denoting the water repelling properties.

properties.name: ProtectivePoreRatio
properties.definition: The protective pore ratio indicating the frost-resistance of the concrete.

Pset_MaterialEnergy.name: Pset_MaterialEnergy
Pset_MaterialEnergy.definition: A set of extended material properties for energy calculation purposes.

properties.name: ViscosityTemperatureDerivative
properties.definition: Viscosity temperature derivative.

properties.name: MoistureCapacityThermalGradient
properties.definition: Thermal gradient coefficient for moisture capacity. Based on water vapor density.

properties.name: ThermalConductivityTemperatureDerivative
properties.definition: Thermal conductivity temperature derivative.

properties.name: SpecificHeatTemperatureDerivative
properties.definition: Specific heat temperature derivative.

properties.name: VisibleRefractionIndex
properties.definition: Index of refraction (visible) defines the "bending" of the sola! r ray in the visible spectrum when it passes from one medium into another.

properties.name: SolarRefractionIndex
properties.definition: Index of refraction (solar) defines the "bending" of the solar ray when it passes from one medium into another.

properties.name: GasPressure
properties.definition: Fill pressure (e.g. for between-pane gas fills): the pressure exerted by a mass of gas confined in a constant volume.

Pset_MaterialFuel.name: Pset_MaterialFuel
Pset_MaterialFuel.definition: A set of extended material properties of fuel energy typically used within the context of building services and flow distribution systems.

properties.name: CombustionTemperature
properties.definition:
Combustion temperature.

Combustion temperature of the material when air is at 298 K and 100 kPa.

properties.name: CarbonContent
properties.definition: The carbon content in the fuel. This is measured in weight of carbon per unit weight of fuel and is therefore unitless.

properties.name: LowerHeatingValue
properties.definition: Lower Heating Value is defined as the amount of energy released (MJ/kg) when a fuel is burned completely, and H2O is in vapor form in the combustion products.

properties.name: HigherHeatingValue
properties.definition: Higher Heating Value is defined as the amount of energy released (MJ/kg) when a fuel is burned completely, and H2O is in liquid form in the combustion products.

Pset_MaterialHygroscopic.name: Pset_MaterialHygroscopic
Pset_MaterialHygroscopic.definition: A set of hygroscopic properties of materials.

properties.name: UpperVaporResistanceFactor
properties.definition: The vapor permeability relationship of air/material (typically value > 1), measured in high relative humidity (typically in 95/50 % RH).

properties.name: LowerVaporResistanceFactor
properties.definition: The vapor permeability relationship of air/material (typically value > 1), measured in low relative humidity (typically in 0/50 % RH).

properties.name: IsothermalMoistureCapacity
properties.definition: Based on water vapor density.

properties.name: VaporPermeability
properties.definition: The rate of water vapor transmission per unit area per unit of vapor pressure differential under test conditions.

properties.name: MoistureDiffusivity
properties.definition: Moisture diffusivity is a transport property that is frequently used in the hygrothermal analysis of building envelope components.

Pset_MaterialMechanical.name: Pset_MaterialMechanical
Pset_MaterialMechanical.definition: A set of mechanical material properties normally used for structural analysis purpose. It contains all properties which are independent of the actual material type.

properties.name: DynamicViscosity
properties.definition: A measure of the viscous resistance of the material.

properties.name: YoungModulus
properties.definition: A measure of the Young's modulus of elasticity of the material.

properties.name: ShearModulus
properties.definition: A measure of the shear modulus of elasticity of the material.

properties.name: PoissonRatio
properties.definition: A measure of the lateral deformations in the elastic range.

properties.name: ThermalExpansionCoefficient
properties.definition: Quantity characterizing the variation with thermodynamic temperature T of the distance l between two points of a body, under given conditions (IEC 113-04-27). The ratio is defined per Kelvin.

Pset_MaterialOptical.name: Pset_MaterialOptical
Pset_MaterialOptical.definition: A set of optical properties of materials.

properties.name: VisibleTransmittance
properties.definition: Transmittance at normal incidence (visible). Defines the fraction of the visible spectrum of solar radiation that passes through per unit area, perpendicular to the surface.

properties.name: SolarTransmittance
properties.definition: The ratio of incident solar radiation that directly passes through a system (also named e). Note the following equation Asol + Rsol + Tsol = 1

properties.name: ThermalIrTransmittance
properties.definition: Thermal IR transmittance at normal incidence. Defines the fraction of thermal energy that passes through per unit area, perpendicular to the surface.

properties.name: ThermalIrEmissivityBack
properties.definition: Thermal IR emissivity: back side. Defines the fraction of thermal energy emitted per unit area to "blackbody" at the same temperature, through the "back" side of the material.

properties.name: ThermalIrEmissivityFront
properties.definition: Thermal IR emissivity: front side. Defines the fraction of thermal energy emitted per unit area to "blackbody" at the same temperature, through the "front" side of the material.

properties.name: VisibleReflectanceBack
properties.definition: Reflectance at normal incidence (visible): back side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray in the visible spectrum that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "back" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics.

properties.name: VisibleReflectanceFront
properties.definition: Reflectance at normal incidence (visible): front side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray in the visible spectrum that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "front" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics.

properties.name: SolarReflectanceBack
properties.definition: Reflectance at normal incidence (solar): back side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "back" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics.

properties.name: SolarReflectanceFront
properties.definition: Reflectance at normal incidence (solar): front side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "front" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics.

Pset_MaterialSteel.name: Pset_MaterialSteel
Pset_MaterialSteel.definition: A set of extended mechanical properties related to steel (or other metallic and isotropic) materials.

properties.name: YieldStress
properties.definition: A measure of the yield stress (or characteristic 0.2 percent proof stress) of the material.

properties.name: UltimateStress
properties.definition: A measure of the ultimate stress of the material.

properties.name: UltimateStrain
properties.definition: A measure of the (engineering) strain at the state of ultimate stress of the material.

properties.name: HardeningModule
properties.definition: A measure of the hardening module of the material (slope of stress versus strain curve after yield range).

properties.name: ProportionalStress
properties.definition: A measure of the proportional stress of the material. It describes the stress before the first plastic deformation occurs and is commonly measured at a deformation of 0.01%.

properties.name: PlasticStrain
properties.definition: A measure of the permanent displacement, as in slip or twinning, which remains after the stress has been removed. Currently applied to a strain of 0.2% proportional stress of the material.

properties.name: Relaxations
properties.definition:
Measures of decrease in stress over long time intervals resulting from plastic flow. Different relaxation values for different initial stress levels for a material may be given. It describes the time dependent relative relaxation value for a given initial stress level at constant strain.
Relating values are the "RelaxationValue". Related values are the "InitialStress"

properties.name: StructuralGrade
properties.definition: Classification label to define mechanical properties according to structural grades defined in published standards; designated by numbers, letters, or a combination of both.

Pset_MaterialThermal.name: Pset_MaterialThermal
Pset_MaterialThermal.definition: A set of thermal material properties.

properties.name: SpecificHeatCapacity
properties.definition:
Defines the specific heat capacity of a material.

Defines the specific heat of the material: heat energy absorbed per temperature unit.

properties.name: BoilingPoint
properties.definition: The boiling point of the material (fluid).

properties.name: FreezingPoint
properties.definition: The freezing point of the material (fluid).

properties.name: ThermalConductivity
properties.definition:
The thermal conductivity of the object.

The rate at which thermal energy is transmitted through the material.

Pset_MaterialWater.name: Pset_MaterialWater
Pset_MaterialWater.definition: A set of extended material properties for of water typically used within the context of building services and flow distribution systems.

properties.name: IsPotable
properties.definition: If TRUE, then the water is considered potable.

properties.name: Hardness
properties.definition: Water hardness as positive, multivalent ion concentration in the water (usually concentrations of calcium and magnesium ions in terms of calcium carbonate).

properties.name: AlkalinityConcentration
properties.definition: Maximum alkalinity concentration (maximum sum of concentrations of each of the negative ions substances measured as CaCO3).

properties.name: AcidityConcentration
properties.definition: Maximum CaCO3 equivalent that would neutralize the acid.

properties.name: ImpuritiesContent
properties.definition: Fraction of impurities such as dust to the total amount of water. This is measured in weight of impurities per weight of water and is therefore unitless.

properties.name: DissolvedSolidsContent
properties.definition: Fraction of the dissolved solids to the total amount of water. This is measured in weight of dissolved solids per weight of water and is therefore unitless.

properties.name: PHLevel
properties.definition: Maximum water PH in a range from 0-14.

Pset_MaterialWood.name: Pset_MaterialWood
Pset_MaterialWood.definition: This is a collection of properties applicable to wood-based materials that specify kind and grade of material as well as moisture related parameters.

properties.name: Species
properties.definition: Wood species of a solid wood or laminated wood product.

properties.name: StrengthGrade
properties.definition: Grade with respect to mechanical strength and stiffness.

properties.name: AppearanceGrade
properties.definition: Grade with respect to visual quality.

properties.name: Layup
properties.definition: Configuration of the lamination.

properties.name: Layers
properties.definition: Number of layers.

properties.name: Plies
properties.definition: Number of plies.

properties.name: MoistureContent
properties.definition: Total weight of moisture relative to oven-dried weight of the wood.

properties.name: DimensionalChangeCoefficient
properties.definition: Weighted dimensional change coefficient, relative to 1% change in moisture content.

properties.name: ThicknessSwelling
properties.definition: Swelling ratio relative to board depth.

Pset_MaterialWoodBasedStructure.name: Pset_MaterialWoodBasedStructure
Pset_MaterialWoodBasedStructure.definition: Properties about Material of Wood Based Structure.

properties.name: ApplicableStructuralDesignMethod
properties.definition: Determines whether mechanical material properties are applicable to 'ASD' = allowable stress design (working stress design), 'LSD' = limit state design, or 'LRFD' = load and resistance factor design.

Pset_MechanicalBeamInPlane.name: Pset_MechanicalBeamInPlane
Pset_MechanicalBeamInPlane.definition: Properties about Mechanical Beam in Plane.

properties.name: YoungModulus
properties.definition: A measure of the Young's modulus of elasticity of the material.

properties.name: YoungModulusMin

Pset_PavementCommon.name: Pset_PavementCommon
Pset_PavementCommon.definition:
Describes the common properties and nominal dimensions of pavement.Property use clarification
The nominal thickness of the pavement remains constant with the value from NominalThickness, unless the property NominalThicknessEnd is provided. In which case NominalThickness is the value at the beginning of a transition (usually at the object placement location). e.g. a (road) transition segment where the pavement object's linear placement along an alignment denotes the beginning location and NominalThicknessEnd is the value at the end as indicated by the property NominalLength. In the case of local placements, it is user defined along which axis lengths and widths are measured.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.definition: The nominal thickness of the object after a transition from its original value. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: StructuralSlope
properties.definition: The nominal side slope (allowable steepness) of the pavement structure (not including side slope fill) as a positive ratio measure. The slope  information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters take precedence. Value is typically less than 1.0 (1:1) but may be greater than that for steeper slopes.

properties.name: StructuralSlopeType
properties.definition: User defined description on the type of slope used for the pavement structure (not including side slope fill) . Examples are "Even" or "Stepped".

properties.name: NominalWidth
properties.definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: NominalLength
properties.definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: NominalThickness
properties.definition: The nominal thickness of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: NominalDepth

properties.name: NominalWidth
properties.definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. properties.name: OperationType
properties.definition:
Type of operations. Also used to assign standard symbolic presentations according to national building standards.

For a permeable covering, it is the type of permeable covering operations. Also used to assign standard symbolic presentations according to national building standards.

properties.name: PanelPosition
properties.definition:
Position of the panel.

For a permeable covering, it is the position of the permeable covering panel within the overall window or door type.

properties.name: FrameDepth
properties.definition:
The length (or depth) of the frame.

For a permeable covering, it is the depth of panel frame (used to include the permeable covering), measured from front face to back face horizontally (i.e. perpendicular to the window or door elevation plane).

properties.name: FrameThickness
properties.definition:
The thickness of the frame.

For a permeable covering, it is the width of panel frame (used to include the permeable covering), measured from inside of panel (at permeable covering) to outside of panel (at lining), i.e. parallel to the window or door (elevation) plane.

Pset_Permit.name: Pset_Permit
Pset_Permit.definition:
A permit is a document that allows permission to gain access to an area or carry out work in a situation where security or other access restrictions apply.
HISTORY: IFC4 EndDate added. PermitType, PermitDuration, StartTime and EndTime are deleted.

properties.name: EscortRequirement
properties.definition: Indicates whether or not an escort is required to accompany persons carrying out a work order at or to/from the place of work (= TRUE) or not (= FALSE).NOTE - There are many instances where escorting is required, particularly in a facility that has a high security rating. Escorting may require that persons are escorted to and from the place of work. Alternatively, it may involve the escort remaining at the place of work at all times.

properties.name: StartDate
properties.definition: Date and time from which the permit becomes valid.

properties.name: EndDate
properties.definition: Date and time at which the permit ceases to be valid.

properties.name: SpecialRequirements
properties.definition: Any additional special requirements that need to be included in the permit to work.NOTE - Additional permit requirements may be imposed according to the nature of the facility at which the work is carried out. For instance, in clean areas, special clothing may be required whilst in corrective institutions, it may be necessary to check in and check out tools that will be used for work as a safety precaution.

For geometry editing applications, like CAD: this value should be write-only.

Pset_PrecastConcreteElementFabrication.definition: Production and manufacturing related properties common to different types of precast concrete elements. The Pset applies to manufactured pieces. It can be used by a number of subtypes of IfcBuiltElement. If the precast concrete ele

properties.name: ProductionLotId

properties.name: SerialNumber

properties.name: PieceMark
properties.definition: Defines a unique piece for production purposes. All pieces with the same piece mark value are identical and interchangeable. The piece mark may be composed of sub-parts that have specific locally defined meaning (e.g. B-1A may denote a beam, of generic type 1 and specific shape A).

properties.name: AsBuiltLocationNumber
properties.definition: Defines a unique location within a structure, the slot into which the piece was installed. Where pieces share the same piece mark, they can be interchanged. The value is only known after erection.

properties.name: ActualProductionDate
