The Pset can be used by a number of subtypes of IfcBuiltElement. If the precast concrete element is a sandwich wall panel each structural layer or shell represented by an IfcBuildingElementPart may be attached to a separate Pset of this type, if needed. Some of the properties apply only for specific types of precast concrete elements.

properties.name: TypeDesignation
properties.definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. 'Bull nose', 'Half batter', 'Dropper', 'Chamfer' etc

properties.name: CornerChamfer
properties.definition: The chamfer in the corners of the precast element. The chamfer is presumed to be equal in both directions.

properties.name: ManufacturingToleranceClass
properties.definition: Classification designation of the manufacturing tolerances according to local standards.

properties.name: FormStrippingStrength
properties.definition: The minimum required compressive strength of the concrete at form stripping time.

properties.name: LiftingStrength
properties.definition: The minimum required compressive strength of the concrete when the concrete element is lifted.

properties.name: ReleaseStrength
properties.definition: The minimum required compressive strength of the concrete when the tendon stress is released. This property applies to prestressed concrete elements only.

properties.name: MinimumAllowableSupportLength
properties.definition: The minimum allowable support length.

properties.name: InitialTension
properties.definition: The initial stress of the tendon. This property applies to prestressed concrete elements only.

properties.name: TendonRelaxation
properties.definition: The maximum allowable relaxation of the tendon (usually expressed as %/1000 h).This property applies to prestressed concrete elements only.

properties.name: TransportationStrength
properties.definition: The minimum required compressive strength of the concrete required for transportation.

properties.name: SupportDuringTransportDescription
properties.definition: Textual description of how the concrete element is supported during transportation.

properties.name: SupportDuringTransportDocReference
properties.definition: Reference to an external document defining how the concrete element is supported during transportation.

properties.name: HollowCorePlugging
properties.definition: A descriptive label for how the hollow core ends are treated: they may be left open, closed with a plug, or sealed with cast concrete. Values would be, for example: 'Unplugged', 'Plugged', 'SealedWithConcrete'. This property applies to  hollow core slabs only.

properties.name: CamberAtMidspan
properties.definition: The camber deflection, measured from the midpoint of a cambered face of a piece to the midpoint of the chord joining the ends of the same face, as shown in the figure below, divided by the original (nominal) straight length of the face of the piece.

properties.name: BatterAtStart
properties.definition: The angle, in radians, by which the formwork at the starting face of a piece is to be rotated from the vertical in order to compensate for the rotation of the face that will occur once the piece is stripped from its form, inducing camber due to eccentric prestressing.

properties.name: BatterAtEnd
properties.definition: The angle, in radians, by which the formwork at the ending face of a piece is to be rotated from the vertical in order to compensate for the rotation of the face that will occur once the piece is stripped from its form, inducing camber due to eccentric prestressing.

properties.name: Twisting
properties.definition: The angle, in radians, through which the end face of a precast piece is rotated with respect to its starting face, along its longitudinal axis, as a result of non-aligned supports. This measure is also termed the warping angle.

properties.name: Shortening
properties.definition: The ratio of the distance by which a precast piece is shortened after release from its form (due to compression induced by prestressing) to its original (nominal) length.

properties.name: PieceMark
properties.definition: Defines a unique piece for production purposes. All pieces with the same piece mark value are identical and interchangeable. The piece mark may be composed of sub-parts that have specific locally defined meaning (e.g. B-1A may denote a beam, of generic type 1 and specific shape A).

properties.name: DesignLocationNumber
properties.definition: Defines a unique location within a structure, the slot for which the piece was designed.

properties.name: NominalHeight
properties.definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: NominalLength
properties.definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: TypeDesignation
properties.definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. 'Bull nose', 'Half batter', 'Dropper', 'Chamfer' etc

properties.name: NominalWidth
properties.definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Pset_PrecastSlab.name: Pset_PrecastSlab
Pset_PrecastSlab.definition: Layout and component information defining how prestressed slab components are laid out in a precast slab assembly. The values are global defaults for the slab as a whole, but can be overridden by local placements of the individual com

properties.name: TypeDesignation
properties.definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. 'Bull nose', 'Half batter', 'Dropper', 'Chamfer' etc

properties.name: ToppingType
properties.definition: Defines if a topping is applied and what kind. Values are Full topping, Perimeter Wash, None

properties.name: EdgeDistanceToFirstAxis
properties.definition: The distance from the left (West) edge of the slab (in the direction of span of the components) to the axis of the first component.

properties.name: DistanceBetweenComponentAxes
properties.definition: The distance between the axes of the components, measured along the South edge of the slab.

properties.name: AngleToFirstAxis
properties.definition: The angle of rotation of the axis of the first component relative to the West edge of the slab.

properties.name: AngleBetweenComponentAxes
properties.definition: The angle between the axes of each pair of components.

properties.name: NominalThickness
properties.definition: The nominal thickness of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: NominalToppingThickness
properties.definition: The nominal thickness of the topping.

Pset_ProcessCapacity.name: Pset_ProcessCapacity
Pset_ProcessCapacity.definition: Property set for the application of process data to spatial elements and transport assets

properties.name: ProcessItem
properties.definition: The type of item (and its measurement method) being modelled within a process. This can be cargo, passengers or vehicles that pass through the system.

properties.name: ProcessCapacity
properties.definition: The number of units that can be processed in the time defined in ProcessPerformance

properties.name: ProcessPerformance
properties.definition: Minimum time to accept or dispatch the entire item capacity.

properties.name: DownstreamConnections
properties.definition: Names of downstream connected equipment and spaces, if not otherwise represented

properties.name: UpstreamConnections
properties.definition: Names of upstream connected equipment and spaces, if not otherwise represented

Pset_ProfileArbitraryDoubleT.name: Pset_ProfileArbitraryDoubleT
Pset_ProfileArbitraryDoubleT.definition: This is a collection of geometric properties of double-T section profiles of precast concrete elements, to be used in conjunction with IfcArbitraryClosedProfileDef when profile designation alone does not fulfill the information requirements.

properties.name: OverallWidth
properties.definition: Overall width of the profile.

properties.name: LeftFlangeWidth
properties.definition: Left flange width of the profile.

properties.name: RightFlangeWidth
properties.definition: Right flange width of the profile.

properties.name: OverallDepth
properties.definition: Overall depth of the profile.

properties.name: FlangeDepth
properties.definition: Flange depth of the profile.

properties.name: FlangeDraft
properties.definition: Flange draft of the profile.

properties.name: FlangeChamfer
properties.definition: Flange chamfer of the profile.

properties.name: FlangeBaseFillet
properties.definition: Flange base fillet of the profile.

properties.name: FlangeTopFillet
properties.definition: Flange top fillet of the profile.

properties.name: StemBaseWidth
properties.definition: Stem base width of the profile.

properties.name: StemTopWidth
properties.definition: Stem top width of the profile.

properties.name: StemBaseChamfer
properties.definition: Stem base chamfer of the profile.

properties.name: StemTopChamfer
properties.definition: Stem top chamfer of the profile.

properties.name: StemBaseFillet
properties.definition: Stem base fillet of the profile.

properties.name: StemTopFillet
properties.definition: Stem top fillet of the profile.

Pset_ProfileArbitraryHollowCore.name: Pset_ProfileArbitraryHollowCore
Pset_ProfileArbitraryHollowCore.definition: This is a collection of geometric properties of hollow core section profiles of precast concrete elements, to be used in conjunction with IfcArbitraryProfileDefWithVoids when profile designation alone does not fulfill the information requirements.In all cases, the cores are symmetrically distributed on either side of the plank center line, irrespective of whether the number of cores is odd or even. For planks with a center core with different geometry to that of the other cores, provide the property CenterCoreSpacing. When the number of cores is even, no Center Core properties shall be asserted.Key chamfers and draft chamfer are all 45 degree chamfers.The CoreTopRadius and CoreBaseRadius parameters can be derived and are therefore not listed in the property set. They are shown to define that the curves are arcs. The parameters for the center core are the same as above, but with the prefix "Center".

properties.name: OverallWidth
properties.definition: Overall width of the profile.

properties.name: OverallDepth
properties.definition: Overall depth of the profile.

properties.name: EdgeDraft
properties.definition: Edge draft of the profile.

properties.name: DraftBaseOffset
properties.definition: Draft base offset of the profile.

properties.name: DraftSideOffset
properties.definition: Draft side offset of the profile.

properties.name: BaseChamfer
properties.definition: Base chamfer of the profile.

properties.name: KeyDepth
properties.definition: Key depth of the profile.

properties.name: KeyHeight
properties.definition: Key height of the profile.

properties.name: KeyOffset
properties.definition: Key offset of the profile.

properties.name: BottomCover
properties.definition: Bottom cover of the profile.

properties.name: CoreSpacing
properties.definition: Core spacing of the profile.

properties.name: CoreBaseHeight
properties.definition: Core base height of the profile.

properties.name: CoreMiddleHeight
properties.definition: Core middle height of the profile.

properties.name: CoreTopHeight
properties.definition: Core top height of the profile.

properties.name: CoreBaseWidth
properties.definition: Core base width of the profile.

properties.name: CoreTopWidth
properties.definition: Core top width of the profile.

properties.name: CenterCoreSpacing
properties.definition: Center core spacing of the profile.

properties.name: CenterCoreBaseHeight
properties.definition: Center core base height of the profile.

properties.name: CenterCoreMiddleHeight
properties.definition: Center core middle height of the profile.

properties.name: CenterCoreTopHeight
properties.definition: Center core top height of the profile.

properties.name: CenterCoreBaseWidth
properties.definition: Center core base width of the profile.

properties.name: CenterCoreTopWidth
properties.definition: Center core top width of the profile.

properties.name: NumberOfCores
properties.definition: The number of cores.

Pset_ProfileMechanical.name: Pset_ProfileMechanical
Pset_ProfileMechanical.definition: This is a collection of mechanical properties that are applicable to virtually all profile classes. Most of these properties are especially used in structural analysis.

properties.name: MassPerLength
properties.definition: Mass per length, i.e. mass of a beam with a unit length of extrusion. For example measured in kg/m.

properties.name: CrossSectionArea
properties.definition: Total area of the cross section (or profile) of the object.

properties.name: Perimeter
properties.definition:
Perimeter of the object.

Perimeter of the profile for calculating the surface area. For example measured in mm.

properties.name: MinimumPlateThickness
properties.definition: This value may be needed for stress analysis and to handle buckling problems. It can also be derived from the given profile geometry or classification and therefore it is only an optional feature allowing for an explicit description. For example measured in mm.

properties.name: MaximumPlateThickness
properties.definition: This value may be needed for stress analysis and to handle buckling problems. It can also be derived from the given profile geometry or classification and therefore it is only an optional feature allowing for an explicit description. For example measured in mm.

properties.name: CentreOfGravityInX
properties.definition: Location of the profile's centre of gravity (geometric centroid), measured along xp.

properties.name: CentreOfGravityInY
properties.definition: Location of the profile's centre of gravity (geometric centroid), measured along yp.

properties.name: ShearCentreZ
properties.definition: Location of the profile's shear centre, measured along zs.

properties.name: ShearCentreY
properties.definition: Location of the profile's shear centre, measured along ys.

properties.name: MomentOfInertiaY
properties.definition: Moment of inertia about ys (second moment of area, about ys). For example measured in mm4.

properties.name: MomentOfInertiaZ
properties.definition: Moment of inertia about zs (second moment of area, about zs). For example measured in mm4

properties.name: MomentOfInertiaYZ
properties.definition: Moment of inertia about ys and zs (product moment of area). For example measured in mm4.

properties.name: TorsionalConstantX
properties.definition: Torsional constant about xs. For example measured in mm4.

properties.name: WarpingConstant
properties.definition: Warping constant of the profile for torsional action. For example measured in mm6.

properties.name: ShearDeformationAreaZ
properties.definition: Area of the profile for calculating the shear deformation due to a shear force parallel to zs. For example measured in mm. If given, the shear deformation area zs shall be non-negative.

properties.name: ShearDeformationAreaY
properties.definition: Area of the profile for calculating the shear deformation due to a shear force parallel to ys. For example measured in mm. If given, the shear deformation area ys shall be non-negative.

properties.name: MaximumSectionModulusY
properties.definition: Bending resistance about the ys axis at the point with maximum zs ordinate. For example measured in mm.

properties.name: MinimumSectionModulusY
properties.definition: Bending resistance about the ys axis at the point with minimum zs ordinate. For example measured in mm.

properties.name: MaximumSectionModulusZ
properties.definition: Bending resistance about the zs axis at the point with maximum ys ordinate. For example measured in mm.

properties.name: MinimumSectionModulusZ
properties.definition: Bending resistance about the zs axis at the point with minimum ys ordinate. For example measured in mm.

properties.name: TorsionalSectionModulus
properties.definition: Torsional resistance (about xs). For example measured in mm.

properties.name: ShearAreaZ
properties.definition: Area of the profile for calculating the shear stress due to shear force parallel to the section analysis axis zs. For example measured in mm. If given, the shear area zs shall be non-negative.

properties.name: ShearAreaY
properties.definition: Area of the profile for calculating the shear stress due to shear force parallel to the section analysis axis ys. For example measured in mm. If given, the shear area ys shall be non-negative.

properties.name: PlasticShapeFactorY
properties.definition: Ratio of plastic versus elastic bending moment capacity about the section analysis axis ys. A dimensionless value.

properties.name: PlasticShapeFactorZ
properties.definition: Ratio of plastic versus elastic bending moment capacity about the section analysis axis zs. A dimensionless value.

Pset_ProjectCommon.name: Pset_ProjectCommon
Pset_ProjectCommon.definition: Property set for the application of high level project information.

properties.name: ProjectType
properties.definition: Additional typing of a project

properties.name: ProjectInvestmentEstimate
properties.definition: Estimate of investment cost

properties.name: FundingSource
properties.definition: Investment funding source

properties.name: ROI
properties.definition: Return on Investment

properties.name: NetEarnedValue
properties.definition: Net earned value

properties.name: PaybackPeriod
properties.definition: Payback period of investment

Pset_ProjectOrderChangeOrder.name: Pset_ProjectOrderChangeOrder
Pset_ProjectOrderChangeOrder.definition: A change order is an instruction to make a change to a product or work being undertake. Note that the change order status is defined in the same way as a work order status since a change order implies a work requirement.

properties.name: ReasonForChange
properties.definition: A description of the problem for why a change is needed.

properties.name: BudgetSource
properties.definition: The budget source requested.

Pset_ProjectOrderMaintenanceWorkOrder.name: Pset_ProjectOrderMaintenanceWorkOrder
Pset_ProjectOrderMaintenanceWorkOrder.definition: A MaintenanceWorkOrder is a detailed description of maintenance work that is to be performed. Note that the Scheduled Frequency property of the maintenance work order is used when the order is required as an instance of a scheduled work order.

properties.name: ProductDescription
properties.definition: A textual description of the products that require the work.

properties.name: WorkTypeRequested
properties.definition: Work type requested in circumstances where there are categorizations of types of work task. It could be used to identify a remedial task, minor work task, electrical task etc.

properties.name: ContractualType
properties.definition: The contractual type of the work.

properties.name: IfNotAccomplished
properties.definition: Comments if the job is not accomplished.

properties.name: MaintenanceType
properties.definition:
Identifies the predefined types of maintenance that can be done from which the type that generates the maintenance work order may be set where:ConditionBased: generated as a result of the condition of an asset or artefact being less than a determined value.
Corrective: generated as a result of an immediate and urgent need for maintenance action.
PlannedCorrective: generated as a result of immediate corrective action being needed but with sufficient time available for the work order to be included in maintenance planning.
Scheduled: generated as a result of a fixed, periodic maintenance requirement.

properties.name: FaultPriorityType
properties.definition:
Identifies the predefined types of priority that can be assigned from which the type may be set where:High: action is required urgently.
Medium: action can occur within a reasonable period of time.
Low: action can occur when convenient.

properties.name: LocationPriorityType
properties.definition:
Identifies the predefined types of priority that can be assigned from which the type may be set where:High: action is required urgently.
Medium: action can occur within a reasonable period of time.
Low: action can occur when convenient.

properties.name: ScheduledFrequency
properties.definition: The period of time between expected instantiations of a work order that may have been predefined.

Pset_ProjectOrderMoveOrder.name: Pset_ProjectOrderMoveOrder
Pset_ProjectOrderMoveOrder.definition: Defines the requirements for move orders. Note that the move order status is defined in the same way as a work order status since a move order implies a work requirement.

properties.name: SpecialInstructions
properties.definition: Special instructions.

Pset_ProjectOrderPurchaseOrder.name: Pset_ProjectOrderPurchaseOrder
Pset_ProjectOrderPurchaseOrder.definition: Defines the requirements for purchase orders in a project.

properties.name: IsFOB
properties.definition: Indication of whether contents of the purchase order are delivered 'Free on Board' (= True) or not (= False). FOB is a shipping term which indicates that the supplier pays the shipping costs (and usually also the insurance costs) from the point of manufacture to a specified destination, at which point the buyer takes responsibility.

properties.name: ShipMethod
properties.definition: Method of shipping that will be used for goods or services.

Pset_ProjectOrderWorkOrder.name: Pset_ProjectOrderWorkOrder
Pset_ProjectOrderWorkOrder.definition: Defines the requirements for purchase orders in a project.

properties.name: ProductDescription
properties.definition: A textual description of the products that require the work.

properties.name: WorkTypeRequested
properties.definition: Work type requested in circumstances where there are categorizations of types of work task. It could be used to identify a remedial task, minor work task, electrical task etc.

properties.name: ContractualType
properties.definition: The contractual type of the work.

properties.name: IfNotAccomplished
properties.definition: Comments if the job is not accomplished.

Pset_PropertyAgreement.name: Pset_PropertyAgreement
Pset_PropertyAgreement.definition: A property agreement is an agreement that enables the occupation of a property for a period of time.The objective is to capture the information within an  agreement that is relevant to a facilities manager. Design and construction information associated with the property is not considered. A property agreement may be applied to an instance of IfcSpatialStructureElement including to compositions defined through the IfcSpatialStructureElement.Element.CompositionEnum.Note that the associated actors are captured by the IfcOccupant class.

properties.name: AgreementType
properties.definition: Identifies the predefined types of property agreement from which the type required may be set.

properties.name: TrackingIdentifier
properties.definition: The identifier assigned to the agreement for the purposes of tracking.

properties.name: AgreementVersion
properties.definition: The version number of the agreement that is identified.

properties.name: AgreementDate
properties.definition: The date on which the version of the agreement became applicable.

properties.name: PropertyName
properties.definition: Addressing details of the property as stated within the agreement.

properties.name: CommencementDate
properties.definition: Date on which the agreement commences.

properties.name: TerminationDate
properties.definition: Date on which the agreement terminates.

properties.name: Duration
properties.definition:
Duration.

The period of time for the lease.

properties.name: Options
properties.definition: A statement of the options available in the agreement.

properties.name: ConditionCommencement
properties.definition: Condition of property provided on commencement of the agreement e.g. cold shell, warm lit shell, broom clean, turn-key.

properties.name: Restrictions
properties.definition: Restrictions that may be placed by a  competent authority.

properties.name: ConditionTermination
properties.definition: Condition of property required on termination of the agreement e.g. cold shell, warm lit shell, broom clean, turn-key.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitI2TCurve.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitI2TCurve
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitI2TCurve.definition: A coherent set of attributes representing a curve for let-through energy of a protective device. Note - A protective device may be associated with different instances of this pSet providing information related to different  basic characteristics

properties.name: VoltageLevel
properties.definition: The voltage levels for which the data of the instance is valid. More than one value may be selected in the enumeration.

properties.name: NominalCurrent
properties.definition:
The nominal current that is designed to be measured.

A set of nominal currents in [A] for which the data of this instance is valid. At least one value shall be provided. Any value in the set shall not exceed the value of the
UltimateRatedCurrent associated with the same breaker unit.

properties.name: BreakerUnitCurve
properties.definition:
A curve that establishes the let through energy of a breaker unit when a particular prospective current is applied.  Note that the breaker unit curve is defined within a Cartesian coordinate system and this fact must be asserted within the property set:(1) Defining value: ProspectiveCurrent: A list of minimum 2 and maximum 16 numbers providing the currents in [A] for points in the current/I2t log/log coordinate space. The curve is drawn as a straight line between two consecutive points.
(2) Defined value: LetThroughEnergy: A list of minimum 2 and maximum 16 numbers providing the let-through energy, I2t, in [A2s] for points in the current/I2t log/log coordinate space. The curve is drawn as a straight line between two consecutive points.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitI2TFuseC.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitI2TFuseCurve
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitI2TFuseC.definition: A coherent set of attributes representing curves for melting- and breaking-energy of a fuse. Note - A fuse may be associated with different instances of this property set providing information related to different  basic characteristics.

properties.name: VoltageLevel
properties.definition: The voltage levels for which the data of the instance is valid. More than one value may be selected in the enumeration.

properties.name: BreakerUnitFuseMeltingCurve
properties.definition:
A curve that establishes the energy required to melt the fuse of a breaker unit when a particular prospective melting current is applied.  Note that the breaker unit fuse melting curve is defined within a Cartesian coordinate system and this fact must be:(1) Defining value: ProspectiveCurrentMelting :A list of minimum 2 and maximum 8 numbers providing the currents in [A] for points in the
current/melting_energy log/log coordinate space. The curve is drawn as a straight line between two consecutive points.
(2) Defined value: MeltingEnergy: A list of minimum 2 and maximum 8 numbers providing the energy whereby the fuse is starting to melt, I2t, in [A2s] for points in the current/melting_energy log/log coordinate space. The curve is drawn as a straight line between two consecutive points.

properties.name: BreakerUnitFuseBreakingingCurve
properties.definition:
A curve that establishes the let through breaking energy of a breaker unit when a particular prospective breaking current is applied.  Note that the breaker unit fuse breaking curve is defined within a Cartesian coordinate system and this fact must be:(1) Defining value: ProspectiveCurrentBreaking: A list of minimum 2 and maximum 8 numbers providing the currents in [A] for points in the
current/breaking energy log/log coordinate space. The curve is drawn as a straight line between two consecutive points.
(2) Defined value: LetThroughBreakingEnergy: A list of minimum 2 and maximum 8 numbers providing the breaking energy whereby the fuse has provided a break, I2t, in [A2s] for points in the current/breakting_energy log/log coordinate space. The curve is drawn as a straight line between two consecutive.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitIPICurve.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitIPICurve
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitIPICurve.definition: A coherent set of attributes representing curves for  let-through currents of a protective device. Note - A protective device may be associated with different instances of this pSet providing information related to different  basic characteristics.

properties.name: VoltageLevel
properties.definition: The voltage levels for which the data of the instance is valid. More than one value may be selected in the enumeration.

properties.name: NominalCurrent
properties.definition:
The nominal current that is designed to be measured.

A set of nominal currents in [A] for which the data of this instance is valid. At least one value shall be provided. Any value in the set shall not exceed the value of the
UltimateRatedCurrent associated with the same breaker unit.

properties.name: BreakerUnitIPICurve
properties.definition:
A curve that establishes the let through peak current of a breaker unit when a particular prospective current is applied.  Note that the breaker unit IPI curve is defined within a Cartesian coordinate system and this fact must be asserted within the property set:(1) Defining value: A list of minimum 2 and maximum 16 numbers providing the currents in [A] for points in the I/ log/log coordinate space. The curve is drawn as a straight line between two consecutive points.
(2) Defined value: A list of minimum 2 and maximum 16 numbers providing the let-through peak currents, , in [A] for points in the I/ log/log coordinate space. The curve is drawn as a straight line between two consecutive points.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitTypeMCB.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitTypeMCB
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitTypeMCB.definition: A coherent set of attributes representing the breaking capacities of an MCB. Note - A protective device may be associated with different instances of this property set providing information related to different  basic characteristics.

properties.name: PowerLoss
properties.definition:
The power loss in [W].

The power loss in [W] per pole of the MCB  when the nominal current is flowing through the MCB.

properties.name: VoltageLevel
properties.definition: The voltage levels for which the data of the instance is valid. More than one value may be selected in the enumeration.

properties.name: NominalCurrents
properties.definition:
A set of values providing information on available modules (chips) for setting the nominal current of the protective device.

A set of nominal currents in [A] for which the data of this instance is valid. At least one value shall be provided. Any value in the set shall not exceed the value of the
UltimateRatedCurrent associated with the same breaker unit.

properties.name: ICU60947
properties.definition: The ultimate breaking capacity in [A] for an object tested in accordance with the IEC 60947 series.

properties.name: ICS60947
properties.definition: The service breaking capacity in [A] for an object tested in accordance with the IEC 60947 series.

properties.name: ICN60898
properties.definition: The nominal breaking capacity in [A] for an MCB tested in accordance with the IEC 60898 series.

properties.name: ICS60898
properties.definition: The service breaking capacity in [A] for an MCB tested in accordance with the IEC 60898 series.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitTypeMoto.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitTypeMotorProtection
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceBreakerUnitTypeMoto.definition: A coherent set of attributes representing different capacities of a a motor protection device, defined in accordance with IEC 60947. Note - A protective device may be associated with different instances of this Pset.

properties.name: PerformanceClasses
properties.definition:
A set of designations of performance classes for the breaker unit for which the data of this instance is valid.

A set of designations of performance classes for the breaker unit for which the data of this instance is valid. A breaker unit being a motor protection device may be
constructed for different levels of breaking capacities. A maximum of 7 different
performance classes may be provided. Examples of performance classes that may be specified include B, C, N, S, H, L, V.

properties.name: VoltageLevel
properties.definition: The voltage levels for which the data of the instance is valid. More than one value may be selected in the enumeration.

properties.name: ICU60947
properties.definition: The ultimate breaking capacity in [A] for an object tested in accordance with the IEC 60947 series.

properties.name: ICS60947
properties.definition: The service breaking capacity in [A] for an object tested in accordance with the IEC 60947 series.

properties.name: ICW60947
properties.definition: The thermal withstand current in [A] for a circuit breaker or motor protection device tested in accordance with the IEC 60947 series. The value shall be related to 1 s.

properties.name: ICM60947
properties.definition: The making capacity in [A] for a circuit breaker or motor protection device tested in accordance with the IEC 60947 series.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceOccurrence.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceOccurrence
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceOccurrence.definition: Properties that are applied to an occurrence of a protective device.

properties.name: PoleUsage
properties.definition: Pole usage.

properties.name: LongTimeFunction
properties.definition:
Applying long time function
A flag indicating that the long time function (i.e. the thermal tripping) of the device is used. The value should be set to TRUE for all devices except those that allows the Long time function of the device not to be used.

properties.name: ShortTimeFunction
properties.definition: Applying short time function A flag indicating that the short time function of the device is used. The value should be set to FALSE for devices not having a short time function, or if the short time function is not selected to be used.

properties.name: ShortTimei2tFunction
properties.definition: Applying short time i2t function. A flag indicating that the I2t short time function of the device is used. The value should be set to TRUE only if the I2t function is explicitly selected for the device.

properties.name: GroundFaultFunction
properties.definition: Applying ground fault function. A flag indicating that the ground fault function of the device is used. The value should be set to FALSE for devices not having a ground fault function, or if the ground fault function is not selected to be used.

properties.name: GroundFaulti2tFunction
properties.definition: Applying ground fault i2t function. A flag indicating that the I2t ground fault function of the device is used. The value should be set to TRUE only if the I2t function is explicitly selected for the device.

properties.name: LongTimeCurrentSetValue
properties.definition: Long time current set value. The set value of the long time tripping current if adjustable.

properties.name: ShortTimeCurrentSetValue
properties.definition: Short time current set value. The set value of the long time tripping current if adjustable.

properties.name: InstantaneousCurrentSetValue
properties.definition: Instantaneous current set value. The set value of the instantaneous tripping current if adjustable.

properties.name: GroundFaultCurrentSetValue
properties.definition: Ground fault current set value. The set value of the ground tripping current if adjustable.

properties.name: LongTimeDelay
properties.definition: Long time delay. The set value of the long time time-delay if adjustable.

properties.name: ShortTimeTrippingTime
properties.definition: Short time tripping time. The set value of the short time tripping time if adjustable.

properties.name: InstantaneousTrippingTime
properties.definition: Instantaneous tripping time. The set value of the instantaneous tripping time if adjustable.

properties.name: GroundFaultTrippingTime
properties.definition: Ground fault tripping time. The set value of the ground fault tripping current if adjustable.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingCurve.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingCurve
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingCurve.definition: Tripping curves are applied to thermal, thermal magnetic or MCB_RCD tripping units (i.e. tripping units having type property sets for thermal, thermal magnetic or MCB_RCD tripping defined). They are not applied to electronic tripping units.

properties.name: TrippingCurveType
properties.definition: The type of tripping curve that is represented by the property set.

properties.name: TrippingCurve
properties.definition:
A curve that establishes the release time of a tripping unit when a particular prospective current is applied.  Note that the tripping curve is defined within a Cartesian coordinate system and this fact must be asserted within the property set:(1) Defining value is the Prospective Current which is a list of minimum 2 and maximum 16 numbers providing the currents in [x In] for points in the current/time log/log coordinate space. The curve is drawn as a straight line between two consecutive points.
(2) Defined value is a list of minimum 2 and maximum 16 numbers providing the release_time in [s] for points in the current/time log/log coordinate space. The curve is drawn as a straight line between two consecutive points. Note that a defined interpolation.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionGCu.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionGCurve
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionGCu.definition:
Tripping functions are applied to electronic tripping units (i.e. tripping units having type property sets for electronic tripping defined). They are not applied to thermal, thermal magnetic or RCD tripping units.
This property set represent the ground fault protection (G-curve) of an electronic protection device

properties.name: IsSelectable
properties.definition: Indication whether something can be switched off or not.

properties.name: NominalCurrentAdjusted
properties.definition: An indication if the tripping currents of the short time protection is related to the nominal current multiplied with the actual setting of the current adjustment, if any, of the long time protection part of the protective device, or not.

properties.name: ExternalAdjusted
properties.definition: An indication if the ground fault protection may be adjusted according to an external current coil or not.

properties.name: ReleaseCurrent
properties.definition: The release current in [x In] for the initial tripping of the S-function.

properties.name: ReleaseTime
properties.definition: The release time in [s] for the initial tripping of the relevant part. This time indicates that for current lower than the indicated release current, the tripping time will be longer than the indicated release time. The value is given as a mean value.

properties.name: CurrentTolerance1
properties.definition: The tolerance for the current of time/current-curve in [%].

properties.name: CurrentToleranceLimit1
properties.definition: The time limit in [s] limiting the application of CurrentTolerance1, if any. If the value is set to 0, the value of the CurrentTolerance1 is valid for the whole time/current-curve.

properties.name: CurrentTolerance2
properties.definition: The tolerance for the current of time/current-curve in [%] valid for times above CurrentTolereanceLimit1.

properties.name: IsCurrentTolerancePositiveOnly
properties.definition: Indication whether the value of  CurrentTolerance1 is provided as a positive tolereance only  or not. If not, the value is proved as a pluss/minus tolerance.

properties.name: TimeTolerance1
properties.definition: The tolerance for the time of time/current-curve in [%].

properties.name: TimeToleranceLimit1
properties.definition: The current limit in [x In] limiting the application of TimeTolerance1, if any. If the value is set to 0, the value of the TimeTolerance1 is valid for the whole time/current-curve.

properties.name: TimeTolerance2
properties.definition: The tolerance for the time of the time/current-curve in [%] valid for currents above TimeToleranceLimit1.

properties.name: IsTimeTolerancePositiveOnly
properties.definition: Indication whether the value of  TimeTolerance1 is provided as a positive tolereance only  or not. If not, the value is proved as a pluss/minus tolerance.

properties.name: ReleaseCurrentI2tStart
properties.definition:
The release current in [x In].

For the start point of the I2t tripping curve of the G-function, if any.

properties.name: ReleaseTimeI2tStart
properties.definition:
The release time in [s].

For the start point of the I2t tripping curve of the G-function, if any.

properties.name: ReleaseCurrentI2tEnd
properties.definition:
The release current in [x In].

For the end point of the I2t tripping curve of the G-function, if any. The value of ReleaseCurrentI2tEnd shall be larger than ReleaseCurrentI2tStart.

properties.name: ReleaseTimeI2tEnd
properties.definition:
The release time in [s].

For the end point of the I2 tripping curve of the G-function, if any. The value of ReleaseTimeI2tEnd shall be lower than ReleaseTimeI2tStart.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionICu.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionICurve
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionICu.definition:
Tripping functions are applied to electronic tripping units (i.e. tripping units having type property sets for electronic tripping defined). They are not applied to thermal, thermal magnetic or RCD tripping units.
This property set represent the instantaneous time protection (I-curve) of an electronic protection device.

properties.name: IsSelectable
properties.definition: Indication whether something can be switched off or not.

properties.name: NominalCurrentAdjusted
properties.definition: An indication if the tripping currents of the short time protection is related to the nominal current multiplied with the actual setting of the current adjustment, if any, of the long time protection part of the protective device, or not.

properties.name: ReleaseCurrent
properties.definition: The release current in [x In] for the initial tripping of the S-function.

properties.name: ReleaseTime
properties.definition: The release time in [s] for the initial tripping of the relevant part. This time indicates that for current lower than the indicated release current, the tripping time will be longer than the indicated release time. The value is given as a mean value.

properties.name: CurrentTolerance1
properties.definition: The tolerance for the current of time/current-curve in [%].

properties.name: CurrentToleranceLimit1
properties.definition: The time limit in [s] limiting the application of CurrentTolerance1, if any. If the value is set to 0, the value of the CurrentTolerance1 is valid for the whole time/current-curve.

properties.name: CurrentTolerance2
properties.definition: The tolerance for the current of time/current-curve in [%] valid for times above CurrentTolereanceLimit1.

properties.name: IsCurrentTolerancePositiveOnly
properties.definition: Indication whether the value of  CurrentTolerance1 is provided as a positive tolereance only  or not. If not, the value is proved as a pluss/minus tolerance.

properties.name: TimeTolerance1
properties.definition: The tolerance for the time of time/current-curve in [%].

properties.name: TimeToleranceLimit1
properties.definition: The current limit in [x In] limiting the application of TimeTolerance1, if any. If the value is set to 0, the value of the TimeTolerance1 is valid for the whole time/current-curve.

properties.name: TimeTolerance2
properties.definition: The tolerance for the time of the time/current-curve in [%] valid for currents above TimeToleranceLimit1.

properties.name: IsTimeTolerancePositiveOnly
properties.definition: Indication whether the value of  TimeTolerance1 is provided as a positive tolereance only  or not. If not, the value is proved as a pluss/minus tolerance.

properties.name: MaxAdjustmentX_ICS
properties.definition: Provides the maximum setting value for the available current adjustment in relation to the Ics breaking capacity of the protection device of which the actual tripping unit is a part of. The value is not asserted unless the instantaneous time protection is.

properties.name: IsOffWhenSFunctionOn
properties.definition: Indication whether the I-function is automatically switched off when the S-function is switched on.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionLCu.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionLCurve
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionLCu.definition:
Tripping functions are applied to electronic tripping units (i.e. tripping units having type property sets for electronic tripping defined). They are not applied to thermal, thermal magnetic or RCD tripping units.
This property set represent the long time protection (L-curve) of an electronic protection device

properties.name: IsSelectable
properties.definition: Indication whether something can be switched off or not.

properties.name: UpperCurrent1
properties.definition: The current in [x In], indicating that for currents larger than UpperCurrent1 the I2t part of the L-function will trip the current.

properties.name: UpperCurrent2
properties.definition: The current in [x In], indicating the upper current limit of the upper time/current curve of the I2t part of the L-function.

properties.name: UpperTime1
properties.definition: The time in [s], indicating that tripping times of the upper time/current curve lower than UpperTime1 is determined by the I2t part of the L-function.

properties.name: UpperTime2
properties.definition: The time in [s], indicating the tripping times of the upper time/current curve at the UpperCurrent2.

properties.name: LowerCurrent1
properties.definition: The current in [x In], indicating that for currents smaller than LowerCurrent1 the I2t part of the L-function will not trip the current,

properties.name: LowerCurrent2
properties.definition: The current in [x In], indicating the upper current limit of the lower time/current curve of the I2t part of the L-function.

properties.name: LowerTime1
properties.definition: The time in [s], indicating that tripping times of the lower time/current curve lower than LowerTime1 is determined by the I2t part of the L-function.

properties.name: LowerTime2
properties.definition: The time in [s], indicating the tripping times of the upper time/current curve at the LowerCurrent2.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionSCu.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionSCurve
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionSCu.definition:
Tripping functions are applied to electronic tripping units (i.e. tripping units having type property sets for electronic tripping defined). They are not applied to thermal, thermal magnetic or RCD tripping units.
This property set represent the short time protection (S-curve) of an electronic protection device.

properties.name: IsSelectable
properties.definition: Indication whether something can be switched off or not.

properties.name: NominalCurrentAdjusted
properties.definition: An indication if the tripping currents of the short time protection is related to the nominal current multiplied with the actual setting of the current adjustment, if any, of the long time protection part of the protective device, or not.

properties.name: ReleaseCurrent
properties.definition: The release current in [x In] for the initial tripping of the S-function.

properties.name: ReleaseTime
properties.definition: The release time in [s] for the initial tripping of the relevant part. This time indicates that for current lower than the indicated release current, the tripping time will be longer than the indicated release time. The value is given as a mean value.

properties.name: CurrentTolerance1
properties.definition: The tolerance for the current of time/current-curve in [%].

properties.name: CurrentToleranceLimit1
properties.definition: The time limit in [s] limiting the application of CurrentTolerance1, if any. If the value is set to 0, the value of the CurrentTolerance1 is valid for the whole time/current-curve.

properties.name: CurrentTolerance2
properties.definition: The tolerance for the current of time/current-curve in [%] valid for times above CurrentTolereanceLimit1.

properties.name: IsCurrentTolerancePositiveOnly
properties.definition: Indication whether the value of  CurrentTolerance1 is provided as a positive tolereance only  or not. If not, the value is proved as a pluss/minus tolerance.

properties.name: TimeTolerance1
properties.definition: The tolerance for the time of time/current-curve in [%].

properties.name: TimeToleranceLimit1
properties.definition: The current limit in [x In] limiting the application of TimeTolerance1, if any. If the value is set to 0, the value of the TimeTolerance1 is valid for the whole time/current-curve.

properties.name: TimeTolerance2
properties.definition: The tolerance for the time of the time/current-curve in [%] valid for currents above TimeToleranceLimit1.

properties.name: IsTimeTolerancePositiveOnly
properties.definition: Indication whether the value of  TimeTolerance1 is provided as a positive tolereance only  or not. If not, the value is proved as a pluss/minus tolerance.

properties.name: ReleaseCurrentI2tStart
properties.definition:
The release current in [x In].

For the start point of the I2t tripping curve of the S-function, if any.

properties.name: ReleaseTimeI2tStart
properties.definition:
The release time in [s].

For the start point of the I2t tripping curve of the S-function, if any

properties.name: ReleaseCurrentI2tEnd
properties.definition:
The release current in [x In].

For the end point of the I2t tripping curve of the S-function, if any. The value of ReleaseCurrentI2tEnd shall be larger than ReleaseCurrentI2tStart.

properties.name: ReleaseTimeI2tEnd
properties.definition:
The release time in [s].

For the end point of the I2 tripping curve of the S-function, if any. The value of ReleaseTimeI2tEnd shall be lower than ReleaseTimeI2tStart.

properties.name: IsOffWhenLfunctionOn
properties.definition: Indication whether the S-function is automatically switched off when the I-function is switched on.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitCurrent.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitCurrentAdjustment
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitCurrent.definition: A set of current adjustment values that may be applied to an electronic or thermal tripping unit type.

properties.name: AdjustmentValueType
properties.definition: The type of adjustment value that is applied through the property set. This determines the properties that should be asserted (see below).

properties.name: CurrentAdjustmentRange
properties.definition: Upper and lower current adjustment limits for an AdjustmentValueType = RANGE. Note that this property should not have a value for an  AdjustmentValueType = LIST.

properties.name: CurrentAdjustmentRangeStepValue
properties.definition: Step value of current adjustment for an AdjustmentValueType = RANGE. Note that this property should not have a value for an  AdjustmentValueType = LIST.

properties.name: CurrentAdjustmentValues
properties.definition: A list of current adjustment values that may be applied to a tripping unit for an AdjustmentValueType = LIST. A minimum of 1 and a maximum of 16 adjustment values may be specified. Note that this property should not have a value for an  AdjustmentValueType = RANGE.

properties.name: AdjustmentDesignation
properties.definition: The desgnation on the device for the adjustment.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTimeAdj.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTimeAdjustment
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTimeAdj.definition: A set of time adjustment values that may be applied to an electronic or thermal tripping unit type.

properties.name: AdjustmentValueType
properties.definition: The type of adjustment value that is applied through the property set. This determines the properties that should be asserted (see below).

properties.name: TimeAdjustmentRange
properties.definition: Upper and lower time adjustment limits for an AdjustmentValueType = RANGE. Note that this property should not have a value for an  AdjustmentValueType = LIST.

properties.name: TimeAdjustmentRangeStepValue
properties.definition: Step value of time adjustment for an AdjustmentValueType = RANGE. Note that this property should not have a value for an  AdjustmentValueType = LIST.

properties.name: TimeAdjustmentValues
properties.definition: A list of time adjustment values that may be applied to a tripping unit for an AdjustmentValueType = LIST. A minimum of 1 and a maximum of 16 adjustment values may be specified. Note that this property should not have a value for an  AdjustmentValueType = RANGE.

properties.name: AdjustmentDesignation
properties.definition: The desgnation on the device for the adjustment.

properties.name: CurrentForTimeDelay
properties.definition: The tripping current in [x In] at which the time delay is specified. A value for this property should only be asserted for time delay of L-function, and for I2t of the S and G function.

properties.name: I2TApplicability
properties.definition: The applicability of the time adjustment related to the tripping function.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeCom.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeCommon
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeCom.definition: Common information concerning tripping units that area associated with protective devices

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: Standard
properties.definition:
The designation of the standard applicable for the definition of the object used.

The designation of the standard applicable for the definition of the characteristics of the
tripping_unit.

properties.name: UseInDiscrimination
properties.definition:
An indication whether the time/current tripping information can be applied in a discrimination
analysis or not.

properties.name: AtexVerified
properties.definition: An indication whether the tripping_unit is verified to be applied in EX-environment or not.

properties.name: OldDevice
properties.definition: Indication whether the protection_ unit is out-dated or not. If not out-dated, the device is still for sale.

properties.name: LimitingTerminalSize
properties.definition: The maximum terminal size capacity of the device.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeEle.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeElectroMagnetic
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeEle.definition: Information on tripping units that are electrically or magnetically tripped.

properties.name: ElectroMagneticTrippingUnitType
properties.definition: A list of the available types of electric magnetic tripping unit  from which that required may be selected. These cover overload, none special, short circuit, motor protection and bi-metal tripping.

properties.name: I1
properties.definition: The (thermal) lower testing current limit in [x In], indicating that for currents lower than I1, the tripping time shall be longer than the associated tripping time, T2.

properties.name: I2
properties.definition: The (thermal) upper testing current limit in [x In], indicating that for currents larger than I2, the tripping time shall be shorter than the associated tripping time, T2.

properties.name: T2
properties.definition: The (thermal) testing time in [s] associated with the testing currents I1 and I2.

properties.name: DefinedTemperature
properties.definition: The ambient temperature at which the thermal current/time-curve associated with this protection device is defined.

properties.name: TemperatureFactor
properties.definition: The correction factor (typically measured as %/deg K) for adjusting the thermal current/time to an ambient temperature different from the value given by the defined temperature.

properties.name: I4
properties.definition: The lower electromagnetic testing current limit in [x In], indicating that for currents lower than I4, the tripping time shall be longer than the associated tripping time, T5, i.e. the device shall not trip instantaneous.

properties.name: I5
properties.definition: The upper electromagnetic testing current limit in [x In], indicating that for currents larger than I5, the tripping time shall be shorter than or equal to the associated tripping time, T5, i.e. the device shall trip instantaneous.

properties.name: T5
properties.definition: The electromagnetic testing time in [s] associated with the testing currents I4 and I5, i.e. electromagnetic tripping time

properties.name: CurveDesignation
properties.definition: The designation of the trippingcurve given by the manufacturer. For a MCB the designation should be in accordance with the designations given in IEC 60898.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeEle.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeElectronic
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeEle.definition: Information on tripping units that are electronically tripped.

properties.name: ElectronicTrippingUnitType
properties.definition: A list of the available types of electronic tripping unit  from which that required may be selected.

properties.name: NominalCurrents
properties.definition:
A set of values providing information on available modules (chips) for setting the nominal current of the protective device.

A set of values providing information on available modules (chips) for setting the nominal current of the protective device. If
the set is empty, no nominal current modules are available for the tripping unit.

properties.name: N_Protection
properties.definition: An indication whether the electronic tripping unit has separate protection for the N conductor, or not.

properties.name: N_Protection_50
properties.definition: An indication whether the electronic tripping unit is tripping if the current in the N conductor is more than 50% of that of the phase conductors. The property is only asserted if the property N_Protection is asserted.

properties.name: N_Protection_100
properties.definition: An indication whether the electronic tripping unit is tripping if the current in the N conductor is more than 100% of that of the phase conductors. The property is only asserted if the property N_Protection is asserted.

properties.name: N_Protection_Select
properties.definition: An indication whether the use of the N_Protection can be selected by the user or not. If both the properties N_Protection_50 and N_Protection_100 are asserted, the value of N_Protection_Select property is set to TRUE. The property is only asserted if the property N_Protection is asserted.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeRes.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeResidualCurrent
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeRes.definition: Information on tripping units that are activated by residual current.

properties.name: TrippingUnitReleaseCurrent
properties.definition: The value of tripping or residual current for which the device has the possibility to be equipped. The values are given in mA.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeThe.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeThermal
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeThe.definition: Information on tripping units that are thermally tripped.

properties.name: ThermalTrippingUnitType
properties.definition: A list of the available types of thermal tripping unit  from which that required may be selected.

properties.name: I1
properties.definition: The (thermal) lower testing current limit in [x In], indicating that for currents lower than I1, the tripping time shall be longer than the associated tripping time, T2.

properties.name: I2
properties.definition: The (thermal) upper testing current limit in [x In], indicating that for currents larger than I2, the tripping time shall be shorter than the associated tripping time, T2.

properties.name: T2
properties.definition: The (thermal) testing time in [s] associated with the testing currents I1 and I2.

properties.name: DefinedTemperature
properties.definition: The ambient temperature at which the thermal current/time-curve associated with this protection device is defined.

properties.name: TemperatureFactor
properties.definition: The correction factor (typically measured as %/deg K) for adjusting the thermal current/time to an ambient temperature different from the value given by the defined temperature.

properties.name: CurveDesignation
properties.definition: The designation of the trippingcurve given by the manufacturer. For a MCB the designation should be in accordance with the designations given in IEC 60898.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeAntiArcingDevic.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeAntiArcingDevice
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeAntiArcingDevic.definition: Anti arcing device properties used in energy domain. The property set can be used by the predefined type ANTI_ARCING_DEVICE of IfcProtectiveDevice.

properties.name: RatedVoltage
properties.definition: The range of allowed voltage that a device is certified to handle. The upper bound of this value is the maximum.

properties.name: GroundingType
properties.definition: The type of grounding connection.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeCircuitBreaker.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeCircuitBreaker
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeCircuitBreaker.definition: A coherent set of attributes representing different capacities of a circuit breaker or of a motor protection device, defined in accordance with IEC 60947. Note - A protective device may be associated with different instances of this property set providing information related to different basic characteristics.

properties.name: PerformanceClasses
properties.definition:
A set of designations of performance classes for the breaker unit for which the data of this instance is valid.

A set of designations of performance classes for the breaker unit for which the data of this instance is valid. A breaker unit being a circuit breaker may be
constructed for different levels of breaking capacities. A maximum of 7 different
performance classes may be provided. Examples of performance classes that may be specified include B, C, N, S, H, L, V.

properties.name: VoltageLevel
properties.definition: The voltage levels for which the data of the instance is valid. More than one value may be selected in the enumeration.

properties.name: ICU60947
properties.definition: The ultimate breaking capacity in [A] for an object tested in accordance with the IEC 60947 series.

properties.name: ICS60947
properties.definition: The service breaking capacity in [A] for an object tested in accordance with the IEC 60947 series.

properties.name: ICW60947
properties.definition: The thermal withstand current in [A] for a circuit breaker or motor protection device tested in accordance with the IEC 60947 series. The value shall be related to 1 s.

properties.name: ICM60947
properties.definition: The making capacity in [A] for a circuit breaker or motor protection device tested in accordance with the IEC 60947 series.

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeCommon.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeCommon
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeCommon.definition: Properties that are applied to a definition of a protective device.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeEarthLeakageCir.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeEarthLeakageCircuitBreaker
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeEarthLeakageCir.definition: An earth failure device acts to protect people and equipment from the effects of current leakage.

properties.name: EarthFailureDeviceType
properties.definition:
A list of the available types of circuit breaker from which that required may be selected where:Standard: Device that operates without a time delay.
TimeDelayed: Device that operates after a time delay.

properties.name: Sensitivity
properties.definition:
Sensitivity.

The rated rms value of the vector sum of the instantaneous currents flowing in the main circuits of the device which causes the device to operate under specified conditions. (IEC 61008-1).

Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeFuseDisconnecto.name: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeFuseDisconnector
Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTypeFuseDisconnecto.definition: A coherent set of attributes representing the breaking capacity of a fuse, defined in accordance with IEC 60269. Note - A protective device may be associated with different instances of this pSet providing information related to different  basic characteristics.

properties.name: FuseDisconnectorType
properties.definition:
A list of the available types of fuse disconnector from which that required may be selected where:EngineProtectionDevice: A fuse whose characteristic is specifically designed for the protection of a motor or generator.
FuseSwitchDisconnector: A switch disconnector in which a fuse link or a fuse carrier with fuse link forms the moving contact,
HRC: A standard fuse (High Rupturing Capacity)
OverloadProtectionDevice: A device that disconnects the supply when the operating conditions in an electrically undamaged circuit causes an overcurrent,
SemiconductorFuse: A fuse whose characteristic is specifically designed for the protection of sem-conductor devices.
SwitchDisconnectorFuse: A switch disconnector in which one or more poles have a fuse in series in a composite unit.

properties.name: VoltageLevel
properties.definition: The voltage levels for which the data of the instance is valid. More than one value may be selected in the enumeration.

properties.name: IC60269
properties.definition: The breaking capacity in [A] for fuses in accordance with the IEC 60269 series.

properties.name: PowerLoss
properties.definition:
The power loss in [W].

The power loss in [W] of the fuse when the nominal current is flowing through the fuse.

properties.name: NumberOfPhases
properties.definition: Number of phases that the equipment operates on.

properties.name: ReferenceEnvironmentTemperature
