Pset_Risk.name: Pset_Risk
Pset_Risk.definition: An indication of exposure to mischance, peril, menace, hazard or loss. Documentation of a potential hazard, likilihood and consequence aligned with AS/NZS 4360 and BS PAS 1192-6:2017, which can be assigned to or associated with a product, activity and/or location. Alternatively it may be assigned to an ISO 3864 annotation symbol.HISTORY Extended in IFC2x3, Revised IFC4x3There are various types of risk that may be encountered and there may be several instances of Pset_Risk associated to an instance or type.

properties.name: RiskName
properties.definition: A locally unique identifier for the risk entry that can be used to track the development and mitigation of the risk throughout the project life cycle

properties.name: RiskType
properties.definition: Identifies the predefined types of risk from which the type required may be set.

properties.name: NatureOfRisk
properties.definition: A description of the generic nature of the context or hazard that might be encountered.

properties.name: RiskAssessmentMethodology
properties.definition: An indication or link to the chosen risk assessment methodology, for example PAS1192-6 or a chosen ISO13100 annex.

properties.name: UnmitigatedRiskLikelihood
properties.definition: Identifies the likelihood of the hazard prior to any specific mitigation.

properties.name: UnmitigatedRiskConsequence
properties.definition: Identifies the consequence of the hazard prior to any specific mitigation.

properties.name: UnmitigatedRiskSignificance
properties.definition: Identifies the significance of the risk given the likelihood and consequence prior to any specific mitigation.

properties.name: MitigationPlanned
properties.definition: The planned (agreed and irrevocable) mitigation of the likelhood and consequences of the hazard.

properties.name: MitigatedRiskLikelihood
properties.definition: Identifies the likelihood of the hazard given the planned mitigation.

properties.name: MitigatedRiskConsequence
properties.definition: Identifies the consequence of the hazard given the planned mitigation.

properties.name: MitigatedRiskSignificance
properties.definition: Identifies the significance of the risk given the mitigation of likelihood and consequence.

properties.name: MitigationProposed
properties.definition: Any proposed, but not yet agreed and irrevocable, mitigation of the likelhood and consequences of the hazard.

properties.name: AssociatedProduct
properties.definition: An indication or link to any associated product or material that may trigger the hazard. If used directly on an annotation or semantic object. for an alternative see group use encoding template

properties.name: AssociatedActivity
properties.definition: An indication or link to any associated activity or process that may trigger the hazard. If used directly on an annotation or semantic object. for an alternative see group use encoding template

properties.name: AssociatedLocation
properties.definition: An indication or link to any associated location or space that may trigger the hazard. If used directly on an annotation or semantic object. for an alternative see group use encoding template

Pset_RoadDesignCriteriaCommon.name: Pset_RoadDesignCriteriaCommon
Pset_RoadDesignCriteriaCommon.definition: Road design criteria that may be attached to road parts.

properties.name: Crossfall
properties.definition: Specifies the nominal crossfall as a ratio measure (slope) at the location of the event.

properties.name: DesignSpeed
properties.definition:
Speed selected in designing a new road or in modernizing, strengthening or rehabilitating an existing road section, to determine the various geometric design features of the carriageway that allow a car to travel safely at that speed, under normal road surface and weather conditions.NOTE  Definition according to PIARC.
NOTE  The design speed is not constant, but may vary depending on the conditions of relief (plain, hill, mountain).

properties.name: DesignTrafficVolume
properties.definition: The traffic volume used for planning and design purposes specified as the number of vehicles per day . Typically given as AADT - Average Annual Daily Traffic

properties.name: DesignVehicleClass
properties.definition: A vehicle designator with content according to local standards.

properties.name: LaneWidth
properties.definition: Standard nominal width of one trough lane.

properties.name: NumberOfThroughLanes
properties.definition: The total number of through lanes on the segment. This excludes auxiliary lanes, parking and turning lanes, acceleration/deceleration lanes, toll collection lanes, shoulders etc.

properties.name: RoadDesignClass
properties.definition: A road design class designator with content according to local standards.

Pset_RoadGuardElement.name: Pset_RoadGuardElement
Pset_RoadGuardElement.definition: Properties assigned to IfcWall/PARAPET or IfcRailing/GUARDRAIL when assigned as road guard elements.

properties.name: IsMoveable
properties.definition: True if element is moveable.

properties.name: IsTerminal
properties.definition: True if element is a terminal. See class Terminal.

properties.name: IsTransition
properties.definition: True if element is a transition. See class Transition.

properties.name: TerminalType
properties.definition: Specifies the kind of terminal if IsTerminal is true.

properties.name: ApplicationMethod
properties.definition: State the application method used... e.g. spray, extruded

properties.name: DiagramNumber
properties.definition: A designator with content according to local standards, e.g. M25.

properties.name: MaterialColour
properties.definition: Actual colour on the road marking material

properties.name: MaterialThickness
properties.definition: Nominal thickness of the applied material

properties.name: MaterialType
properties.definition: Material type used... e.g. paint, tape, thermoplastic, stone

properties.name: Structure
properties.definition: State if marking is Structured or not, and what type... e.g. Kamflex, Longflex, Dropflex

properties.name: Text
properties.definition: Text content

properties.name: TypeDesignation
properties.definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. 'Bull nose', 'Half batter', 'Dropper', 'Chamfer' etc

Pset_RoofCommon.name: Pset_RoofCommon
Pset_RoofCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcRoof. Note: Properties for ProjectedArea and TotalArea added in IFC 2x3

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: AcousticRating
properties.definition:
Acoustic rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code. It indicates the sound transmission resistance of this object by an index ratio (instead of providing full sound absorption values).

properties.name: IsExternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

properties.name: ThermalTransmittance
properties.definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of an element, within the direction of the thermal flow (including all materials).

properties.name: FireRating
properties.definition: Fire rating for this object. It is given according to the national fire safety classification.

properties.name: LoadBearing
properties.definition: Indicates whether the object is intended to carry loads (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeBath.name: Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeBath
Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeBath.definition: Sanitary appliance for immersion of the human body or parts of it (BS6100). HISTORY: In IFC4, Material and MaterialThickness properties removed. Use materials capabilities from IfcMaterialResource schema. Datatype of color changed to IfcLabel (still a string value)

properties.name: BathType
properties.definition: The property enumeration defines the types of bath that may be specified within the property set.

properties.name: DrainSize
properties.definition: The size of the drain outlet connection from the object.

properties.name: HasGrabHandles
properties.definition: Indicates whether the bath is fitted with handles that provide assistance to a bather in entering or leaving the bath.

Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeBidet.name: Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeBidet
Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeBidet.definition: Waste water appliance for washing the excretory organs while sitting astride the bowl (BS6100). HISTORY: In IFC4, Material property removed. Use materials capabilities from IfcMaterialResource schema. Datatype of color changed to IfcLabel (still a string value). BidetMounting changed to Mounting.

properties.name: Mounting
properties.definition:
The property enumeration Pset_SanitaryMountingEnum defines the forms of mounting or fixing of the sanitary terminal that may be specified within property sets used to define sanitary terminals (WCs, basins, sinks, etc.) where:-BackToWall:     A pedestal mounted sanitary terminal that fits flush to the wall at the rear to cover its service connections
Pedestal:   A floor mounted sanitary terminal that has an integral base
CounterTop:     A sanitary terminal that is installed into a horizontal surface that is installed into a horizontal surface. Note: When applied to a wash hand basin, the term more normally used is vanity. See also Wash Hand Basin Type specification.
WallHung:   A sanitary terminal cantilevered clear of the floor.Note that BackToWall, Pedestal and WallHung are allowable values for a bidet.

properties.name: SpilloverLevel
properties.definition: The level at which water spills out of the object.

properties.name: DrainSize
properties.definition: The size of the drain outlet connection from the object.

Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeCistern.name: Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeCistern
Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeCistern.definition: A water storage unit attached to a sanitary terminal that is fitted with a device, operated automatically or by the user, that discharges water to cleanse a water closet (toilet) pan, urinal or slop hopper. (BS6100 330 5008)

properties.name: CisternHeight
properties.definition: Enumeration that identifies the height of the cistern or, if set to 'None' if the urinal has no cistern and is flushed using mains or high pressure water through a flushing valve.

properties.name: CisternCapacity
properties.definition: Volumetric capacity of the cistern

properties.name: IsSingleFlush
properties.definition: Indicates whether the cistern is single flush = TRUE (i.e. the same amount of water is used for each and every flush) or dual flush = FALSE (i.e. the amount of water used for a flush may be selected by the user to be high or low depending on the waste material to be removed).

properties.name: FlushType
properties.definition:
The property enumeration Pset_FlushTypeEnum defines the types of flushing mechanism that may be specified for cisterns and sanitary terminals where:-Lever:  Flushing is achieved by twisting a lever that causes a predetermined flow of water to be passed from a cistern to the sanitary terminal.
Pull:   Flushing is achieved by pulling a handle or knob vertically upwards that causes a predetermined flow of water to be passed from a cistern to the sanitary terminal.
Push:   Flushing is achieved by pushing a button or plate that causes a predetermined flow of water to be passed from a cistern to the sanitary terminal.
Sensor: Flush is activated through an automatic sensing mechanism.

properties.name: FlushRate
properties.definition: The minimum and maximum volume of water used at each flush. Where a single flush is used, the value of upper bound and lower bound should be equal. For a dual flush toilet, the lower bound should be used for the lesser flush rate and the upper bound for the greater flush rate. Where flush is achieved using mains pressure water through a flush valve, the value of upper and lower bound should be equal and should be the same as the flush rate property of the flush valve (see relevant valve property set). Alternatively, in this case, do not assert the flush rate property; refer to the flush rate of the flush valve.

properties.name: IsAutomaticFlush
properties.definition: Boolean value that determines if the cistern is flushed automatically either after each use or periodically (TRUE) or whether manual flushing is required (FALSE).

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: NominalLength
properties.definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: NominalWidth
properties.definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: NominalDepth
properties.definition: Nominal Depth of the object

properties.name: Colour
properties.definition: Colour of this object.

Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeSanitaryFountai.name: Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeSanitaryFountain
Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeSanitaryFountai.definition: Asanitary terminal that provides a low pressure jet of water for a specific purpose (IAI). HISTORY: In IFC4, Material property removed. Use materials capabilities from IfcMaterialResource schema. Datatype of color changed to IfcLabel (still a string value).

properties.name: FountainType
properties.definition:
Selection of the type of fountain from the enumerated list of types where:-DrinkingWater:  Sanitary appliance that provides a low pressure jet of drinking water.
Eyewash:    Waste water appliance, usually installed in work places where there is a risk of injury to eyes by solid particles or dangerous liquids, with which the user can wash the eyes without touching them.

properties.name: Mounting
properties.definition:
The property enumeration Pset_SanitaryMountingEnum defines the forms of mounting or fixing of the sanitary terminal that may be specified within property sets used to define sanitary terminals (WCs, basins, sinks, etc.) where:-BackToWall:     A pedestal mounted sanitary terminal that fits flush to the wall at the rear to cover its service connections
Pedestal:   A floor mounted sanitary terminal that has an integral base
CounterTop:     A sanitary terminal that is installed into a horizontal surface that is installed into a horizontal surface. Note: When applied to a wash hand basin, the term more normally used is vanity. See also Wash Hand Basin Type specification.
WallHung:   A sanitary terminal cantilevered clear of the floor.Note that BackToWall, Pedestal and WallHung are allowable values for a bidet.

properties.name: DrainSize
properties.definition: The size of the drain outlet connection from the object.

Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeShower.name: Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeShower
Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeShower.definition: Installation or waste water appliance that emits a spray of water to wash the human body (BS6100). HISTORY: In IFC4, Material and MaterialThickness properties removed. Use materials capabilities from IfcMaterialResource schema. Datatype of color changed to IfcLabel (still a string value)

properties.name: ShowerType
properties.definition:
Selection of the type of shower from the enumerated list of types where:-Drench:     Shower that rapidly gives a thorough soaking in an emergency.
Individual:     Shower unit that is typically enclosed and is for the use of one person at a time.
Tunnel:     Shower that has a succession of shower heads or spreaders that operate simultaneously along its length.

properties.name: HasTray
properties.definition: Indicates whether the shower has a separate receptacle that catches the water in a shower and directs it to a waste outlet.

properties.name: ShowerHeadDescription
properties.definition: A description of the shower head(s) that emit the spray of water.

properties.name: DrainSize
properties.definition: The size of the drain outlet connection from the object.

Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeSink.name: Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeSink
Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeSink.definition: Waste water appliance for receiving, retaining or disposing of domestic, culinary, laboratory or industrial process liquids. HISTORY: In IFC4, Material property removed. Use materials capabilities from IfcMaterialResource schema. Datatype of color changed to IfcLabel (still a string value). SinkMounting changed to Mounting.

properties.name: SinkType
properties.definition:
Selection of the type of sink from the enumerated list of types where:-Belfast:    Deep sink that has a plain edge and a weir overflow
.
Bucket:     Sink at low level, with protected front edge, that facilitates filling and emptying buckets, usually with a hinged grid on which to stand them.
Cleaners:    Sink, usually fixed at normal height (900mm), with protected front edge.
Combination_Left:    Sink with integral drainer on left hand side
.
Combination_Right: Sink with integral drainer on right hand side
.
Combination_Double:     Sink with integral drainer on both sides
.
Drip: Small sink that catches drips or flow from a faucet
.
Laboratory: Sink, of acid resisting material, with a top edge shaped to facilitate fixing to the underside of a desktop
.
London: Deep sink that has a plain edge and no overflow
.
Plaster: Sink with sediment receiver to prevent waste plaster passing into drains
.
Pot: Large metal sink, with a standing waste, for washing cooking utensils
.
Rinsing: Metal sink in which water can be heated and culinary utensils and tableware immersed at high temperature that destroys most harmful bacteria and allows subsequent self drying.
.
Shelf: Ceramic sink with an integral back shelf through which water fittings are mounted
.
VegetablePreparation:   Large metal sink, with a standing waste, for washing and preparing vegetables
.

properties.name: Mounting
properties.definition:
The property enumeration Pset_SanitaryMountingEnum defines the forms of mounting or fixing of the sanitary terminal that may be specified within property sets used to define sanitary terminals (WCs, basins, sinks, etc.) where:-BackToWall:     A pedestal mounted sanitary terminal that fits flush to the wall at the rear to cover its service connections
Pedestal:   A floor mounted sanitary terminal that has an integral base
CounterTop:     A sanitary terminal that is installed into a horizontal surface that is installed into a horizontal surface. Note: When applied to a wash hand basin, the term more normally used is vanity. See also Wash Hand Basin Type specification.
WallHung:   A sanitary terminal cantilevered clear of the floor.Note that BackToWall, Pedestal and WallHung are allowable values for a bidet.

properties.name: Colour
properties.definition: Colour of this object.

properties.name: DrainSize
properties.definition: The size of the drain outlet connection from the object.

properties.name: MountingOffset
properties.definition: For counter top mounted basins the vertical offset between the top of the sink and the counter top.

Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeToiletPan.name: Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeToiletPan
Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeToiletPan.definition: Soil appliance for the disposal of excrement. HISTORY: In IFC4, Material property removed. Use materials capabilities from IfcMaterialResource schema. Prefix for color property removed. Datatype of color changed to IfcLabel (still a string value).

properties.name: ToiletType
properties.definition:
Enumeration that defines the types of toilet (water closet) arrangements that may be specified where:-BedPanWasher: Enclosed soil appliance in which bedpans and urinal bottles are emptied and cleansed.
Chemical: Portable receptacle or soil appliance that receives and retains excrement in either an integral or a separate container, in which it is chemically treated and from which it has to be emptied periodically.
CloseCoupled:   Toilet suite in which a flushing cistern is connected directly to the water closet pan.
LooseCoupled:   Toilet arrangement in which a flushing cistern is connected to the water closet pan through a flushing pipe.
SlopHopper:     Hopper shaped soil appliance with a flushing rim and outlet similar to those of a toilet pan, into which human excrement is emptied for disposal.

properties.name: ToiletPanType
properties.definition:
The property enumeration Pset_ToiletPanTypeEnum defines the types of toilet pan that may be specified within the property set Pset_Toilet:-Siphonic:   Toilet pan in which excrement is removed by siphonage induced by the flushing water.
Squat:  Toilet pan with an elongated bowl installed with its top edge at or near floor level, so that the user has to squat.
WashDown:   Toilet pan in which excrement is removed by the momentum of the flushing water.
WashOut:    A washdown toilet pan in which excrement falls first into a shallow water filled bowl.

properties.name: PanMounting
properties.definition:
The property enumeration Pset_SanitaryMountingEnum defines the forms of mounting or fixing of the sanitary terminal that may be specified within property sets used to define sanitary terminals (WCs, basins, sinks, etc.) where:-BackToWall:     A pedestal mounted sanitary terminal that fits flush to the wall at the rear to cover its service connections.
Pedestal:   A floor mounted sanitary terminal that has an integral base.
CounterTop:     A sanitary terminal that is installed into a horizontal surface that is installed into a horizontal surface. Note: When applied to a wash hand basin, the term more normally used is vanity. See also Wash Hand Basin Type specification.
WallHung:   A sanitary terminal cantilevered clear of the floor.

properties.name: SpilloverLevel
properties.definition: The level at which water spills out of the object.

Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeUrinal.name: Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeUrinal
Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeUrinal.definition: Soil appliance that receives urine and directs it to a waste outlet (BS6100). HISTORY: In IFC4, Material property removed. Use materials capabilities from IfcMaterialResource schema. Prefix for color property removed. Datatype of color changed to IfcLabel (still a string value).  Mounting property added.

properties.name: UrinalType
properties.definition:
Selection of the type of urinal from the enumerated list of types where:-Bowl: Individual wall mounted urinal.
Slab: Urinal that consists of a slab or sheet fixed to a wall and down which urinal flows into a floor channel.
Stall: Floor mounted urinal that consists of an elliptically shaped sanitary stall fixed to a wall and down which urine flows into a floor channel.
Trough: Wall mounted urinal of elongated rectangular shape on plan, that can be used by more than one person at a time.

properties.name: Mounting
properties.definition:
The property enumeration Pset_SanitaryMountingEnum defines the forms of mounting or fixing of the sanitary terminal that may be specified within property sets used to define sanitary terminals (WCs, basins, sinks, etc.) where:-BackToWall:     A pedestal mounted sanitary terminal that fits flush to the wall at the rear to cover its service connections
Pedestal:   A floor mounted sanitary terminal that has an integral base
CounterTop:     A sanitary terminal that is installed into a horizontal surface that is installed into a horizontal surface. Note: When applied to a wash hand basin, the term more normally used is vanity. See also Wash Hand Basin Type specification.
WallHung:   A sanitary terminal cantilevered clear of the floor.Note that BackToWall, Pedestal and WallHung are allowable values for a bidet.

properties.name: SpilloverLevel
properties.definition: The level at which water spills out of the object.

Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeWashHandBasin.name: Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeWashHandBasin
Pset_SanitaryTerminalTypeWashHandBasin.definition: Waste water appliance for washing the upper parts of the body. HISTORY: In IFC4, Material property removed. Use materials capabilities from IfcMaterialResource schema. Datatype of color changed to IfcLabel (still a string value).

properties.name: WashHandBasinType
properties.definition:
Defines the types of wash hand basin that may be specified where:DentalCuspidor: Waste water appliance that receives and flushes away mouth washings
.
HandRinse: Wall mounted wash hand basin that has an overall width of 500mm or less
.
Hospital: Wash hand basin that has a smooth easy clean surface without tapholes or overflow slot for use where hygiene is of prime importance.Tipup: Wash hand basin mounted on pivots so that it can be emptied by tilting.Vanity: Wash hand basin for installation into a horizontal surface.Washfountain: Wash hand basin that is circular, semi-circular or polygonal on plan, at which more than one person can wash at the same time.
WashingTrough: Wash hand basin of elongated rectangular shape in plan, at which more than one person can wash at the same time.

properties.name: Mounting
properties.definition:
The property enumeration Pset_SanitaryMountingEnum defines the forms of mounting or fixing of the sanitary terminal that may be specified within property sets used to define sanitary terminals (WCs, basins, sinks, etc.) where:-BackToWall:     A pedestal mounted sanitary terminal that fits flush to the wall at the rear to cover its service connections
Pedestal:   A floor mounted sanitary terminal that has an integral base
CounterTop:     A sanitary terminal that is installed into a horizontal surface that is installed into a horizontal surface. Note: When applied to a wash hand basin, the term more normally used is vanity. See also Wash Hand Basin Type specification.
WallHung:   A sanitary terminal cantilevered clear of the floor.Note that BackToWall, Pedestal and WallHung are allowable values for a bidet.

Pset_SiteCommon.name: Pset_SiteCommon
Pset_SiteCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcSite. Please note that several site attributes are handled directly at the IfcSite instance, the site number (or short name) by IfcSite.Name, the site name (or long name) by IfcSite.LongName, and the description (or comments) by IfcSite.Description. The land title number is also given as an explicit attribute IfcSite.LandTitleNumber. Actual site quantities, like site perimeter, site area and site volume are provided by IfcElementQuantity, and site classification according to national building code by IfcClassificationReference. The global positioning of the site in terms of Northing and Easting and height above sea level datum is given by IfcSite.RefLongitude, IfcSite.RefLatitude, IfcSite.RefElevation and the postal address by IfcSite.SiteAddress.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". properties.definition: The ratio of the utilization,  TotalArea / BuildableArea, expressed as a maximum value. The ratio value may be used to derive BuildableArea.

properties.name: TotalArea
properties.definition: Total planned area for the site. Used for programming the site space.

properties.name: MaxAmbientTemp
properties.definition: Maximum ambient temperature of the site used as a basis of design

properties.name: MinAmbientTemp
properties.definition: Minimum ambient temperature of the site used as a basis of design

Pset_SlabCommon.name: Pset_SlabCommon
Pset_SlabCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcSlab. Note: Properties for PitchAngle added in IFC 2x3

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: AcousticRating
properties.definition:
Acoustic rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code. It indicates the sound transmission resistance of this object by an index ratio (instead of providing full sound absorption values).

properties.name: FireRating
properties.definition: Fire rating for this object. It is given according to the national fire safety classification.

properties.name: PitchAngle
properties.definition: Angle of the slab to the horizontal when used as a component for the roof (specified as 0 degrees or not asserted for cases where the slab is not used as a roof component).The shape information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the shape properties, provided in the attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence.  For geometry editing applications, like CAD: this value should be write-only.

properties.name: Combustible
properties.definition: Indication whether the object is made from combustible material (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: SurfaceSpreadOfFlame
properties.definition:
Indication on how the flames spread around the surface,
It is given according to the national building code that governs the fire behaviour for materials.

properties.name: Compartmentation
properties.definition: Indication whether the object is designed to serve as a fire compartmentation (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: IsExternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

properties.name: ThermalTransmittance
properties.definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of an element, within the direction of the thermal flow (including all materials).

properties.name: LoadBearing
properties.definition: Indicates whether the object is intended to carry loads (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Pset_SlabTypeTrackSlab.name: Pset_SlabTypeTrackSlab
Pset_SlabTypeTrackSlab.definition: Properties in this property set are generally applicable slabs used in railway tracks, modelled as IfcSlab with PredefinedType TRACKSLAB.

properties.name: TechnicalStandard
properties.definition: The technical standard which the element should comply with.

Pset_SolarDeviceTypeCommon.name: Pset_SolarDeviceTypeCommon
Pset_SolarDeviceTypeCommon.definition: Common properties for solar device types.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

Pset_SolidStratumCapacity.name: Pset_SolidStratumCapacity
Pset_SolidStratumCapacity.definition: Properties expressing the capacity of a stratum using physical measures. Regional and National conventions should be captured through classification and specific property sets.

properties.name: CohesionBehaviour
properties.definition: Cohesive shear strength of a rock or soil that is independent of interparticle friction.

properties.name: FrictionAngle
properties.definition: Friction angle is the tested inclination angle from horizontal.

properties.name: FrictionBehaviour
properties.definition: Friction shear strength of a rock or soil that is dependent on interparticle friction.

properties.name: GrainSize
properties.definition: Grain size diameter.

properties.name: HydraulicConductivity
properties.definition: Hydraulic Conductivity (permeability) of soil for water, given with the K or Kf value in m/s

properties.name: LoadBearingCapacity
properties.definition: Maximum load bearing capacity of the floor structure throughtout the storey as designed.

properties.name: NValue
properties.definition: Blow count from standard penetration testing, to ISO 22476-3, ASTM D1586[1] and Australian Standards AS 1289.6.3.1, which correlates to other engineering properties of soils.

properties.name: PermeabilityBehaviour
properties.definition: Proportionality constant in Darcy's law which relates flow rate and viscosity to a pressure gradient applied to the porous media.

properties.name: PoisonsRatio
properties.definition: Ratio of transverse contraction strain to longitudinal extension strain in the direction of stretching force.

properties.name: PwaveVelocity
properties.definition: P-wave velocity of a rock or soil.

properties.name: Resistivity
properties.definition: Electrical resistivity of a rock or soil (Ohm-m).

properties.name: SettlementBehaviour
properties.definition: Estimate of the settlement/compaction behaviour of the stratum.

properties.name: SwaveVelocity
properties.definition: S-wave velocity of a rock or soil.

Pset_SolidStratumComposition.name: Pset_SolidStratumComposition
Pset_SolidStratumComposition.definition: Properties expressing the composition of a stratum using volume measures, implementing ISO14688 Part 2 Table 1 Primary fractions and composite fractions. Regional and National conventions should be captured through classification and specific property sets. Zero values may be omitted.

properties.name: AirVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of air stratum constituents.

properties.name: BouldersVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of boulders (typically larger than 200mm) stratum constituents.

properties.name: ClayVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of clay (typically smaller than 0.002mm) stratum constituents.

properties.name: CobblesVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of cobbles (typically larger than 63mm) stratum constituents.

properties.name: ContaminantVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of contaminant stratum constituents.

properties.name: FillVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of fill (controlled placement of anthropogenic soil) stratum constituents.

properties.name: GravelVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of gravel (typically larger than 2mm) stratum constituents.

properties.name: OrganicVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of organic (peat/humus) stratum constituents especially soil.

properties.name: RockVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of rock stratum constituents.

properties.name: SandVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of sand (typically smaller than 2mm) stratum constituents.

properties.name: SiltVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of silt (typically smaller than 0.063mm) stratum constituents.

properties.name: WaterVolume
properties.definition: Relative volume of water stratum constituents.

properties.name: CompositeFractions
properties.definition: Denomination into soil groups by composite fractions

Pset_SoundAttenuation.name: Pset_SoundAttenuation
Pset_SoundAttenuation.definition: Common definition to capture sound pressure at a point on behalf of a device typically used within the context of building services and flow distribution systems.   To indicate sound values from an instance of IfcDistributionFlowElement at a particular location, IfcAnnotation instance(s) should be assigned to the IfcDistributionFlowElement through the IfcRelAssignsToProduct relationship. The IfcAnnotation should specify ObjectType of 'Sound' and geometric representation of 'Annotation Point' consisting of a single IfcPoint subtype as described at IfcAnnotation.  This property set is instantiated multiple times on an object for each frequency band.  HISTORY: New property set in IFC Release 2x4.

properties.name: SoundScale
properties.definition:
The reference sound scale.DBA: Decibels in an A-weighted scale
DBB: Decibels in an B-weighted scale
DBC: Decibels in an C-weighted scale
NC: Noise criteria
NR: Noise rating

properties.name: SoundFrequency
properties.definition: List of nominal sound frequencies, correlated to the SoundPressure time series values (IfcTimeSeries.ListValues)

properties.name: SoundPressure
properties.definition: A time series of sound pressure values measured in decibels at a reference pressure of 20 microPascals for the referenced octave band frequency.  Each value in IfcTimeSeries.ListValues is correlated to the sound frequency at the same position within SoundFrequencies.

Pset_SoundGeneration.name: Pset_SoundGeneration
Pset_SoundGeneration.definition: Common definition to capture the properties of sound typically used within the context of building services and flow distribution systems.  This property set is instantiated multiple times on an object for each frequency band.  HISTORY: New property set in IFC Release 2x4.

properties.name: SoundCurve
properties.definition:
Sound curve.

Table of sound frequencies and sound power measured in decibels at a reference power of 1 picowatt(10\^(-12) watt) for the referenced octave band frequency.

properties.name: CoolingDesignAirFlow
properties.definition: The air flowrate required during the peak cooling conditions.

properties.name: HeatingDesignAirFlow
properties.definition: The air flowrate required during the peak heating conditions, but could also be determined by minimum ventilation requirement or minimum air change requirements.

properties.name: SensibleHeatGain
properties.definition: The  sensible heat or energy gained by the space during the peak conditions.

properties.name: TotalHeatGain
properties.definition: The total (sensible+latent) amount of heat or energy gained by the space at the time of the space's peak cooling conditions.

properties.name: TotalHeatLoss
properties.definition: The total amount of heat or energy lost by the space at the time of the space's peak heating conditions.

properties.name: CoolingDryBulb
properties.definition: Dry bulb temperature, usually for for cooling design.

properties.name: CoolingRelativeHumidity
properties.definition: Inside relative humidity for cooling design.

properties.name: HeatingDryBulb
properties.definition: Dry bulb temperature for heating design.

properties.name: HeatingRelativeHumidity
properties.definition: Inside relative humidity for heating design.

properties.name: VentilationDesignAirFlow
properties.definition: Ventilation outside air requirement for the space.

properties.name: DesignAirFlow
properties.definition: Design air flow rate for the space.

properties.name: CeilingRAPlenum
properties.definition: Ceiling plenum used for return air or not. TRUE = Yes, FALSE = No.

properties.name: BoundaryAreaHeatLoss
properties.definition: Heat loss per unit area for the boundary object. This is a design input value for use in the absence of calculated load data.

Pset_SpaceCommon.name: Pset_SpaceCommon
Pset_SpaceCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcSpace. Please note that several space attributes are handled directly at the IfcSpace instance, the space number (or short name) by IfcSpace.Name, the space name (or long name) by IfcSpace.LongName, and the description (or comments) by IfcSpace.Description. Actual space quantities, like space perimeter, space area and space volume are provided by IfcElementQuantity, and space classification according to national building code by IfcClassificationReference. The level above zero (relative to the building) for the slab row construction is provided by the IfcBuildingStorey.Elevation, the level above zero (relative to the building) for the floor finish is provided by the IfcSpace.ElevationWithFlooring.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: IsExternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

properties.name: GrossPlannedArea
properties.definition: Total planned gross area of the spatial structure element. Used for programming the spatial structure element.

properties.name: NetPlannedArea
properties.definition: Total planned net area of the object. Used for programming the object.

properties.name: PubliclyAccessible
properties.definition: Indication whether this space (in case of e.g., a toilet) is designed to serve as a publicly accessible space, e.g., for a public toilet (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: HandicapAccessible
properties.definition: Indication that this object is designed to be accessible by the handicapped. Set to (TRUE) if this object is rated as handicap accessible according to the local building codes, otherwise (FALSE). It is giving according to the requirements of the national building code.

Pset_SpaceCoveringRequirements.name: Pset_SpaceCoveringRequirements
Pset_SpaceCoveringRequirements.definition: Properties common to the definition of covering requirements of IfcSpace. Those properties define the requirements coming from a space program in early project phases and can later be used to define the room book information, if such coverings are not modeled explicitly as covering elements.

properties.name: FloorCovering
properties.definition: Label to indicate the material or finish of the space flooring. The label is used for room book information and often displayed in room stamp.The material information is provided in absence of an IfcCovering (type=FLOORING) object with own shape representation and material assignment. In case of inconsistency the material assigned to IfcCovering elements takes precedence.

properties.name: FloorCoveringThickness
properties.definition: Thickness of the material layer(s) for the space flooring.The thickness information is provided in absence of an IfcCovering (type=FLOORING) object with own shape representation. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters of an assigned IfcCovering and this attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: WallCovering
properties.definition: Label to indicate the material or finish of the space cladding. The label is used for room book information and often displayed in room stamp.The material information is provided in absence of an IfcCovering (type=CLADDING) object with own shape representation and material assignment. In case of inconsistency the material assigned to IfcCovering elements takes precedence.

properties.name: WallCoveringThickness
properties.definition: Thickness of the material layer(s) for the space cladding.The thickness information is provided in absence of an IfcCovering (type=CLADDING) object with own shape representation. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters of an assigned IfcCovering and this attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: CeilingCovering
properties.definition: Label to indicate the material or finish of the space ceiling. The label is used for room book information and often displayed in room stamp.The material information is provided in absence of an IfcCovering (type=CEILING) object with own shape representation and material assignment. In case of inconsistency the material assigned to IfcCovering elements takes precedence.

properties.name: CeilingCoveringThickness
properties.definition: Thickness of the material layer(s) for the space ceiling.The thickness information is provided in absence of an IfcCovering (type=CEILING) object with own shape representation. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters of an assigned IfcCovering and this attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: SkirtingBoard
properties.definition: Label to indicate the material or construction of the skirting board around the space flooring. The label is used for room book information.The material information is provided in absence of an IfcCovering (type=SKIRTINGBOARD) object with own shape representation and material assignment. In case of inconsistency the material assigned to IfcCovering elements takes precedence.

properties.name: SkirtingBoardHeight
properties.definition: Height of the skirting board.The height information is provided in absence of an IfcCovering (type=SKIRTINGBOARD) object with own shape representation and material assignment. In case of inconsistency the height assigned to IfcCovering elements takes precedence.

properties.name: Molding
properties.definition: Label to indicate the material or construction of the molding around the space ceiling. The label is used for room book information.The material information is provided in absence of an IfcCovering (type=MOLDING) object with own shape representation and material assignment. In case of inconsistency the material assigned to IfcCovering elements takes precedence.

properties.name: MoldingHeight
properties.definition: Height of the molding.The height information is provided in absence of an IfcCovering (type=MOLDING) object with own shape representation and material assignment. In case of inconsistency the height assigned to IfcCovering elements takes precedence.

properties.name: ConcealedFlooring
properties.definition: Indication whether this space is designed to have a concealed flooring space (TRUE) or not (FALSE). A concealed flooring space is normally meant to be the space beneath a raised floor.

properties.name: ConcealedFlooringOffset
properties.definition: Distance between the floor slab and the floor covering, often used for cables and other installations. Often referred to as raised flooring.

properties.name: ConcealedCeiling
properties.definition: Indication whether this space is designed to have a concealed flooring space (TRUE) or not (FALSE). A concealed ceiling space is normally meant to be the space between a slab and a ceiling.

properties.name: ConcealedCeilingOffset
properties.definition: Distance between the upper floor slab and the suspended ceiling, often used for distribution systems. Often referred to as plenum.

Pset_SpaceFireSafetyRequirements.name: Pset_SpaceFireSafetyRequirements
Pset_SpaceFireSafetyRequirements.definition: Properties related to fire protection of spaces that apply to the occurrences of IfcSpace or IfcZone.

properties.name: FireRiskFactor
properties.definition: Fire Risk factor assigned to the space according to local building regulations. It defines the fire risk of the space at several levels of fire hazard.

properties.name: FlammableStorage
properties.definition: Indication whether the space is intended to serve as a storage of flammable material (which is regarded as such by the presiding building code. (TRUE) indicates yes, (FALSE) otherwise.

properties.name: FireExit
properties.definition:
Indication whether this object is designed to serve as an exit in the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Here whether the space (in case of e.g., a corridor) is designed to serve as an exit space, e.g., for fire escape purposes.

properties.name: SprinklerProtection
properties.definition: Indication whether this object is sprinkler protected (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: SprinklerProtectionAutomatic
properties.definition:
Indication whether this object has an automatic sprinkler protection (TRUE) or not (FALSE).
It should only be given, if the property "SprinklerProtection" is set to TRUE.

properties.name: AirPressurization
properties.definition: Indication whether the space is required to have pressurized air (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Pset_SpaceHeaterPHistory.name: Pset_SpaceHeaterPHistory
Pset_SpaceHeaterPHistory.definition: Space heater performance history common attributes.

properties.name: FractionRadiantHeatTransfer
properties.definition: Fraction of the total heat transfer rate as the radiant heat transfer.

properties.name: FractionConvectiveHeatTransfer
properties.definition: Fraction of the total heat transfer rate as the convective heat transfer.

properties.name: Effectiveness
properties.definition:
Effectiveness, represented as ratio.

Ratio of the real heat transfer rate to the maximum possible heat transfer rate.

properties.name: SurfaceTemperature
properties.definition: Average surface temperature of the component.

properties.name: SpaceAirTemperature
properties.definition: Dry bulb temperature in the space.

properties.name: SpaceMeanRadiantTemperature
properties.definition: Mean radiant temperature in the space.

properties.name: AuxiliaryEnergySourceConsumption
properties.definition: Auxiliary energy source consumption.

properties.name: UACurve
properties.definition:
UA value.

As a function of ambient temperature and surface temperature; UA = f (Tambient, Tsurface)

properties.name: OutputCapacityCurve
properties.definition: Partial output capacity curve (as a function of water temperature); Q = f (Twater).

properties.name: AirResistanceCurve
properties.definition: Air resistance curve (w/ fan only); Pressure = f ( flow rate).

properties.name: CharacteristicExponent
properties.definition: Characteristic exponent, slope of log(heat output) vs log (surface temperature minus environmental temperature).

properties.name: HeatOutputRate
properties.definition: Overall heat transfer rate.

Pset_SpaceHeaterTypeCommon.name: Pset_SpaceHeaterTypeCommon
Pset_SpaceHeaterTypeCommon.definition:
Space heater type common attributes.
SoundLevel attribute deleted in IFC2x2 Pset Addendum: Use IfcSoundProperties instead.  Properties added in IFC4.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: SpaceHeaterPlacement
properties.definition: Indicates how the space heater is designed to be placed.

properties.name: TemperatureClassification
properties.definition:
Enumeration defining the temperature classification of the space heater surface temperature.
low temperature - surface temperature is relatively low, usually heated by hot water or electricity.
high temperature - surface temperature is relatively high, usually heated by gas or steam.

properties.name: HeatTransferDimension
properties.definition: Indicates how heat is transmitted according to the shape of the space heater.

properties.name: HeatTransferMedium
properties.definition: Enumeration defining the heat transfer medium if applicable.

properties.name: EnergySource
properties.definition:
Enumeration defining the energy source or fuel cumbusted.

Note: hydronic heaters shall use UNSET; dual-use hydronic/electric heaters shall use ELECTRICITY.

properties.name: BodyMass
properties.definition: Overall body mass of the heater.

properties.name: ThermalMassHeatCapacity
properties.definition: Product of component mass and specific heat.

properties.name: OutputCapacity
properties.definition: Total nominal heat output as listed by the manufacturer.

properties.name: ThermalEfficiency
properties.definition: Overall Thermal Efficiency is defined as gross energy output of the heat transfer device divided by the energy input.

properties.name: NumberOfPanels
properties.definition: Number of panels.

properties.name: NumberOfSections
properties.definition:
Number of sections.

Number of vertical sections, measured in the direction of flow.

properties.name: ConvectorType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of convector, whether forced air (mechanically driven) or natural (gravity).

properties.name: RadiatorType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of radiator.

properties.name: TubingLength
properties.definition: Water tube length inside the component.

properties.name: WaterContent
properties.definition: Weight of water content within the heater.

Pset_SpaceHVACDesign.name: Pset_SpaceHVACDesign
Pset_SpaceHVACDesign.definition: Properties for HVAC requirements for spaces.

properties.name: TemperatureSetPoint
properties.definition: The temperature setpoint range and default setpoint.

properties.name: TemperatureMax
properties.definition: Maximal temperature of the space or zone, that is required from user/designer view point.  If no summer or winter space temperature requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

properties.name: TemperatureMin
properties.definition: Minimal temperature of the space or zone, that is required from user/designer view point. If no summer or winter space temperature requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

properties.name: TemperatureSummerMax
properties.definition: Maximal temperature of the space or zone for the hot (summer) period, that is required from user/designer view point and provided as requirement for cooling.

properties.name: TemperatureSummerMin
properties.definition: Minimal temperature of the space or zone for the hot (summer) period, that is required from user/designer view point and provided as requirement for cooling.

properties.name: TemperatureWinterMax
properties.definition: Maximal temperature of the space or zone for the cold (winter) period, that is required from user/designer view point and provided as requirement for heating.

properties.name: TemperatureWinterMin
properties.definition: Minimal temperature of the space or zone for the cold (winter) period, that is required from user/designer view point and provided as requirement for heating.

properties.name: HumiditySetPoint
properties.definition: Humidity of the space or zone that is required from user/designer view point.  If no summer or winter space humidity requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period. Provide this property, if no humidity range (Min-Max) is available.

properties.name: HumidityMax
properties.definition: Maximal permitted humidity of the space or zone that is required from user/designer view point.  If no summer or winter space humidity requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

properties.name: HumidityMin
properties.definition: Minimal permitted humidity of the space or zone that is required from user/designer view point.  If no summer or winter space humidity requirements are given, it applies all year, otherwise for the intermediate period.

properties.name: HumiditySummer
properties.definition: Humidity of the space or zone for the hot (summer) period, that is required from user/designer view point and provided as requirement for cooling.

properties.name: HumidityWinter
properties.definition: Humidity of the space or zone for the cold (winter) period that is required from user/designer view point and provided as requirement for heating.

properties.name: DiscontinuedHeating
properties.definition: Indication whether discontinued heating is required/desirable from user/designer view point. (TRUE) if yes, (FALSE) otherwise.

properties.name: NaturalVentilation
properties.definition: Indication whether the space is required to have natural ventilation (TRUE), or not (FALSE).

properties.name: NaturalVentilationRate
properties.definition: Indication of the requirement of a particular natural air ventilation rate, given in air changes per hour.

properties.name: MechanicalVentilation
properties.definition: Indication whether the space is required to have mechanical ventilation (TRUE), or not (FALSE).

properties.name: MechanicalVentilationRate
properties.definition: Indication of the requirement of a particular mechanical air ventilation rate, given in air changes per hour.

properties.name: AirConditioning
properties.definition: Indication whether this space requires air conditioning provided (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: AirConditioningCentral
properties.definition:
Indication whether the space  requires a central air conditioning provided (TRUE) or not (FALSE).
It should only be given, if the property "AirConditioning" is set to TRUE.

properties.name: AirHandlingName
properties.definition: The name of the air side system.IfcRelServicesBuildings should be used to reference the correct AirHandlingSystem (IfcSystem)

Pset_SpaceLightingDesign.name: Pset_SpaceLightingDesign
Pset_SpaceLightingDesign.definition: Properties for requirements on Lighting of spaces.

properties.name: ArtificialLighting
properties.definition: Indication whether this space  requires artificial lighting (as natural lighting would be not sufficient). (TRUE) indicates yes (FALSE) otherwise.

properties.name: Illuminance
properties.definition: Required average illuminance value for this space.

Pset_SpaceOccupancyRequirements.name: Pset_SpaceOccupancyRequirements
Pset_SpaceOccupancyRequirements.definition: Properties concerning work activities occurring or expected to occur within one or a set of similar spatial structure elements.

properties.name: OccupancyType
properties.definition:
Occupancy type for this object.
It is defined according to the presiding national building code.

properties.name: OccupancyNumber
properties.definition: Number of people required for the activity assigned to this space.

properties.name: OccupancyNumberPeak
properties.definition: Maximal number of people required for the activity assigned to this space in peak time.

properties.name: OccupancyTimePerDay
properties.definition: The amount of time during the day that the activity is required within this space.

properties.name: AreaPerOccupant
properties.definition: Design occupancy loading for this type of usage assigned to this space.

properties.name: MinimumHeadroom
properties.definition: Headroom required for the activity assigned to this space.

properties.name: IsOutlookDesirable
properties.definition: An indication of whether the outlook is desirable (set TRUE) or not (set FALSE)

Pset_SpaceParking.name: Pset_SpaceParking
Pset_SpaceParking.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcSpace which have an attribute value for ObjectType = 'Parking'.NOTE  Modified in IFC 2x3, properties ParkingUse and ParkingUnits added.

properties.name: ParkingUse
properties.definition: Identifies the type of transportation for which the parking space is designed. Values are not predefined but might include car, compact car, motorcycle, bicycle, truck, bus etc.

properties.name: ParkingUnits
properties.definition: Indicates the number of transportation units of the type specified by the property ParkingUse that may be accommodated within the space. Generally, this value should default to 1 unit. However, where the parking space is for motorcycles or bicycles, provision may be made for more than one unit in the space.

properties.name: IsAisle
properties.definition: Indicates that this parking zone is for accessing the parking units, i.e. an aisle (TRUE) and not a parking unit itself (FALSE)

properties.name: IsOneWay
properties.definition: Indicates whether the parking aisle is designed for oneway traffic (TRUE) or twoway traffic (FALSE). Should only be provided if the property IsAisle is set to TRUE.

Pset_SpaceThermalLoad.name: Pset_SpaceThermalLoad
Pset_SpaceThermalLoad.definition: The space thermal load defines all thermal losses and gains occurring within a space or zone.  The thermal load source attribute defines an enumeration of possible sources of the thermal load. The maximum, minimum, time series and app

properties.name: People
properties.definition: Heat gains and losses from people.

properties.name: Lighting
properties.definition: Lighting loads.

properties.name: EquipmentSensible
properties.definition: Heat gains and losses from equipment.

properties.name: VentilationIndoorAir
properties.definition: Ventilation loads from indoor air.

properties.name: VentilationOutdoorAir
properties.definition: Ventilation loads from outdoor air.

properties.name: RecirculatedAir
properties.definition: Loads from recirculated air.

properties.name: ExhaustAir
properties.definition: Loads from exhaust air.

properties.name: AirExchangeRate
properties.definition: Loads from the air exchange rate.

properties.name: DryBulbTemperature
properties.definition:
Dry bulb temperature of the object.

Loads from the dry bulb temperature.

properties.name: Reference

Pset_StairCommon.name: Pset_StairCommon
Pset_StairCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcStair.

It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: NumberOfRiser
properties.definition: Total number of the risers included in the stair or stair flight.

properties.name: NumberOfTreads
properties.definition: Total number of treads included in the stair or stairflight.

properties.name: RiserHeight
properties.definition:
Vertical distance from tread to tread.
The riser height is supposed to be equal for all steps of a stair or stair flight.

properties.name: TreadLength
properties.definition:
Horizontal distance from the front of the thread to the front of the next tread.
The tread length is supposed to be equal for all steps of the stair or stair flight at the walking line.

properties.name: NosingLength
properties.definition: Horizontal distance from the front of the tread to the riser underneath. It is the overhang of the tread.

properties.name: WalkingLineOffset
properties.definition:
Offset of the walking line from the inner side of the flight.
Note: the walking line may have a own shape representation (in case of inconsistencies, the value derived from the shape representation shall take precedence).

properties.name: TreadLengthAtOffset
properties.definition:
Length of treads at a given offset.
Walking line position is given by the 'WalkingLineOffset'. The resulting value should normally be identical with TreadLength, it may be given in addition, if the walking line offset for building code calculations is different from that used in design.

properties.name: TreadLengthAtInnerSide
properties.definition:
Minimum length of treads at the inner side of the winder.
Only relevant in case of winding flights, for straight flights it is identical with IfcStairFlight.TreadLength. It is a pre-calculated value, in case of inconsistencies, the value derived from the shape representation shall take precedence.

properties.name: WaistThickness
properties.definition: Minimum thickness of the stair flight, measured perpendicular to the slope of the flight to the inner corner of riser and tread. It is a pre-calculated value, in case of inconsistencies, the value derived from the shape representation shall take precedence.

properties.name: RequiredHeadroom
properties.definition: Required headroom clearance for the passageway according to the applicable building code or additional requirements.

properties.name: HandicapAccessible
properties.definition: Indication that this object is designed to be accessible by the handicapped. Set to (TRUE) if this object is rated as handicap accessible according to the local building codes, otherwise (FALSE). It is giving according to the requirements of the national building code.

properties.name: HasNonSkidSurface
properties.definition: Indication whether the surface finish is designed to prevent slippery (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: IsExternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

properties.name: ThermalTransmittance
properties.definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of an element, within the direction of the thermal flow (including all materials).

properties.name: LoadBearing
properties.definition: Indicates whether the object is intended to carry loads (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: FireRating
properties.definition: Fire rating for this object. It is given according to the national fire safety classification.

properties.name: FireExit
properties.definition:
Indication whether this object is designed to serve as an exit in the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Here it defines an exit stair in accordance to the national building code.

Offset of the walking line from the inner side of the flight.

properties.name: HasIncreasingStation
properties.definition: Inform on the increasing or decreasing progress of stationing values, for referents nested in a given alignment.If present and true, or if not present, then the relevant subsequently nested referents are expected to have greater Pset_Stationing.Station values (i.e., increasing stations).If present and false, then the relevant subsequently nested referents are expected to have lower Pset_Stationing.Station values (i.e., decreasing stations).

Pset_StructuralSurfaceMemberVaryingThick.name: Pset_StructuralSurfaceMemberVaryingThickness
Pset_StructuralSurfaceMemberVaryingThick.definition: Thickness parameters of a surface member (structural analysis item) with varying thickness, particularly with linearly varying thickness.  The thickness is interpolated/ extrapolated from three points.  The locations of these points are given either in local x,y coordinates of the surface member or in global X,Y,Z coordinates.  Either way, these points are required to be located within the face or at the bounds of the face  of the surface member, and they must not be located on a common line.  Local and global coordinates shall not be mixed within the same property set instance.

properties.name: Thickness1
properties.definition: First thickness parameter of a surface member with varying thickness

properties.name: Location1Local
properties.definition: Local x,y coordinates of the point in which Thickness1 is given

properties.name: Location1Global
properties.definition: Global X,Y,Z coordinates of the point in which Thickness1 is given

properties.name: Thickness2
properties.definition: Second thickness parameter of a surface member with varying thickness

properties.name: Location2Local
properties.definition: Local x,y coordinates of the point in which Thickness2 is given

properties.name: Location2Global
properties.definition: Global X,Y,Z coordinates of the point in which Thickness2 is given

properties.name: Thickness3
properties.definition: Third thickness parameter of a surface member with varying thickness

properties.name: Location3Local
properties.definition: Local x,y coordinates of the point in which Thickness3 is given

properties.name: Location3Global
properties.definition: Global X,Y,Z coordinates of the point in which Thickness3 is given

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeCommon.definition: A switching device is a device designed to make or break the current in one or more electric circuits.

properties.name: NumberOfGangs

Number of gangs in the object.

Number of gangs/buttons on this switch.

properties.name: SwitchFunction
properties.definition: Indicates types of switches which differs in functionality.

properties.name: HasLock
properties.definition: Indication of whether a switching device has a key operated lock (=TRUE) or not (= FALSE).

properties.name: IsIlluminated
properties.definition: An indication of whether there is an illuminated indicator to show that the switch is on (=TRUE) or not (= FALSE).

properties.name: Legend
properties.definition: A text inscribed or applied to the switch as a legend to indicate purpose or function.

properties.name: SetPoint
properties.definition:
Indicates the setpoint and label.

For toggle switches, there are two positions, 0 for off and 1 for on.  For dimmer switches, the values may indicate the fully-off and full-on positions, where missing integer values in between are interpolated.   For selector switches, the range indicates the available positions.
An IfcTable may be attached (using IfcMetric and IfcResourceConstraintRelationship) containing columns of the specified header names and types:
'Position' (IfcInteger): The discrete setpoint level.
'Sink' (IfcLabel): The Name of the switched input port (IfcDistributionPort with FlowDirection=SINK).
'Source' (IfcLabel): The Name of the switched output port (IfcDistributionPort with FlowDirection=SOURCE).
'Ratio' (IfcNormalisedRatioMeasure): The ratio of power at the setpoint where 0.0 is off and 1.0 is fully on.

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeContactor.name: Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeContactor
Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeContactor.definition: An electrical device used to control the flow of power in a circuit on or off.

properties.name: ContactorType
properties.definition:
A list of the available types of contactor from which that required may be selected where:CapacitorSwitching: for switching 3 phase single or multi-step capacitor banks.
LowCurrent: requires the use of low resistance contacts.
MagneticLatching: enables the contactor to remain in the on position when the coil is no longer energized.
MechanicalLatching: requires that the contactor is mechanically retained in the on position.
Modular: are totally enclosed and self contained.
Reversing: has a double set of contactors that are prewired.
Standard: is a generic device that controls the flow of power in a circuit on or off.

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeDimmerSwitch.name: Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeDimmerSwitch
Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeDimmerSwitch.definition: A dimmer switch is a switch that adjusts electrical power through a variable position level action.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: DimmerType
properties.definition: A list of the available types of dimmer switch from which that required may be selected.

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeEmergencyStop.name: Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeEmergencyStop
Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeEmergencyStop.definition: An emergency stop device acts to remove as quickly as possible any danger that may have arisen unexpectedly.

properties.name: SwitchOperation
properties.definition: Indicates operation of emergency stop switch.

properties.name: NumberOfPhases
properties.definition: Number of phases that the equipment operates on.

properties.name: ReferenceEnvironmentTemperature
properties.definition: Ideal temperature range.

properties.name: BreakingCapacity
properties.definition: The current that a fuse, circuit breaker, or other electrical apparatus is able to interrupt without being destroyed or causing an electric arc with unacceptable duration.

properties.name: NumberOfEarthFaultRelays
properties.definition: Indicates the number of relays used for preventing earth fault.

properties.name: NumberOfEmergencyButtons
properties.definition: The number of emergency buttons built in the device.

properties.name: NumberOfRelays
properties.definition: Indicates number of relays built in the device.

properties.name: NumberOfOverCurrentRelays
properties.definition: Indicates number of relays used for preventing over current.

properties.name: NumberOfAffectedPoles
properties.definition: Number of poles that the equipment affects.

properties.name: NominalCurrent
properties.definition: The nominal current that is designed to be measured.

properties.name: RatedFrequency
properties.definition: Frequency of the AC electric power supply when the device or system reaches its optimum operating condition.

properties.name: RatedVoltage
properties.definition: The range of allowed voltage that a device is certified to handle. The upper bound of this value is the maximum.

properties.name: TransformationRatio
properties.definition: The ratio of the actual primary current or voltage to the actual secondary current or voltage.

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeKeypad.name: Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeKeypad
Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeKeypad.definition: A keypad is a switch supporting multiple functions.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: KeypadType
properties.definition: A list of the available types of keypad switch from which that required may be selected.

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeMomentarySwitch.name: Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeMomentarySwitch
Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeMomentarySwitch.definition: A momentary switch is a switch that does not hold state.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: MomentaryType
properties.definition: A list of the available types of momentary switch from which that required may be selected.

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypePHistory.name: Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypePHistory

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeRelay.definition: Properties in this property set are applicable for IfcSwitchingDevice with PredefinedType RELAY.

properties.name: NominalHeight
properties.definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: Current
properties.definition: The actual current and operable range.

properties.name: NominalLength
properties.definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: InsulationResistance
properties.definition: Minimum resistance between one terminal or several terminals connected together and the case or enclosure of a component at specified voltage.

properties.name: NominalWidth
properties.definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: ContactResistance
properties.definition: Resistance when electrical node is closed.

properties.name: PullInVoltage
properties.definition: Working voltage of relay in excitation state.

properties.name: ReleaseVoltage
properties.definition: The maximum voltage to guarantee the drop of the relay node.

properties.name: Voltage
properties.definition: The actual voltage and operable range.

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeSelectorSwitch.name: Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeSelectorSwitch
Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeSelectorSwitch.definition: A selector switch is a switch that adjusts electrical power through a multi-position action.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: SelectorType
properties.definition: A list of the available types of selector switch from which that required may be selected.

properties.name: SwitchUsage

properties.name: SwitchActivation
properties.definition: A list of the available activations for switches from which that required may be selected.

properties.name: NominalCurrent
properties.definition: The nominal current that is designed to be measured.

properties.name: ReferenceEnvironmentTemperature

properties.name: RatedFrequency

properties.name: NumberOfPhases
