properties.name: NominalPower
properties.definition: A conventional value of apparent power determining a value of the rated current that may be carried with rated voltage applied, under specified conditions. ( IEV ref 421-04-04)

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeStarter.name: Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeStarter
Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeStarter.definition: A starter is a switch which in the closed position controls the application of power to an electrical device.

properties.name: StarterType
properties.definition:
A list of the available types of starter from which that required may be selected where:AutoTransformer: A starter for an induction motor which uses for starting one or more reduced voltages derived from an auto transformer. (IEC 441-14-45)
Manual: A starter in which the force for closing the main contacts is provided exclusively by manual energy. (IEC 441-14-39)
DirectOnLine: A starter which connects the line voltage across the motor terminals in one step. (IEC 441-14-40)
Frequency: A starter in which the frequency of the power supply is progressively increased until the normal operation frequency is attained.
nStep: A starter in which there are (n-1) intermediate accelerating positions between the off and full on positions. (IEC 441-14-41)
Rheostatic: A starter using one or several resistors for obtaining, during starting, stated motor torque characteristics and for limiting the current. (IEC 441-14-425)
StarDelta: A starter for a 3 phase induction motor such that in the starting position the stator windings are connected in star and in the final running position they are connected in delta. (IEC 441-14-44)

Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeSwitchDisconnect.name: Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeSwitchDisconnector
Pset_SwitchingDeviceTypeSwitchDisconnect.definition: A switch disconnector is a switch which in the open position satisfies the isolating requirements specified for a disconnector.History: Property 'HasVisualIndication' changed to 'IsIlluminated' to conform with property name for toggle switch

properties.name: SwitchDisconnectorType
properties.definition:
A list of the available types of switch disconnector from which that required may be selected where:CenterBreak: A disconnector in which both contacts of each pole are movable and engage at a point substantially midway between their supports. (IEC 441-14-08)
DividedSupport: A disconnector in which the fixed and moving contacts of each pole are not supported by a common base or frame. (IEC 441-14-06)
DoubleBreak: A disconnector that opens a circuit at two points. (IEC 441-14-09)
EarthingSwitch: A disconnector in which the fixed and moving contacts of each pole are not supported by a common base or frame. (IEC 441-14-07)
Isolator: A disconnector which in the open position satisfies isolating requirements. (IEC 441-14-12)

properties.name: LoadDisconnectionType

properties.name: HasOpening
properties.definition: indicates whether the panel has an opening (= TRUE) or not (= FALSE).

properties.name: FurniturePanelType
properties.definition: Available panel types from which that required may be selected.

properties.name: NominalThickness
properties.definition: The nominal thickness of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Pset_SystemFurnitureElementTypeSubrack.name: Pset_SystemFurnitureElementTypeSubrack
Pset_SystemFurnitureElementTypeSubrack.definition: Properties of subrack used in railway telecom. The property set can be used by the predefined type SUBRACK of IfcSystemFurnitureElement

properties.name: NumberOfSlots
properties.definition: Indicates the number of  slots.

properties.name: NumberOfUnits
properties.definition: Indicates the number of vertical units.

properties.name: NumberOfOccupiedUnits
properties.definition: Indicates the number of vertical units occupied by the equipment.

Pset_SystemFurnitureElementTypeWorkSurfa.name: Pset_SystemFurnitureElementTypeWorkSurface
Pset_SystemFurnitureElementTypeWorkSurfa.definition: A set of specific properties for work surfaces used in workstations. HISTORY: First issued in IFC Release R1.5. Renamed from Pset_Worksurface

properties.name: UsePurpose
properties.definition: The principal purpose for which the work surface is intended to be used e.g. writing/reading, computer, meeting, printer, reference files, etc.

properties.name: SupportType
properties.definition: Available support types from which that required may be selected.

properties.name: HangingHeight
properties.definition: The hanging height of the worksurface.

properties.name: NominalThickness
properties.definition: The nominal thickness of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: ShapeDescription
properties.definition: A description of the shape of the work surface e.g. corner square, rectangle, etc.

Pset_TankOccurrence.name: Pset_TankOccurrence
Pset_TankOccurrence.definition: Properties that relate to a tank. Note that a partial tank may be considered as a compartment within a compartmentalized tank.

properties.name: TankComposition
properties.definition:
Defines the level of element composition where.COMPLEX: A set of elementary units aggregated together to fulfill the overall  required purpose.
ELEMENT: A single elementary unit that may exist of itself or as an aggregation of partial units..
PARTIAL: A partial elementary unit.

properties.name: HasLadder
properties.definition: Indication of whether the tank is provided with a ladder (set TRUE) for access to the top. If no ladder is provided then value is set FALSE.Note: No indication is given of the type of ladder (gooseneck etc.)

properties.name: HasVisualIndicator
properties.definition: Indication of whether the tank is provided with a visual indicator (set TRUE) that shows the water level in the tank. If no visual indicator is provided then value is set FALSE.

Pset_TankTypeCommon.name: Pset_TankTypeCommon
Pset_TankTypeCommon.definition: Common attributes of a tank type.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: AccessType
properties.definition: Defines the types of access (or cover) to a tank that may be specified.Note that covers are generally specified for rectangular tanks. For cylindrical tanks, access will normally be via a manhole.

properties.name: StorageType
properties.definition: Defines the general material category intended to be stored.

properties.name: NominalLengthOrDiameter
properties.definition: The nominal length or, in the case of a vertical cylindrical tank, the nominal diameter of the tank.

properties.name: NominalWidthOrDiameter
properties.definition: The nominal width or, in the case of a horizontal cylindrical tank, the nominal diameter of the tank.Note: Not required for a vertical cylindrical tank.

properties.name: NominalDepth
properties.definition: Nominal Depth of the object

properties.name: TankNominalCapacity
properties.definition: The total nominal or design volumetric capacity of the tank.

properties.name: EffectiveCapacity
properties.definition: The total effective or actual volumetric capacity of the tank.

properties.name: OperatingWeight
properties.definition: Operating weight of the tank including all of its contents.

properties.name: PatternType
properties.definition: Defines the types of pattern (or shape of a tank that may be specified.

properties.name: EndShapeType
properties.definition: Defines the types of end shapes that can be used for preformed tanks. The convention for reading these enumerated values is that for a vertical cylinder, the first value is the base and the second is the top; for a horizontal cylinder, the order of reading should be left to right. For a speherical tank, the value UNSET should be used.

properties.name: FirstCurvatureRadius
properties.definition: FirstCurvatureRadius should be defined as the base or left side radius of curvature value.

properties.name: SecondCurvatureRadius
properties.definition: SecondCurvatureRadius should be defined as the top or right side radius of curvature value.

properties.name: NumberOfSections
properties.definition:
Number of sections.

Number of sections used in the construction of the tank. Default is 1.Note: All sections assumed to be the same size.

Pset_TankTypeExpansion.name: Pset_TankTypeExpansion
Pset_TankTypeExpansion.definition: Common attributes of an expansion type tank.

properties.name: ChargePressure
properties.definition: Nominal or design operating pressure of the tank.

properties.name: PressureRegulatorSetting
properties.definition: Pressure that is automatically maintained in the tank.

properties.name: ReliefValveSetting
properties.definition: Pressure at which the relief valve activates.

Pset_TankTypePreformed.name: Pset_TankTypePreformed
Pset_TankTypePreformed.definition: Fixed vessel manufactured as a single unit with one or more compartments for storing a liquid.Pset renamed from Pset_TankTypePreformedTank to Pset_TankTypePreformed in IFC2x2 Pset Addendum.

properties.name: PatternType
properties.definition: Defines the types of pattern (or shape of a tank that may be specified.

properties.name: EndShapeType
properties.definition: Defines the types of end shapes that can be used for preformed tanks. The convention for reading these enumerated values is that for a vertical cylinder, the first value is the base and the second is the top; for a horizontal cylinder, the order of reading should be left to right. For a speherical tank, the value UNSET should be used.

properties.name: FirstCurvatureRadius
properties.definition: FirstCurvatureRadius should be defined as the base or left side radius of curvature value.

properties.name: SecondCurvatureRadius
properties.definition: SecondCurvatureRadius should be defined as the top or right side radius of curvature value.

Pset_TankTypePressureVessel.name: Pset_TankTypePressureVessel
Pset_TankTypePressureVessel.definition: Common attributes of a pressure vessel.

properties.name: ChargePressure
properties.definition: Nominal or design operating pressure of the tank.

properties.name: PressureRegulatorSetting
properties.definition: Pressure that is automatically maintained in the tank.

properties.name: ReliefValveSetting
properties.definition: Pressure at which the relief valve activates.

Pset_TankTypeSectional.name: Pset_TankTypeSectional
Pset_TankTypeSectional.definition:
Fixed vessel constructed from sectional parts with one or more compartments for storing a liquid.Note (1): All sectional construction tanks are considered to be rectangular by default.
Note (2): Generally, it is not expected that sectional construction tanks will be used for the purposes of gas storage.Pset renamed from Pset_TankTypeSectionalTank to Pset_TankTypeSectional in IFC2x2 Pset Addendum.

properties.name: NumberOfSections
properties.definition:
Number of sections.

Number of sections used in the construction of the tankNote: All sections assumed to be the same size.

properties.name: SectionLength
properties.definition: The length of a section used in the construction of the tank.

properties.name: SectionWidth
properties.definition: The width of a section used in the construction of the tank.

Pset_TelecomCableGeneral.name: Pset_TelecomCableGeneral
Pset_TelecomCableGeneral.definition: Properties common to occurrences and types of IfcCableSegment and IfcCableFitting applied in telecommunication domain.

properties.name: Attenuation
properties.definition: Indicates the optical or electrical attenuation of the cable measured in dB, at a certain wavelength or frequency, changing with the length of the cable.

properties.name: FireRating
properties.definition: Fire rating for this object. It is given according to the national fire safety classification.

properties.name: IsFireResistant
properties.definition: Indicates whether the cable is fire resistant.

properties.name: NominalDiameter
properties.definition: Nominal diameter or width of the object.

properties.name: JacketColour
properties.definition: Indicates the colour of the cable or fitting jacket.

properties.name: CableFunctionType
properties.definition: Distinguishes between Telecom and Power Supply cables.

properties.name: CableArmourType
properties.definition: The armour type of the cable for mechanical protection.

Pset_ThermalLoad.name: Pset_ThermalLoad
Pset_ThermalLoad.definition: Properties for thermal loads of elements.

properties.name: OccupancyDiversity
properties.definition: Diversity factor that may be applied to the number of people in the space.

properties.name: LightingDiversity
properties.definition: Lighting diversity.

properties.name: ApplianceDiversity
properties.definition: Diversity of appliance load.

properties.name: OutsideAirPerPerson
properties.definition: Design quantity of outside air to be provided per person in the space.

properties.name: ReceptacleLoadIntensity
properties.definition: Average power use intensity of appliances and other non-HVAC equipment in the space per unit area.(PowerMeasure/IfcAreaMeasure).

properties.name: AppliancePercentLoadToRadiant
properties.definition: Percent of sensible load to radiant heat.

properties.name: LightingLoadIntensity
properties.definition: Average lighting load intensity in the space per unit area (PowerMeasure/IfcAreaMeasure).

properties.name: LightingPercentLoadToReturnAir
properties.definition: Percent of lighting load to the return air plenum.

properties.name: TotalCoolingLoad
properties.definition: The peak total cooling load for the building, zone or space.

properties.name: TotalHeatingLoad
properties.definition: The peak total heating load for the building, zone or space.

properties.name: InfiltrationDiversitySummer
properties.definition: Diversity factor for Summer infiltration.

properties.name: InfiltrationDiversityWinter
properties.definition: Diversity factor for Winter infiltration.

properties.name: LoadSafetyFactor
properties.definition: Load safety factor.

Pset_TicketProcessing.name: Pset_TicketProcessing
Pset_TicketProcessing.definition: Properties for indicating performance ratings for ticket processing of entry elements (e.g. turnstile, boom barrier).

properties.name: TicketProcessingTime
properties.definition: Indicates the processing time of a ticket.

properties.name: TicketStuckRatio
properties.definition: Indicates the ratio of tickets being stuck or jammed in the appliance.

Pset_TicketVendingMachine.name: Pset_TicketVendingMachine
Pset_TicketVendingMachine.definition: Properties of ticket vending machine. The property set can be used by IfcElectricAppliance with PredefinedType VENDINGMACHINE.

properties.name: TicketStuckRatio
properties.definition: Indicates the ratio of tickets being stuck or jammed in the appliance.

properties.name: MoneyStuckRatio
properties.definition: Indicates the ratio of money being stuck or jammed in appliance.

properties.name: PaymentMethod
properties.definition: Indicates the vending machine payment method.

properties.name: TicketProductionSpeed
properties.definition: Indicates the production speed of the ticket. It is measured by counting the number of tickets that can be produced per hour.

properties.name: TicketVendingMachineType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of ticket vending machine.

properties.name: VendingMachineUserInterface
properties.definition: Indicates the type of vending machine user interface.

properties.name: Permeability
properties.definition:
Ratio of the permeability of the ceiling.
The ration can be used to indicate an open ceiling (that enables identification of whether ceiling construction should be considered as impeding distribution of sprinkler water, light etc. from installations within the ceiling area).

properties.name: TileLength
properties.definition: Length of ceiling tiles. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: TileWidth
properties.definition: Width of ceiling tiles. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Pset_Tolerance.name: Pset_Tolerance
Pset_Tolerance.definition: Properties expressing the tolerance relating to locating and shaping of an intended element or feature. Range diameters are non-negative describing a linear, rectangular or  boxed region  .

properties.name: ToleranceDescription
properties.definition: General description of the tolerance associated to the element or feature, its source and implications.

properties.name: ToleranceBasis
properties.definition: Indication of the basis of the tolerance requirement

properties.name: OverallTolerance
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range tolerance associated to the intended shape and position in XYZ.

properties.name: HorizontalTolerance
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range tolerance associated to the horizontal shape and position in X, if different to the overall tolerance.

properties.name: OrthogonalTolerance
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range tolerance associated to the horizontal shape and position in Y, if different to the overall tolerance.

properties.name: VerticalTolerance
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range tolerance associated to the vertical shape and position in Z, if different to the overall tolerance.

properties.name: PlanarFlatness
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range flatness associated to the intended shape and position in XYZ.

properties.name: HorizontalFlatness
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range flatness associated to the horizontal surface in XY, if different to the overall flatness.

properties.name: ElevationalFlatness
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range flatness associated to the elevational surface in ZX, if different to the overall flatness.

properties.name: SideFlatness
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range flatness associated to the side surface in YZ, if different to the overall flatness.

properties.name: OverallOrthogonality
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range orthogonality associated to the intended shape and orientation in XYZ.

properties.name: HorizontalOrthogonality
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range orthogonality associated to the horizontal shape and orientation in X, if different to the overall orthogonality.

properties.name: OrthogonalOrthogonality
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range orthogonality associated to the horizontal shape and orientation in Y, if different to the overall orthogonality.

properties.name: VerticalOrthogonality
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range orthogonality associated to the vertical shape and orientation in Z, if different to the overall orthogonality.

properties.name: OverallStraightness
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range straightness associated to the intended shape.

properties.name: HorizontalStraightness
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range straightness  associated to the horizontal shape in X, if different to the overall straightness.

properties.name: OrthogonalStraightness
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range straightness  associated to the horizontal shape  in Y, if different to the overall straightness.

properties.name: VerticalStraightness
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range straightness associated to the vertical shape in Z, if different to the overall straightness.

Pset_TrackBase.name: Pset_TrackBase
Pset_TrackBase.definition: Properties in this property set are applicable for IfcSlab with PredefinedType BASESLAB, indicated that the base slab is a track base slab.

properties.name: IsSurfaceGalling
properties.definition: Indicates whether the surface is galling or not.

properties.name: SurfaceGallingArea
properties.definition: The galling area of the object surface.

Pset_TrackElementOccurrenceSleeper.name: Pset_TrackElementOccurrenceSleeper
Pset_TrackElementOccurrenceSleeper.definition: Properties common to the definition to all occurrences of IfcTrackElement with PredefinedType set to SLEEPER.

properties.name: HasSpecialEquipment
properties.definition: Indicates whether the sleeper has any special equipment for fastening components (e.g. Balise, signum magnet) or not.

properties.name: SequenceInTrackPanel
properties.definition: Sequence of the sleeper within the track panel.

properties.name: UnderSleeperPadStiffness
properties.definition: Indicates the stiffness of the under-sleeper pad as design reference for the sleeper.

properties.name: IsContaminatedSleeper
properties.definition: Indicates whether the sleeper is contaminated and requires special disposal or not.

Pset_TrackElementPHistoryDerailer.name: Pset_TrackElementPHistoryDerailer
Pset_TrackElementPHistoryDerailer.definition: Indicates derailer information over time for operation management.

properties.name: IsDerailing
properties.definition: Indicates whether the derailer is on or not.

Pset_TrackElementTypeDerailer.name: Pset_TrackElementTypeDerailer
Pset_TrackElementTypeDerailer.definition: Properties common to the definition to all occurrences and types of IfcTrackElement with PredefinedType set to DERAILER.

properties.name: AppliedLineLoad
properties.definition: The load of line where the derailer is installed. It is a design parameter and is defined by mass per length.

properties.name: DerailmentMaximumSpeedLimit
properties.definition: Indicates the maximum allowable train speed for the derailer.

properties.name: DerailmentWheelDiameter
properties.definition: Indicates the wheel diameter requirement for the derailer.

properties.name: DerailmentHeight
properties.definition: Height of derailment block when derailer in protection state.

Pset_TrackElementTypeSleeper.name: Pset_TrackElementTypeSleeper
Pset_TrackElementTypeSleeper.definition: Properties common to the definition to all occurrences and types of IfcTrackElement with PredefinedType set to SLEEPER.

properties.name: InstalledCondition
properties.definition: Assessment of the condition of the element at point of installation.

properties.name: SleeperType
properties.definition: Indicates the sleeper type.

properties.name: TechnicalStandard
properties.definition: The technical standard which the element should comply with.

properties.name: FasteningType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of fastening used to generate traction between the foot of the rail and the sleeper. It depends on but is not uniquely identified by the type of sleeper. This property shall only be used when sleeper fastening is not modelled as an element.

properties.name: IsElectricallyInsulated
properties.definition: Indicates whether the sleeper is electrically insulated due to its design or the running rails or not.

properties.name: HollowSleeperUsage
properties.definition: Indicates the purpose of using hollow sleeper. The possible value can be eg. cable trenching, protection of turnout mechanism, etc.

properties.name: NumberOfTrackCenters
properties.definition: Indicates the number of track centers running over the sleepers.

properties.name: IsHollowSleeper
properties.definition: Indicates whether the sleeper is hollowed or not.

Pset_TractionPowerSystem.name: Pset_TractionPowerSystem
Pset_TractionPowerSystem.definition: Properties of a traction power system. The property is associated to the predefined type ELECTRICAL of IfcDistributionSystem, and is used to characterise systems such as railway electrical distribution networks used to provide energy for rolling stock.

properties.name: PowerSupplyMode
properties.definition: Power supply mode of the equipment or system.

properties.name: ElectrificationType
properties.definition: Indicates the type of railway electrification.

properties.name: RatedFrequency
properties.definition: Frequency of the AC electric power supply when the device or system reaches its optimum operating condition.

properties.name: NominalVoltage
properties.definition: The optimum voltage for the electrical appliance or system.

Pset_TrafficCalmingDeviceCommon.name: Pset_TrafficCalmingDeviceCommon
Pset_TrafficCalmingDeviceCommon.definition: Properties for a traffic calming device.

properties.name: TypeDesignation
properties.definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. 'Bull nose', 'Half batter', 'Dropper', 'Chamfer' etc

Pset_TransformerTypeCommon.name: Pset_TransformerTypeCommon
Pset_TransformerTypeCommon.definition: An inductive stationary device that transfers electrical energy from one circuit to another.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: PrimaryVoltage
properties.definition: The voltage that is going to be transformed and that runs into the transformer on the primary side.

properties.name: SecondaryVoltage
properties.definition: The voltage that has been transformed and is running out of the transformer on the secondary side.

properties.name: PrimaryCurrent
properties.definition: The current that is going to be transformed and that runs into the transformer on the primary side.

properties.name: SecondaryCurrent
properties.definition: The current that has been transformed and is running out of the transformer on the secondary side.

properties.name: PrimaryFrequency
properties.definition: The frequency that is going to be transformed and that runs into the transformer on the primary side.

properties.name: SecondaryFrequency
properties.definition: The frequency that has been transformed and is running out of the transformer on the secondary side.

properties.name: PrimaryApparentPower
properties.definition: The power in VA (volt ampere) that has been transformed and that runs into the transformer on the primary side.

properties.name: SecondaryApparentPower
properties.definition: The power in VA (volt ampere) that has been transformed and is running out of the transformer on the secondary side.

properties.name: MaximumApparentPower
properties.definition: Maximum apparent power/capacity in VA (volt ampere).

properties.name: SecondaryCurrentType
properties.definition: A list of the secondary current types that can result from transformer output.

properties.name: ShortCircuitVoltage
properties.definition: A complex number that specifies the real and imaginary parts of the short-circuit voltage at rated current of a transformer given in %.

properties.name: RealImpedanceRatio
properties.definition:
The ratio between the real part of the zero sequence impedance and the real part of the positive impedance (i.e. real part of the short-circuit voltage) of the transformer.
Used for three-phase transformer which includes a N-conductor.

properties.name: ImaginaryImpedanceRatio
properties.definition:
The ratio between the imaginary part of the zero sequence impedance and the imaginary part of the positive impedance (i.e. imaginary part of the short-circuit voltage) of the transformer.
Used for three-phase transformer which includes a N-conductor.

properties.name: TransformerVectorGroup
properties.definition:
List of the possible vector groups for the transformer from which that required may be set. Values in the enumeration list follow a standard international code where the first letter  describes how the primary windings are connected,
the second letter describes how the secondary windings are connected, and the numbers describe the rotation of voltages and currents from the primary to the secondary side in multiples of 30 degrees.D: means that the windings are delta-connected.
Y: means that the windings are star-connected.
Z: means that the windings are zig-zag connected (a special start-connected providing low reactance of the transformer);
The connectivity is only relevant for three-phase transformers.

properties.name: IsNeutralPrimaryTerminalAvailable
properties.definition: An indication of whether the neutral point of the primary winding is available as a terminal (=TRUE) or not (= FALSE).

properties.name: IsNeutralSecondaryTerminalAvailable
properties.definition: An indication of whether the neutral point of the secondary winding is available as a terminal (=TRUE) or not (= FALSE).

properties.name: NominalLength
properties.definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Pset_TransportElementCommon.name: Pset_TransportElementCommon
Pset_TransportElementCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcTransportElement or IfcTransportElementType

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: CapacityPeople
properties.definition: Capacity of the transportation element measured in numbers of person.

properties.name: CapacityWeight
properties.definition: Capacity of the transport element measured by weight.

properties.name: FireExit
properties.definition:
Indication whether this object is designed to serve as an exit in the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Here whether the transport element (in case of e.g., a lift) is designed to serve as a fire exit, e.g., for fire escape purposes.

Pset_TransportElementElevator.name: Pset_TransportElementElevator
Pset_TransportElementElevator.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcTransportElement with the predefined type ="ELEVATOR"

properties.name: FireFightingLift
properties.definition: Indication whether the elevator is designed to serve as a fire fighting lift the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE). A fire fighting lift is used by fire fighters to access the location of fire and to evacuate people.

properties.name: ClearWidth
properties.definition:
The clear width.

It indicates the distance from the inner surfaces of the elevator car left and right from the elevator door.

properties.name: ClearDepth
properties.definition:
The clear depth.

It indicates the distance from the inner surface of the elevator door to the opposite surface of the elevator car.

properties.name: ClearHeight
properties.definition:
Clear height of the object (elevator).
The shape information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the shape properties, provided in the attached property, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Pset_TransportEquipmentOTN.name: Pset_TransportEquipmentOTN
Pset_TransportEquipmentOTN.definition: Properties in this property set are applied to transport equipment that act in optical transport network (OTN) system.

properties.name: SingleChannelAveragePower
properties.definition: Indicates the average power of a single channel of the transport equipment.

properties.name: ChromaticDispersionTolerance
properties.definition: Indicates the tolerance of the transport equipment chromatic dispersion. The value is defined by picosecond per nanometer (ps/nm).

properties.name: SingleChannelPower
properties.definition: Indicates the power range of a single channel of the transport equipment.

properties.name: MinimumOpticalSignalToNoiseRatio
properties.definition: Indicates the minimum optical signal to noise ratio of the transport equipment.

properties.name: PolarizationModeDispersionTolerance
properties.definition: Indicates the polarization mode dispersion tolerance of the transport equipment. It is usually measured by picosecond.

properties.name: SingleWaveTransmissionRate
properties.definition: Indicates the single wave transmission rate of the transport equipment.

properties.name: EquipmentCapacity
properties.definition: Indicates the equipment capacity of the appliance. The value is defined in bits/s.

properties.name: NominalDepth
properties.definition: Nominal Depth of the object

properties.name: NominalWidth
properties.definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: NumberOfRows
properties.definition: Number of tube rows in the tube bundle assembly.

properties.name: StaggeredRowSpacing
properties.definition: Staggered tube row spacing.

properties.name: InLineRowSpacing
properties.definition: In-line tube row spacing.

properties.name: NumberOfCircuits
properties.definition:
Number of circuits.

Number of parallel fluid tube circuits.

properties.name: FoulingFactor
properties.definition: Fouling factor of the tubes in the tube bundle.

properties.name: ThermalConductivity
properties.definition: The thermal conductivity of the object.

properties.name: Length
properties.definition: The length of the object.

properties.name: Volume
properties.definition:
Volume of the element.

Total volume of fluid in the tubes and their headers.

properties.name: NominalDiameter
properties.definition:
Nominal diameter or width of the object.

Nominal diameter or width of the tubes in the tube bundle.

properties.name: OutsideDiameter
properties.definition: Actual outside diameter of the tube in the tube bundle.

properties.name: InsideDiameter

For circular fins only.

properties.name: LinearUncertainty

properties.name: VerticalUncertainty
properties.definition: Indicative (95%-100%) range diameter associated to the vertical shape and position in Z, if different to the linear uncertainty.

Pset_UnitaryControlElementBaseStationCon.name: Pset_UnitaryControlElementBaseStationController

Pset_UnitaryControlElementPHistory.definition: Properties for history and operating schedules of thermostats.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

Indicates the temperature setpoint.  For thermostats with setbacks or separate high and low setpoints, then the time series may contain a pair of values at each entry where the first value is the heating setpoint (low) and the second value is the cooling setpoint (high).

Pset_UnitaryControlElementTypeControlPan.name: Pset_UnitaryControlElementTypeControlPanel
Pset_UnitaryControlElementTypeControlPan.definition: Properties that are applicable to IfcUnitaryControlElement with the predefined type set to CONTROLPANEL.

properties.name: NominalCurrent

UltimateRatedCurrent associated with the same breaker unit.

properties.name: ReferenceAirRelativeHumidity

Pset_UnitaryControlElementTypeIndicatorP.name: Pset_UnitaryControlElementTypeIndicatorPanel
Pset_UnitaryControlElementTypeIndicatorP.definition: Unitary control element type indicator panel attributes.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: UnitaryApplication
properties.definition: The application of the unitary control element.

Pset_UnitaryControlElementTypeThermostat.name: Pset_UnitaryControlElementTypeThermostat
Pset_UnitaryControlElementTypeThermostat.definition: Unitary control element type thermostat attributes.  HISTORY: Added in IFC4.

properties.name: TemperatureSetPoint

properties.name: SensibleCoolingCapacity

properties.name: LatentCoolingCapacity

properties.name: HeatingCapacity

properties.name: HeatingEfficiency

properties.name: CondenserFlowrate

properties.definition: Temperature of fluid entering condenser.

properties.name: CondenserLeavingTemperature
properties.definition: Temperature of fluid leaving condenser.

properties.name: OutsideAirFlowrate

Pset_UnitaryEquipmentTypeAirHandler.definition:
Air handler unitary equipment type attributes.

properties.name: AirHandlerConstruction
properties.definition: Enumeration defining how the air handler might be fabricated.

properties.name: AirHandlerFanCoilArrangement
properties.definition: Enumeration defining the arrangement of the supply air fan and the cooling coil.

properties.name: DualDeck
properties.definition: Does the AirHandler have a dual deck? TRUE = Yes, FALSE = No.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

Pset_UtilityConsumptionPHistory.name: Pset_UtilityConsumptionPHistory
Pset_UtilityConsumptionPHistory.definition: Consumption of utility resources, typically applied to the IfcBuilding instance, used to identify how much was consumed on I.e., a monthly basis.

properties.name: Heat
properties.definition: The amount of heat energy consumed during the period specified in the time series.

properties.name: Electricity
properties.definition: The amount of electricity consumed during the period specified in the time series.

properties.name: Water
properties.definition: The amount of water consumed during the period specified in the time series.

properties.name: Fuel
properties.definition: The amount of fuel consumed during the period specified in the time series.

properties.name: Steam
properties.definition: The amount of steam consumed during the period specified in the time series.

Pset_ValvePHistory.name: Pset_ValvePHistory
Pset_ValvePHistory.definition: Valve performance history common attributes of a typical 2 port pattern type valve.

properties.name: PercentageOpen
properties.definition: The ratio between the amount that the valve is open to the full open position of the valve.

properties.name: MeasuredFlowRate
properties.definition: The rate of flow of a fluid measured across the valve.

properties.name: MeasuredPressureDrop
properties.definition: The actual pressure drop in the fluid measured across the valve.

Pset_ValveTypeAirRelease.name: Pset_ValveTypeAirRelease
Pset_ValveTypeAirRelease.definition:
Valve used to release air from a pipe or fitting.
Note that an air release valve is constrained to have a single port pattern

properties.name: IsAutomatic
properties.definition: Indication of whether the valve is automatically operated (TRUE) or manually operated (FALSE).

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: ValvePattern
properties.definition:
The configuration of the ports of a valve according to either the linear route taken by a fluid flowing through the valve or by the number of ports where:SINGLEPORT: Valve that has a single entry port from the system that it serves, the exit port being to the surrounding environment.
ANGLED_2_PORT: Valve in which the direction of flow is changed through 90 degrees.
STRAIGHT_2_PORT: Valve in which the flow is straight through.
STRAIGHT_3_PORT: Valve with three separate ports.
CROSSOVER_4_PORT: Valve with 4 separate ports.

properties.name: ValveOperation
properties.definition:
The method of valve operation where:DROPWEIGHT: A valve that is closed by the action of a weighted lever being released, the weight normally being prevented from dropping by being held by a wire, the closure normally being made by the action of heat on a fusible link in the wire
FLOAT: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of a float that rises and falls with water level. The float may be a ball attached to a lever or other mechanism
HYDRAULIC: A valve that is opened and closed by hydraulic actuation
LEVER: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of a lever rotating the gate within the valve.
LOCKSHIELD: A valve that requires the use of a special lockshield key for opening and closing, the operating mechanism being protected by a shroud during normal operation.
MOTORIZED: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of an electric motor on an actuator
PNEUMATIC: A valve that is opened and closed by pneumatic actuation
SOLENOID: A valve that is normally held open by a magnetic field in a coil acting on the gate but that is closed immediately if the electrical current generating the magnetic field is removed.
SPRING: A valve that is normally held in position by the pressure of a spring on a plate but that may be caused to open if the pressure of the fluid is sufficient to overcome the spring pressure.
THERMOSTATIC: A valve in which the ports are opened or closed to maintain a required predetermined temperature.
WHEEL: A valve that is opened and closed by the action of a wheel moving the gate within the valve.

properties.name: ValveMechanism
properties.definition:
The mechanism by which the valve function is achieved where:BALL: Valve that has a ported ball that can be turned relative to the body seat ports.
BUTTERFLY: Valve in which a streamlined disc pivots about a diametric axis.
CONFIGUREDGATE: Screwdown valve in which the closing gate is shaped in a configured manner to have a more precise control of pressure and flow change across the valve.
GLAND: Valve with a tapered seating, in which a rotatable plug is retained by means of a gland and gland packing.
GLOBE: Screwdown valve that has a spherical body.
LUBRICATEDPLUG: Plug valve in which a lubricant is injected under pressure between the plug face and the body.
NEEDLE: Valve for regulating the flow in or from a pipe, in which a slender cone moves along the axis of flow to close against a fixed conical seat.
PARALLELSLIDE: Screwdown valve that has a machined plate that slides in formed grooves to form a seal.
PLUG: Valve that has a ported plug that can be turned relative to the body seat ports.
WEDGEGATE: Screwdown valve that has a wedge shaped plate fitting into tapered guides to form a seal.

properties.name: Size
properties.definition: The size of the connection to the valve (or to each connection for faucets, mixing valves, etc.).

properties.name: TestPressure
properties.definition: The maximum pressure to which the valve has been subjected under test.

properties.name: WorkingPressure
properties.definition:
Working pressure.

The normally expected maximum working pressure of the valve.

properties.name: FlowCoefficient
properties.definition: Flow coefficient (the quantity of fluid that passes through a fully open valve at unit pressure drop), typically expressed as the Kv or Cv value for the valve.

properties.name: CloseOffRating
properties.definition: Close off rating.

Pset_ValveTypeDrawOffCock.name: Pset_ValveTypeDrawOffCock
Pset_ValveTypeDrawOffCock.definition: A small diameter valve, used to drain water from a cistern or water filled system.

properties.name: HasHoseUnion
properties.definition: Indicates whether the object is fitted with a hose union connection (= TRUE) or not (= FALSE).

Pset_ValveTypeFaucet.name: Pset_ValveTypeFaucet
Pset_ValveTypeFaucet.definition: A small diameter valve, with a free outlet, from which water is drawn.

properties.name: FaucetType
properties.definition:
Defines the range of faucet types that may be specified where:Bib:     Faucet with a horizontal inlet and a nozzle that discharges downwards.
Globe:   Faucet fitted through the end of a bath, with a horizontal inlet, a partially spherical body and a vertical nozzle.
Diverter:   Combination faucet assembly with a valve to enable the flow of mixed water to be transferred to a showerhead.
DividedFlowCombination:  Combination faucet assembly in which hot and cold water are kept separate until emerging from a common nozzle
.
Pillar:  Faucet that has a vertical inlet and a nozzle that discharges downwards
.
SingleOutletCombination =    Combination faucet assembly in which hot and cold water mix before emerging from a common nozzle
.
Spray:   Faucet with a spray outlet
.
SprayMixing:     Spray faucet connected to hot and cold water supplies that delivers water at a temperature determined during use.

properties.name: FaucetOperation
properties.definition:
Defines the range of ways in which a faucet can be operated that may be specified where:CeramicDisc: Quick action faucet with a ceramic seal to open or close the orifice
.
LeverHandle: Quick action faucet that is operated by a lever handle
.
NonConcussiveSelfClosing:    Self closing faucet that does not induce surge pressure
.
QuarterTurn: Quick action faucet that can be fully opened or shut by turning the operating mechanism through 90 degrees.
QuickAction: Faucet that can be opened or closed fully with a single small movement of the operating mechanism
.
ScrewDown: Faucet in which a plate or disc is moved, by the rotation of a screwed spindle, to close or open the orifice.
SelfClosing: Faucet that is opened by pressure of the top of an operating spindle and is closed under the action of a spring or weight when the pressure is released.
TimedSelfClosing:   Self closing faucet that discharges for a predetermined period of time
.

properties.name: FaucetFunction
properties.definition: Defines the operating temperature of a faucet that may be specified.

properties.name: Finish
properties.definition: Description of the (surface) finish of the object for informational purposes.

properties.name: FaucetTopDescription
properties.definition: Description of the operating mechanism/top of the faucet.

Pset_ValveTypeFlushing.name: Pset_ValveTypeFlushing
Pset_ValveTypeFlushing.definition:
Valve that flushes a predetermined quantity of water to cleanse a WC, urinal or slop hopper.
Note that a flushing valve is constrained to have a 2 port  pattern.

properties.name: FlushingRate
properties.definition: The predetermined quantity of water to be flushed.

properties.name: HasIntegralShutOffDevice
properties.definition: Indication of whether the flushing valve has an integral shut off device fitted (set TRUE) or not (set FALSE).

properties.name: IsHighPressure
properties.definition: Indication of whether the flushing valve is suitable for use on a high pressure water main (set TRUE) or not (set FALSE).

Pset_ValveTypeGasTap.name: Pset_ValveTypeGasTap
Pset_ValveTypeGasTap.definition: A small diameter valve, used to discharge gas from a system.

properties.name: HasHoseUnion
properties.definition: Indicates whether the object is fitted with a hose union connection (= TRUE) or not (= FALSE).

Pset_ValveTypeIsolating.name: Pset_ValveTypeIsolating
Pset_ValveTypeIsolating.definition:
Valve that is used to isolate system components.
Note that an isolating valve is constrained to have a 2 port  pattern.

properties.name: IsNormallyOpen
properties.definition: If TRUE, the valve is normally open. If FALSE is is normally closed.

properties.name: IsolatingPurpose
properties.definition: Defines the purpose for which the isolating valve is used since the way in which the valve is identified as an isolating valve may be in the context of its use. Note that unless there is a contextual name for the isolating valve (as in the case of a Landing Valve on a rising fire main), then the value assigned shoulkd be UNSET.

Pset_ValveTypeMixing.name: Pset_ValveTypeMixing
Pset_ValveTypeMixing.definition: A valve where typically the temperature of the outlet is determined by mixing hot and cold water inlet flows.

properties.name: MixerControl
properties.definition: Defines the form of control of the mixing valve.

properties.name: OutletConnectionSize
properties.definition:
Size of the outlet connection from the object.

The size of the pipework connection from the mixing valve.

Pset_ValveTypePressureReducing.name: Pset_ValveTypePressureReducing
Pset_ValveTypePressureReducing.definition:
Valve that reduces the pressure of a fluid immediately downstream of its position in a pipeline to a preselected value or by a predetermined ratio.
Note that a pressure reducing valve is constrained to have a 2 port  pattern.

properties.name: UpstreamPressure
properties.definition: The operating pressure of the fluid upstream of the pressure reducing valve.

properties.name: DownstreamPressure
properties.definition: The operating pressure of the fluid downstream of the pressure reducing valve.

Pset_ValveTypePressureRelief.name: Pset_ValveTypePressureRelief
Pset_ValveTypePressureRelief.definition:
Spring or weight loaded valve that automatically discharges to a safe place fluid that has built up to excessive pressure in pipes or fittings.
Note that a pressure relief valve is constrained to have a single port pattern.

properties.name: ReliefPressure
properties.definition: The pressure at which the spring or weight in the valve is set to discharge fluid.

Pset_VegetationCommon.name: Pset_VegetationCommon
Pset_VegetationCommon.definition: Properties for vegetation and plants, modelled as instances of IfcGeographicElement with the predefined type set to VEGETATION.

properties.name: BotanicalName
properties.definition: Formal scientific name conforming to the International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (ICN)

properties.name: LocalName
properties.definition: The local name that the plant is known as.

Pset_VehicleAvailability.name: Pset_VehicleAvailability
Pset_VehicleAvailability.definition: Property set for the application of availability data to vehicles and equipment.

properties.name: VehicleAvailability
properties.definition: Vehicle or Plant availability

properties.name: MaintenanceDowntime
properties.definition: Maintenance downtime proportion.

properties.name: WeatherDowntime
properties.definition: Weather downtime proportion

Pset_VesselLineCommon.name: Pset_VesselLineCommon
Pset_VesselLineCommon.definition: Properties for vessel lines and anchoring

properties.name: LineIdentifier
properties.definition: Reference ID relative to a design vessel in the project

properties.name: MidshipToFairLead

properties.name: CentreLineToFairlead
properties.definition: Distance from the vessel centreline to the fairlead for the line

properties.name: HeightAboveMainDeck
properties.definition: Height of the fairlead above the main deck of the vessel

properties.name: FairleadToTermination

properties.name: WinchBreakLimit

properties.name: PreTensionAim
properties.definition: Line force that the winch is set to maintain (minimum load)

properties.name: LineType

properties.name: LineStrength
properties.definition: Breaking load of the line (note that ultimate stress is not part of any of the material Psets)

properties.name: TailLength
properties.definition: Length of the tail

properties.name: TailDiameter
properties.definition: Diameter of the tail

properties.name: TailType
properties.definition: Mooring tail type

properties.name: TailStrength
properties.definition: Breaking load of the tail (note that ultimate stress is not part of any of the material Psets)

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: VibrationTransmissibility
properties.definition: The vibration transmissibility percentage.

properties.name: IsolatorStaticDeflection
properties.definition: Static deflection of the vibration isolator.

properties.name: IsolatorCompressibility
properties.definition: The compressibility of the vibration isolator.

properties.name: MaximumSupportedWeight
properties.definition: The maximum weight that can be carried by the vibration isolator.

properties.name: NominalHeight
properties.definition:
The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Height of the vibration isolator before the application of load.

Pset_VoltageInstrumentTransformer.name: Pset_VoltageInstrumentTransformer
Pset_VoltageInstrumentTransformer.definition: Instrument transformers are high accuracy class electrical devices used to isolate or transform voltage or current levels. The main function of instrument transformers is to operate instruments or metering from high voltage or high current circuits, safely isolating secondary control circuitry from the high voltages or currents. Combination instrument transformers are metering voltage.

properties.name: AccuracyClass
properties.definition: A designation assigned to an instrument transformer the current (or voltage) error and phase displacement of which remain within specified limits under prescribed conditions of use (IEC 321-01-24).

properties.name: AccuracyGrade
properties.definition: The grade of accuracy.

properties.name: RatedVoltage
properties.definition: The range of allowed voltage that a device is certified to handle. The upper bound of this value is the maximum.

properties.name: NominalCurrent
properties.definition: The nominal current that is designed to be measured.

properties.name: NominalPower
properties.definition: A conventional value of apparent power determining a value of the rated current that may be carried with rated voltage applied, under specified conditions. ( IEV ref 421-04-04)

properties.name: NumberOfPhases
properties.definition: Number of phases that the equipment operates on.

properties.name: PrimaryFrequency
properties.definition: The frequency that is going to be transformed and that runs into the transformer on the primary side.

properties.name: PrimaryVoltage
properties.definition: The voltage that is going to be transformed and that runs into the transformer on the primary side.

properties.name: SecondaryFrequency
properties.definition: The frequency that has been transformed and is running out of the transformer on the secondary side.

properties.name: SecondaryVoltage
properties.definition: The voltage that has been transformed and is running out of the transformer on the secondary side.

Pset_WallCommon.name: Pset_WallCommon
Pset_WallCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcWall.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: AcousticRating
properties.definition:
Acoustic rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code. It indicates the sound transmission resistance of this object by an index ratio (instead of providing full sound absorption values).

properties.name: FireRating
properties.definition: Fire rating for this object. It is given according to the national fire safety classification.

properties.name: Combustible
properties.definition: Indication whether the object is made from combustible material (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: SurfaceSpreadOfFlame
properties.definition:
Indication on how the flames spread around the surface,
It is given according to the national building code that governs the fire behaviour for materials.

properties.name: ThermalTransmittance
properties.definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of an element, within the direction of the thermal flow (including all materials).

properties.name: IsExternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

properties.name: LoadBearing
properties.definition: Indicates whether the object is intended to carry loads (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: ExtendToStructure
properties.definition: Indicates whether the object extend to the structure above (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: Compartmentation
properties.definition: Indication whether the object is designed to serve as a fire compartmentation (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Pset_Warranty.name: Pset_Warranty
Pset_Warranty.definition: An assurance given by the seller or provider of an artefact that the artefact is without defects and will operate as described for a defined period of time without failure and that if a defect does arise during that time, that it will be corrected by the seller or provider.

properties.name: WarrantyIdentifier
properties.definition: The identifier assigned to a warranty.

properties.name: WarrantyStartDate
properties.definition: The date on which the warranty commences.

properties.name: IsExtendedWarranty
properties.definition: Indication of whether this is an extended warranty whose duration is greater than that normally assigned to an artefact (=TRUE) or not (= FALSE).

properties.name: WarrantyPeriod
properties.definition: The time duration during which a manufacturer or supplier guarantees or warrants the performance of an artefact.

properties.name: WarrantyContent
properties.definition: The content of the warranty.

properties.name: PointOfContact
properties.definition: The organization that should be contacted for action under the terms of the warranty. Note that the role of the organization (manufacturer, supplier, installer etc.) is determined by the IfcActorRole attribute of IfcOrganization.

properties.name: Exclusions

properties.name: TransitionWidth

In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

Pset_WindowCommon.name: Pset_WindowCommon
Pset_WindowCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of Window.

properties.name: Reference
properties.definition: Reference ID for this specified type in this project (e.g. type 'A-1'), Also referred to as "construction type". It should be provided as an alternative to the name of the "object type", if the software does not support object types and no classification reference to a recognized classification system used.IFC4.3.0.0 DEPRECATION  The Reference property is deprecated and shall no longer be used, use attribute Name on the relating type instead.

properties.name: Status
properties.definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished,  "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

properties.name: AcousticRating
properties.definition:
Acoustic rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code. It indicates the sound transmission resistance of this object by an index ratio (instead of providing full sound absorption values).

properties.name: FireRating
properties.definition: Fire rating for this object. It is given according to the national fire safety classification.

properties.name: SecurityRating
properties.definition:
Index based rating system indicating security level.
It is giving according to the national building code.

properties.name: IsExternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If (TRUE) it is an external element and faces the outside of the building.

properties.name: Infiltration
properties.definition: Infiltration flowrate of outside air for the filler object based on the area of the filler object at a pressure level of 50 Pascals. It shall be used, if the length of all joints is unknown.

properties.name: ThermalTransmittance
properties.definition: Thermal transmittance coefficient (U-Value) of an element, within the direction of the thermal flow (including all materials).

properties.name: GlazingAreaFraction
properties.definition:
Fraction of the glazing area relative to the total area of the filling element.
It shall be used, if the glazing area is not given separately for all panels within the filling element.

properties.name: HasSillExternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the window opening has an external sill (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: HasSillInternal
properties.definition: Indication whether the window opening has an internal sill (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: HasDrive
properties.definition: Indication whether this object has an automatic drive to operate it (TRUE) or no drive (FALSE)

properties.name: SmokeStop
properties.definition: Indication whether the object is designed to provide a smoke stop (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: FireExit
properties.definition:
Indication whether this object is designed to serve as an exit in the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Here it defines an exit window in accordance to the national building code.

properties.name: WaterTightnessRating
properties.definition:
Water tightness rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code.

properties.name: MechanicalLoadRating
properties.definition:
Mechanical load rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code.

properties.name: WindLoadRating
properties.definition:
Wind load resistance rating for this object.
It is provided according to the national building code.

Pset_WindowLiningProperties.name: Pset_WindowLiningProperties
Pset_WindowLiningProperties.definition: Properties of the window lining.HISTORY New property set in IFC4.3.2.0 to replace the entity IfcWindowLiningProperties

properties.name: LiningDepth
properties.definition:
The depth of the lining.

For a window, it is the depth of the window lining, measured perpendicularly to window elevation plane.

properties.name: LiningThickness
properties.definition:
Thickness of the lining.

For a window, it is the thickness of the window lining as explained in the figure below. If LiningThickness value is 0. (zero) it denotes a window without a lining (all other lining parameters shall be set to NIL in this case). If the LiningThickness is NIL it denotes that the value is not available.

properties.name: TransomThickness
properties.definition:
Thickness of the transom.

For a window, it is the thickness of the transom (horizontal separator of window panels within a window), measured parallel to the window elevation plane. The transom is part of the lining and the transom depth is assumed to be identical to the lining depth. If the TransomThickness is set to zero (and the TransomOffset set to a positive length), then the window is divided vertically without a physical divider.

properties.name: MullionThickness
properties.definition:
Thickness of the mullion.

For a window, it is the thickness of the mullion (i.e., the vertical separator of window panels within a window), measured parallel to the window elevation plane. The mullion is part of the lining and the mullion depth is assumed to be identical to the lining depth. If the MullionThickness is set to zero (and the MullionOffset set to a positive length), then the window is divided horizontally without a physical divider.

properties.name: FirstTransomOffset
properties.definition: Offset of the transom centerline, measured along the z-axis of the window placement coordinate system. An offset value = 0.5 indicates that the transom is positioned in the middle of the window.

properties.name: SecondTransomOffset
properties.definition: Offset of the transom centerline for the second transom, measured along the x-axis of the window placement co-ordinate system. An offset value = 0.666 indicates that the second transom is positioned at two/third of the window.

properties.name: FirstMullionOffset
properties.definition: Offset of the mullion centerline, measured along the x-axis of the window placement coordinate system. An offset value = 0.5 indicates that the mullion is positioned in the middle of the window.

properties.name: SecondMullionOffset
properties.definition: Offset of the mullion centerline for the second mullion, measured along the x-axis of the window placement co-ordinate system. An offset value = 0.666 indicates that the second mullion is positioned at two/third of the window.

properties.name: LiningOffset
properties.definition:
Offset of the lining.

For a window, it is the offset of the window lining, given as distance along the y axis of the local placement (perpendicular to the window plane).

properties.name: LiningToPanelOffsetX
properties.definition:
Offset between the lining and the panel, measured along the x-axis of the local placement.

For a window, it is the offset between the lining and the window panel. Should be smaller or equal to the LiningThickness.

properties.name: LiningToPanelOffsetY
properties.definition:
Offset between the lining and the panel, measured along the y-axis of the local placement.

For a window, it is the offset between the lining and the window panel. Should be smaller or equal to the IfcWindowPanelProperties.PanelThickness.

Pset_WindowPanelProperties.name: Pset_WindowPanelProperties
Pset_WindowPanelProperties.definition: Properties of the window panel.HISTORY New property set in IFC4.3.2.0 to replace the entity IfcWindowPanelProperties

properties.name: OperationType
properties.definition:
Type of operations. Also used to assign standard symbolic presentations according to national building standards.

For a window, it is the type of window panel operations. Also used to assign standard symbolic presentations according to national building standards.

properties.name: PanelPosition
properties.definition:
Position of the panel.

For a window, it is the position of the panel within the overall window style.

properties.name: FrameDepth
properties.definition:
The length (or depth) of the frame.

For a window, it is the depth of panel frame, measured from front face to back face horizontally (i.e. perpendicular to the window elevation plane).

properties.name: FrameThickness
properties.definition:
The thickness of the frame.

For a window, it is the width of panel frame, measured from inside of panel (at glazing) to outside of panel (at lining), i.e. parallel to the window (elevation) plane.

Pset_WorkControlCommon.name: Pset_WorkControlCommon
Pset_WorkControlCommon.definition: Properties common to the definition of all occurrences of IfcWorkPlan and IfcWorkSchedule (subtypes of IfcWorkControl).

properties.name: WorkStartTime
properties.definition: The default time of day a task is scheduled to start. For presentation purposes, if the start time of a task matches the WorkStartTime, then applications may choose to display the date only. Conversely when entering dates without specifying time, applications may automatically append the WorkStartTime.

properties.name: WorkFinishTime
properties.definition: The default time of day a task is scheduled to finish. For presentation purposes, if the finish time of a task matches the WorkFinishTime, then applications may choose to display the date only. Conversely when entering dates without specifying time, applications may automatically append the WorkFinishTime.

properties.name: WorkDayDuration
properties.definition: The elapsed time within a worktime-based day. For presentation purposes, applications may choose to display IfcTask durations in work days where IfcTaskTime.DurationType=WORKTIME. This value must be less than or equal to 24 hours (an elapsed day); if omitted then 8 hours is assumed.

properties.name: WorkWeekDuration
properties.definition: The elapsed time within a worktime-based week. For presentation purposes, applications may choose to display IfcTask durations in work weeks where IfcTaskTime.DurationType=WORKTIME. This value must be less than or equal to 168 hours (an elapsed week); if omitted then 40 hours is assumed.

properties.name: WorkMonthDuration
properties.definition: The elapsed time within a worktime-based month. For presentation purposes, applications may choose to display IfcTask durations in work months where IfcTaskTime.DurationType=WORKTIME. This value must be less than or equal to 744 hours (an elapsed month of 31 days); if omitted then 160 hours is assumed.

properties.name: NetPlannedArea

properties.name: PubliclyAccessible
properties.definition: Indication whether this space (in case of e.g., a toilet) is designed to serve as a publicly accessible space, e.g., for a public toilet (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

properties.name: HandicapAccessible
properties.definition: Indication that this object is designed to be accessible by the handicapped. Set to (TRUE) if this object is rated as handicap accessible according to the local building codes, otherwise (FALSE). It is giving according to the requirements of the national building code.

properties.name: Length
properties.definition:
The length of the object.

Not taking into account any cut-out's or other processing features.

properties.name: CrossSectionArea
properties.definition: Total area of the cross section (or profile) of the object.

properties.name: OuterSurfaceArea
properties.definition: Total area of the surfaces of the object (not taking into account the end cap areas), normally generated as perimeter * length in case of extrusions.

properties.name: GrossSurfaceArea
properties.definition: Total gross area of the object, normally generated as perimeter * length + 2 * cross section area. It is the sum of OuterSurfaceArea + (2 x CrossSectionArea) and shall only be given, if the OuterSurfaceArea and CrossSectionArea cannot be established separately.

properties.name: NetSurfaceArea

properties.name: GrossVolume

properties.name: GrossWeight

Qto_BodyGeometryValidation.name: Qto_BodyGeometryValidation
Qto_BodyGeometryValidation.definition: Quantities supplied for validating the correct interpretation of the body shape representation at import. In case of multiple representation items, the quantities are summed for each of the items (irrespective of any overlap). Choosing a suitable tolerance value for comparing the supplied numbers to the numbers calculated from the reconstructed geometry is at the discretion of the importing application.

properties.name: GrossSurfaceArea
properties.definition:
Total gross area of the object, normally generated as perimeter * length + 2 * cross section area. It is the sum of OuterSurfaceArea + (2 x CrossSectionArea) and shall only be given, if the OuterSurfaceArea and CrossSectionArea cannot be established separately.

Total gross surface area of the element before applying product-level geometric features such as openings and projections.

properties.name: NetSurfaceArea
properties.definition:
Net surface area of the object, normally generated as perimeter * length + 2 * cross section area taking into account possible processing features (cut-out's, etc.) or openings and recesses.

Total net surface area of the element after applying product-level geometric features such as openings and projections.

properties.name: GrossVolume
properties.definition:
Total gross volume of the object. Openings, recesses, enclosed objects and projections are not taken into account.

Total gross volume of the element before applying product-level geometric features such as openings and projections.

properties.name: NetVolume
properties.definition:
Total net volume of the object, taking into account possible processing features (cut-out's, etc.) or openings and recesses.

Total net volume of the element before applying product-level geometric features such as openings and projections.

properties.name: SurfaceGenusBeforeFeatures
properties.definition: The Surface Genus of the evaluated representation items before applying product-level geometric features such as openings and projections.Surface Genus is a topological measure that represents the number of "holes" or "handles" on a surface. For example, a sphere has genus 0, and a torus has genus 1.Computed using the Euler characteristic:$$\chi=V-E+F$$With the numbers of vertices (V), edges (E) and faces (F)$$\chi=22gb$$With surface genus (g) and the number of boundaries (b) the latter zero in case of an enclosed volume.

properties.name: SurfaceGenusAfterFeatures
properties.definition: The Surface Genus of the evaluated representation items after applying product-level geometric features such as openings and projections.Surface Genus is a topological measure that represents the number of "holes" or "handles" on a surface. For example, a sphere has genus 0, and a torus has genus 1.Computed using the Euler characteristic:$$\chi=V-E+F$$With the numbers of vertices (V), edges (E) and faces (F)$$\chi=22gb$$With surface genus (g) and the number of boundaries (b) the latter zero in case of an enclosed volume.
